Finland, member, Intl. Committee Nomencl. Alg., Dr. h.c. 1950 Univ. of Helsinki, died 20 Apr 1962 in Tammisaari.

name: *Groenhart, Pieter
description: Dutch lichenologist, born in Ilpendam, schoolteacher in The Netherlands 1916-1926, to Java in Aug 1926, stationed at Batavia, then taught at School of Agriculture in Malang (E. Java) until 1940, studied biology, Utrecht 1932-1936, returned to Indonesia and Buitenzorg, working one day per week in the herb., briefly at Leiden 1947, returned again to Indonesia but ultimately settled in The Netherlands, died 3 Nov 1965 in Oegstgeest (Leiden).

name: Groenland [Grönland], Johannes
description: German horticulturist and microscopist, born 8 Apr 1824 in Altona (Hamburg), trained as a druggist, joined the Schleswig-Holstein army 1849, moved to Paris 1853 as an asst. to Louis Vilmorin and began editing Revue Horticole, returned to Germany after the Franco-Prussian War (1870-1871) and settled in Dahme (nr. Potsdam) as prof. of natural sciences, Agricultural and Agricultural Chemistry Research Station 1872-1891, died 13 Feb 1891 in Dahme.

name: *Grønlund [Groenlund, Grönlund], [Carl] Christian [Howitz]
description: Danish botanist, born 14 Jul 1825 in Vordingborg, studied theology 1850, traveled in Iceland 1868 and 1876, taught botany in Copenhagen until 1879 when appointed manager of the Physiological Laboratory of Nv. Carlsberg (a brewery), died 10 Aug 1901 in Copenhagen.

name: Grøntved [Gröntved], Johannes
description: Danish floristic botanist, born 25 Jan 1882 in Mygdad, Ph.D. 1917 Copenhagen, amanuensis in Botanical Museum 1918-1934, died 11 Jul 1956.

name: Grøntved, Julius
description: Danish algologist interested in diatoms and phytoplankton, Mag. scient., Univ. Planteanatomiske Laboratorium, Copenhagen 1931 (at least), PlanktonLaboratoriet, Copenhagen 1945 (at least).

name: Grönvall, [Troed] Axel Ludvig
description: Swedish bryologist, born 31 Mar 1838 in Söfvestad (Skåne), Ph.D. 1859 Lund, taught at Malmö 1861, died 16 Nov 1892 in Malmö.

name: Groff, G[eorge]. Weidman
description: American horticulturist and "agricultural missionary", born 29 Mar 1884 in Annville (Lebanon Co.), Penn., attended school in Har- risburg, Penn., B.Sc. 1907 and M.S. 1912 (horticulture) Penn. State College (now Penn. State Univ.), State College, Penn., went to China in 1907 and from 1908 served as middle school teacher, Canton Christian College, then held positions as Field Asst., Office of Crop Physiology and Breeding Investigation, U.S.D.A. and in the herb., Lingnan Univ. 1918- 1920, Canton (now Guangzhou), Dean and Dir., Agricultural College 1921-1935 and Dir., Economic Plant Receiving Station 1935, both Lingnan Univ., moved to Florida 1941 (dur- ing W.W.-II), worked in s. China for the U.N. Relief and Rehabilitation Administration 1946-1947, died 4 Dec 1954 in Laurel, Florida.

name: *Gronovius, Johan [Jan] Frederik
description: No description provided.

name: Groom, Percy
description: English botanist, born 12 Sep 1865 in Wellington (Shropshire), B.A. 1887 Cambridge, prof. of botany and arboriculture, Imperial College, Whampoa (now Huangpu), China 1889-1892, lecturer in botany at various colleges in Great Britain 18921908, ultimately asst. prof. of botany and then prof. of technology of woods and fibres, Imperial College of Science & Technology (London) 1908-1931, F.R.S. 1924, M.A., D.Sc. Oxford, F.L.S., died 16 Sep 1931 in Gerrards Cross (Bucks.).

name: Grossheim [Grossgeim], Alexander [Aleksandr] Alphonsovitch [Alfonsovich]
description: Ukrainian-born Soviet botanist, born 6 Mar 1888 in Lichovka nr. Verchnedneprovsk, Ekaterinoslav (from 1926 Dnipropetrovsk), educated at Karkov, Moscow and Tiflis (Tibilisi), worked at Tiflis Botanic Garden, Baku 1929-1946 and then in Leningrad 1946-1948, died 4 Dec 1948 in Leningrad.

name: *Grout, Abel Joel
description: American bryologist, born 24 Mar 1867 in Newfane (Windham Co.), Vermont, Ph.B. 1890 Univ. of Vermont, Ph.D. 1897 Columbia College, New York, New York (under Elizabeth G. Britton), taught at various high-schools in Vermont, New Hampshire and New York state until retirement in 1930 when he was made a research staff member, Cold Spring Harbor Lab., Long Island, New York and hon. curator of mosses, New York Botanical Garden 1943-1947, died 27 Mar 1947 in East Bradenton, Florida, "My interest in mosses began in the early [18]90's largely because I could collect and study them in winter ...."

name: *Grove, William Bywater
description: British mycologist, born 24 Oct 1848 in Birmingham (Warks.), B.A. 1871 Cambridge, headmaster, Birmingham School for Boys at Queen's College 1887-1900, lecturer in botany, Studley Horticultural College (Warks.) 1900-1908 and then Birmingham Municipal Technical School, 1905-1927, hon. Curator, Fungus Herb., Univ. of Birmingham, president Birmingham Natural History Society, M.Sc. (h.c.) 1936, died 6 Jan 1938 in Birmingham.

name: Groves, Enrico (b. Henry)
description: English pharmacist and botanist, born in Weymouth (Dorset), settled in Florence, Italy 1862 where he came to own a pharmacy, collected vigorously during the summers when business was at a stand-still, F.L.S. 1884, died 1 Mar 1891 in Florence.

name: *Groves, Henry
description: British botanist interested in Characeae and nomenclature, born 15 Oct 1855 in London, employed as a stockbroker until 1879, then by Queen Anne's Bounty Office until his death, F.L.S. 1892, died 2 Nov 1912 in London (Clapham).

name: *Groves, James
description: British algologist and paleontologist interested in Characeae, born 19 Jan 1858 in London, worked in Army and Navy Stores until retirement in 1918, F.L.S. 1885, died 20 Mar 1933 in Trevarthian (or Freshwater Bay), Isle of Wight.

name: Groves, J[ames]. Walton
description: Canadian mycologist, born 18 Oct 1906 in Kinburn, Ontario, graduated from Ottawa Normal School, taught public school in Ottawa 1926- 1928, B.A. 1930 Queens' Univ., Kingston, Ontario, M.A. 1932 and Ph.D. 1935 Univ. of Toronto, mycologist, Dept. of Agriculture, Ottawa 1936-1970, incl. chief, Mycology Sect. 1951-1967, Fellow Royal Soc. Canada 1951, founding member I.A.P.T. and served on special committee on Fungi and Lichens 1950-1970, died 6 Mai 1970 in Ottawa.

name: Grubb, Violet Margaret
description: British algologist and missionary, B.Sc. 1920, M.Sc. 1922 and D.Sc. 1926, Westfield College, Univ. of London, visit to Changsa, Hunan, China 1926 evidently sponsored by the Church Missionary Society, F.L.S., later in the Botanical Dept., Westfield College (at Hampstead).

name: Gruber, Eduard A.
description: German phycologist, "aus Freiburg. i. B." (i.e. Freiburg im Breisgau, just N of Basel in Switzerland), doctorate 1896 Univ. of Basel.

name: *Grummann, Vitus Johannes
description: German teacher and amateur lichenologist, born 3 Mar 1899 in Jacobsdorf (Oberschlesien), military service 1917-1918 (i.e. W.W.-I), teacher in Berlin 1920-1942 and again after W.W.-II, Ph.D. 1941 Berlin, retired 1963, died 9 [12?] Dec 1967 in Berlin.

name: Gruner, Leopold Fedorovich
description: Russian-born German field botanist, born 2/14 Oct 1839 in Livland (then a Russian province), collected plants with Eduard Lehmann.

name: *Grunow [Grunov], Albert
description: German chemist and amateur but important diatomologist, born 3 Nov 1826 in Berlin, removed to Berndorf, Austria in 1857 where he worked, died 19 [17?] Mar 1914 in Berndorf.

name: Guadagno, Michele
description: Italian botanist, born 16 Oct 1878 in Naples, titled himself as "Ing." in early papers, esp. interested in the flora of the isl. of Capri, died 10 Sep 1930 in Naples.

name: Guba, Emil Frederick
description: American mycologist and plant pathologist, born 13 Mai 1897 in New Bedford, Mass., B.Sc. 1919 Mass. Agricultural College (now Univ. of Mass.), Amherst, Ph.D. 1923 Univ. of Illinois, plant pathologist, Cornell Univ., Ithaca, New York 1923-1925, asst. prof. 1925 and prof. 1939, Mass. Agricultural College Field Station (a.k.a. Market Garden Field Station), Waltham, Mass., retired 1962, died 16 Mar 1999 in Kingston, Mass. (buried in Waltham).

name: Gubb, Alfred Samuel (M.D.)
description: British doctor (gynecologist and/or obstetrician) and amateur botanist, resided in London (1889) and then Paris (1892), at least, doctorate 1893 Faculty of Medicine, Paris.

name: Gubler, [Nicolas] Adolphe Marie
description: French physician, pharmacologist and botanist, born 4 Apr 1821 in Metz (Moselle), studied medicine in Paris 1841, traveled in Italy, returned to Paris and obtained his doctorate 1849, Prof., Faculty of Medicine, Paris 1858-1879, Académie de médecine 1865, published extensively on human anatomy, physicology and clinical medicine, vice-president, Société Botanique de France, died 20 Apr 1879 in Val Margue nr. Toulon (Var).

name: Guebhard, Ch.
description: Romanian botanist.

name: *Gümbel, [Wilhelm] Theodor (von)
description: German bryologist, born 19 Mar 1812 in Dannenfels (Palatinate), older brother of Carl Wilhelm Gümbel (1823-1898, who became a geologist and also studied mosses), dir. of a secondary school in Landau (Palatinate), died 10 Feb 1858 in Landau.

name: Günthart, [Emil] August
description: Swiss botanist, born 8 Jul 1879 in Frauenfeld (Kt. Thurgau), Ph.D. 1902 Zürich, teacher in girls' schools in Barmen 1902-1905 and Zürich 1905-1912, leader of the mathematics/natural history division of the Teubner Press in Leipzig 1912-1917, Dir., Botanical Garden, Frauenfeld from 1920, died 22 Apr 1957 in Frauenfeld.

page_title_longer_max-80: Gürke [Guerke], Robert Louis August Maximilian [Max] [std. Gürke] (Suppl.)
name: *Gürke [Guerke], Robert Louis August Maximilian [Max]
description: German (Silesian) botanist, born 17 Nov 1854 in Beuthen an der Oder (Oberschlesien) (now Poland), studied natural history and mathematics 1873-1880, taught in Görliz 1880-1884, asst. at Berlin 1886, Ph.D. 1892 Göttingen, asst. curator ("Hilfkustos") 1892, curator ("Kustos") 1893-1911 and Prof. 1904, all Botanical Garden and Museum, Berlin, studied at Kew 1895, died 16 Mar 1911 in Berlin (Steglitz).

name: Güssow [Gussow], Hans Theodor
description: German-born Canadian mycologist and plant pathologist, born 24 Aug 1879 in Breslau, studied applied botany and subsequently plant pathology and bacteriology in Breslau, Leipzig and Berlin, worked in England from 1901-1909 and as asst. to William Carruthers from 1903 to 1909, Dominion Botanist and head of the Botany Division of the Experimental Farms Branch, Ottawa, Canada 1909-1944, Assoc. Dir., Science Service of the Dept. of Agriculture 1938-x, LL.D. 1931 Queen's Univ., Kingston, Ontario, Fellow, Royal Society of Canada 1931, died 15 Jun 1961 in Victoria, British Columbia, Canada.

name: Guest, Evan Rhuvon
description: British agronomist and botanist, born 24 Jan 1902 in London, educated at Eton, B.Sc. 1924 Imperial College, London, Southeastern Agricultural College, Wye (Kent) ca. 1925, Imperial College of Tropical Agriculture, Trinidad ca. 1926, followed by two years in the Anglo-Egyptian Sudan, held various agricultural postings in Iraq through 1933, agricultural advisor, I.C.I. (Malaya) in London 1934-1937, botanist, Rubber Inst., Kuala Lumpur 1937-1940, B.B.C. Foreign Service in London and Cairo during W.W.-II, again in Iraq 1953-1958, returned to London and worked at Kew on the Flora of Iraq until 1987, died 4 Mar 1992.

name: *Guettard, Jean-Étienne
description: French physician, geologist and naturalist, born 22 Sep 1715 in Étampes (Île de France), studied botany under Bernard de Jussieu, Faculty of Medicine, Paris 1742, from 1747 "médecin botaniste" to and keeper of the Duc d'Orléans's natural history collection, he was the first to survey and geologically map France and to observe the exposed bedrock of the Paris Basin, died 6 [7?] Jan 1786 in Paris.

name: Guffroy, Charles Émile
description: French botanist and mycologist, Lic. ès-sciences, Ingénieur-agronome, Paris.

page_title_longer_max-80: Gugelberg von Moos, Maria [Marie] (Barbara Flandrina) [std. Gugelb.]
name: Gugelberg von Moos, Maria [Marie] (Barbara Flandrina)
description: Swiss bryologist and hepaticologist, born 6 Feb 1836 in Schloss Salenegg bei Maienfeld (Kt. Graubünden), studied in Maienfeld and Neuchâtel, evidently also collaborated with Christian Gregor Brügger, died 29 Oct 1918 in Maienfeld.

name: Gugerli, Karl
description: Swiss botanist, born 17 Mar 1910 in Zurich, Ph.D. 1940 Univ. of Zurich.

name: Guilfoyle, William Robert
description: British-born Australian landscape gardener, botanist and civil servant, born 8 Dec 1840 in Chelsea (London), emigrated to Sydney, Australia 1853 with his family where his father, Michael Guilfoyle (1809-1884), established an active nursery business, attended Lyndhurst College, Glebe (Sydney), sailed (as "tourist") aboard H.M.S. Challenger in Pacific Ocean Mai-Oct 1868, farmed sugar cane and tobacco, Tweed River, n.e. New South Wales, appointed curator (i.e. Dir.), Royal Botanic Gardens, Mel- bourne 1873, and concentrated on transforming the gardens rather than on science as did his predecessor F. von Mueller, visited England and Europe 1890-1891 and 1896, retired because of ill health 1909, F.L.S., died 25 Jun 1912 in East Melbourne.

name: Guillaud, Jean-Alexandre
description: French botanist, born 12 Feb 1849 in Aumagne (Charente-Inférieure), Prof., Faculty of Medicine and Pharmacy, Bordeaux, Dr. ès-sciences naturelles 1878 Paris, collected fungi in s.w. France 1883-1884, died 18 Nov 1923 in Saintes (Charente-Maritime).

name: Guillaume, André
description: French lawyer and botanist, born 3 Aug 1883 in Reims, Dr. en droit 1904 Univ. of Paris, Dr. ès-sciences 1923 Univ. of Paris, practiced law in Reims, died 17 Jun 1963 in Paris.

page_title_longer_max-80: Guillaumin, André [Louis Joseph Edmond Armand] [std. Guillaumin] (Suppl.)
name: *Guillaumin, André [Louis Joseph Edmond Armand]
description: French botanist and explorer, born 21 Jun 1885 in Arrou (Eure-et-Loir), Lic. ès-sciences 1906, "preparateur", Lab. de Phanérogamie, Muséum natl. d'Histoire naturelle, Paris 1909 (under Henri Lecomte), Dr. ès-sciences 1910 Paris, sub-dir. 1927-1950 and prof. 1932-1956, Lab. de Culture (i.e. horticulture), Muséum natl. d'Histoire naturelle, Paris, President, Société Botanique de France 1935, retired Oct 1956, died 24 Mai 1974 in Athis-Mons (Essonne).

name: *Guillemin, [Jean Baptiste] Antoine
description: French botanist and traveler, born 20 Jan 1796 in Pouilly-sur-Saône (Côtes-d'Or), apprenticed to a pharmacy in Dijon 1812, moved to Geneva 1814 where he studied under Jean Pierre Vaucher and then A.P. de Candolle, moved to Paris 1820 where eventually he succeeded Achille Richard as curator of Benjamin Delessert's herb. and library 1827-1842, simultaneously "aide-préparateur" 1827 and "aide naturaliste" to the botany chair (succeeding Adolphe T. Brongniart) 1834, Muséum natl. d'Histoire naturelle, Paris, Dr. en médecine 1832 Paris, sent on a government sponsored mission to Brazil 1838-1839, died 13 [15?] Jan 1842 shortly after moving to Montpellier.

name: Guilliermond, [Marie Antoine] Alexandre
description: French mycologist (specializing in yeasts) and cytologist, born 19 Aug 1876 in Lyon, doctorate 1902 Lyon, Faculty of Sciences, Lyon, then from 1921 in Paris where he became prof., Faculty of Sciences at the Sorbonne, Académie des Sciences 1935, president, Société Botanique de France, died 1 Apr 1945 in Lyon.

name: Guinet, [Jean Étienne] Auguste
description: Swiss businessman and botanist, born 23 Mai 1846 in Carouge (Geneva), he botanized during his free time and became a member of the Bot. Soc. Geneva in 1877 (when founded), built a considerable herb. that was incorporated into the Delessert Herb., after 1879 he began microscope studies of cryptogams, particularly lich., then mosses and hepatics, from 1908 asst. curator of mosses at Geneva (under J.I. Briquet), retired 1925, died 3 Aug 1928 in Geneva.

page_title_longer_max-80: Guinier, [Marie Joseph Jean Baptiste] Philibert [std. Guinier]
name: Guinier, [Marie Joseph Jean Baptiste] Philibert ('la bique' to his students)
description: French forester, ecologist and administrator, born 21 Jun 1876 in Grenoble, studied at the National Inst. of Agronomy 1895-1897, then at the École Nationale des Eaux et Forêts, Nancy 1897-1899, asst., forestry research station 1901, instructor of forest botany 1904-1921 and dir. 1921-1941, all at the École Nationale des Eaux et Forêts, retired 1941, Académie d'agriculture de France 1936, president, Société Botanique de France 1946, Légion d'honneur 1948, Académie des Sciences 1953, died 3 Apr 1962 in Paris.

name: Guinochet, [Jean-Étienne] Marcel
description: French phycologist and botanist with interests and influence in phytosociology and biosystematics, born 21 Dec 1909 in Lyon, Lic. ès-sciences naturelles 1931, asst.-"préparateur", Centre de Recherches Agronomiques de Provence (Villa Thuret) in Antibes (Alpes-Maritimes), Dr. ès-sciences 1938 Grenoble, taught in Montpellier 1939-1943, during and after W.W-II held a number of university positions in quick succession, incl. Besançon 1943-1945, Nancy 1945-1946 and Stras- bourg 1946, succeeded René Maire as prof., Faculty of Sciences, Univ. of Alger, Alge- ria 1950-1957, returned to France and joined the Faculty of Sciences, Paris (Orsay) from 1958 until retirement in 1977, president, Société Botanique de France, died 22 Aug 1997 in Fayence (Var).

name: Guppy, Henry Brougham
description: English geologist interested in isls. and seed and plant dispersal by water, born 23 Dec 1854 in Falmouth (Cornwall), educated at King's School, Sherborne, Queen's College, Birmingham, Medical School of St. Bartholomew's Hospital, M.B. 1876 and C.M., Edinburgh Univ., surgeon in Royal Navy 1876-1885, served on the China Station 1877-1880 and on the Australian Station 1881-1884, F.R.S.E. 1888, F.L.S. (Gold Medal) and F.R.S. 1918, died 23 Apr 1926 on board El Kantara in Martinique (remains interred at Seaton).

name: *Gussone, Giovanni
description: Italian botanist, born 18 Feb 1787 in Villamina (Avellino), studied medicine, Univ. of Naples 1811, began collaborating with Michele Tenore in 1810 while still a student, dir., botanical gardens in Boccadifalco nr. Palermo and Caserta nr. Naples, succeeded Tenore as dir., botanical gardens in Naples 1861, died 14 Jan 1866 in Naples.

name: Gustafsson, Carl Emil
description: Swedish botanist, in Trälleborg (Trelleborg) ca. 1921.

name: *Guşuleac, Mihail [Michail]
description: Ukrainian (Soviet) morphologist and botanist, born 12 Oct 1887 in Csernovic (then Austro-Hungarian Empire, now Chernivtsi, Ukraine), graduated 1911 and awarded doctorate 1917, both Franz-Josefs Universität (later Universitatea Regele Carol I din Cernăuţi), Dir., Univ. of Cernăuţi Botanic Garden 1919 (from 1918-1940 Cernăuţi (Chernivtsi) was part of the Kingdom of Romania), died 11 Sep 1960 in Chernivtsi, Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic.

name: Gutner, Lidia Solomonovna
description: Russian mycologist, born 13 Jun 1903 in Mogilev oblast, Belarus, graduated 1925 Leningrad State Univ., trainee and lab. assist. 1925- 1930, Leningrad Agricultural Inst., lab. assist. and ultimately assist. dir. 1930-1932, 1935- 1942, Lab. of Systematics, All-Union Inst. of Plant Protection, plant pathologist 1933-1934, All-Union State Association of Pest Control & Agricultural Diseases, died 4 Feb 1942 in Kotlas, U.S.S.R. (now Russia).

name: Gutwiński [Gutwinski], Roman
description: Polish phycologist, born 4 Jun 1860 in Pagorzyne (Gorlice District), studied at Jaslo College 1871-1878 and then Krakow Univ. 1878-1882, assisted J.T. Rostafińsky until 1885, taught at various secondary schools incl. schools in Podgorze nr. Krakow 1892-1900 and finally Krakow 1900-1924, where he died 27 Oct 1932.

name: Guyot, Alain Lucien
description: French mycologist, prof. of botany and phytopathology, École Nationale Supérieure d'Agriculture de Grignon (Seine-et-Oise), and from 1932 dir. of the Jardin Botanique there, studied rust fungi of s. France and n. Africa (Morocco, Tunisia).

name: Guyot, Arnaud [Arnold] Henri [Henry]
description: Swiss-born American geographer, paleontologist, meteorologist and naturalist, born 28 Sep 1807 in Boudevilliers nr. Neuchâtel, attended Neuchâtel Univ. where he was a classmate of Leo Lesquereaux, Ph.D. Berlin 1835, went to America at instigation of Louis Agassiz in 1848 and became prof. of geology and geography, Princeton Univ., Princeton, New Jersey 1854-1884, L.L.D., died 8 Feb 1884 in Princeton.

name: Guyot, Henry
description: Swiss pharmaceutical researcher and botanist with a keen interest in floristic botany and geology, born 26 Mai 1891 in Saint Imier (Ct. Berne), studied at the Collège de Porrentruy, passed his pharmacy examination 1915, Dr. ès-sciences na- turelles 1917 Univ. of Geneva, taught school nr. Geneva 1918-1921, asst. to R.-H. Chodat 1918-1922, employed as a research scientist at Hoffmann-La Roche (pharmaceutical firm), Basel 1922-1950, died 12 Apr 1950 nr. Montreux.

page_title_longer_max-80: Gwynne-Vaughan, Helen Charlotte I. (née Fraser) [std. H.C.I. Gwynne-Vaughan]
name: Gwynne-Vaughan, Helen Charlotte Isabelle (Dame) (née Fraser)
description: English cytologist and mycologist, born 21 Jan 1879 in London, B.Sc. 1904 and D.Sc. 1907 Univ. of London, lecturer in botany, Royal Holloway College, head, Dept. of Botany 1909-1917 and Prof. of Botany 1921-1939, 1941-1944, Birbeck College (Univ. of London), Queen Mary's Army Auxiliary Corps (W.W.-I) in France 1917, president British Mycological Society 1928, Commandant Women's Royal Air Force (W.W.-II) 1939-1941, on 7 Dec 1911 married David Thomas Gwynne-Vaughan (1871-1915), also a botanist, and generally thereafter published under her married surname, C.B.E. 1918, D.B.E. 1919, Linnean Society Medal 1920, died 26 Aug 1967.

name: *Gyelnik, Vilmos (Wilhelm)
description: Hungarian lichenologist, born 30 Mar 1906 in Budapest, studied botany, Univ. of Pázmány Péter, Budapest 1924-1928, asst., Dept. of Botany, Veterinary College, researcher, Seed Research Station 1928 and visited Agricultural Museum, Cairo, Egypt for eight months, Dr. Phil. 1929 Budapest, "Privatdozent" 1930, curator, Natural History Museum, Budapest 1930, asst. lecturer, Univ. of Debrecen 1934, visited Finland to work with E.A. Vainio, died (along with his family) 15 Mar 1945 in an air-raid at the Amstetten, Austria, railroad station.

page_title_longer_max-80: Györffy, István (often abbrev. as J.) [std. Györffy] (Suppl.)
name: *Győrffy, István (latter often abbreviated "J.")
description: Hungarian bryologist, born 19 Dec 1880 in Hidasnémeti, studied in Makó, lived in Löcsén and collected mosses in the Tatra Mts., habilitation 1913 Franz-Joseph Univ. in Cluj (then Kolozsvár in Hungary, now Romania) and became prof. there from 1915 until Transylvania became Romanian and the Univ. moved to Szeged (1919-1940) where he founded a new inst., a botanical garden and a botanical journal (Folia Cryptogamica), returned to Cluj (Kolozsvár) 1940-1945, after W.W.-II took refuge in Salzburg, Austria but moved again, died 19 Apr 1959 in Csákvár (or Székesfehévár?).

name: Abbayes, Henri des
description: French lichenologist and plant collector at Rennes.

name: Abbot, Charles
description: British clergyman and botanist, vicar of Oakley Raynes and Goldington, Beds.

name: Abel, Clarke
description: British surgeon who travelled to China with Amherst, 1816-1817.

description: German physician and botanist at Ober-Ramstadt.

description: American botanist.

Berlin 1848; high school teacher at Berlin 1849-1859; curator at the Berlin herbarium 1860-1865; from 1865, professor of botany in Bonn; creator of the Bonn Botanical Institute; outstanding plant anatomist and developmental morphologist.

name: Hantzsch, Carl August

name: Happe, Andreas Friederich
description: German naturalist and artist at the Berlin Academy of Sciences.

name: Hara, Hiroshi

name: Hara, Kanesuke
description: Japanese mycologist and plant pathologist.

name: Hard, Miron Elisha
description: American mycologist; superintendent of public instruction at Kirkwood, Mo.

name: Hardouin, L.
description: French botanist active in Normandy.

name: Hardwicke, Thomas

name: Hardy, Apollon Joseph
description: Belgian botanist and high school teacher at Gilly, Tournai and, from 1884, at the middle school of Visé

name: Harkness, Harvey Willson
description: American physician and mycologist; in California from 1849, until 1869 at Sacramento as a practicing physician; from 1869 in retirement at San Francisco.

page_title_long: Harmand, (Frère, Abbé) Julien Herbert Auguste Jules
page_title_longer_max-80: Harmand, (Frère, Abbé) Julien Herbert Auguste Jules [std. Harm.]

name_ed: Harmand, (Frère, Abbé) Julien Herbert Auguste Jules

name: Harms, Hermann August Theodor
description: German botanist of the Engler school; at Berlin from 1893; executive editor of "Pflanzenreich" from 1900, of Engler and Prantl ed. 2 from 1930.

name: Harper, Robert Aimer
description: American botanist; pupil of Brefeld and Strasburger; professor of botany at Madison (Wisc.) (1898-1911); Torrey professor at Columbia University (1911-1930); specialist on the cytology of fungi and on phytopathology.

name: Harper, Roland McMillan
description: American botanist from Georgia; Ph. D. Columbia Univ. 1905; associated with the Geological Surveys of Georgia (1903-1904), Ala- bama (1905 and later), Florida (1903 and at intervals to 1931).

name: Harris, Thomas Maxwell
description: British palaeobotanist in London; trained at Cambridge; collected in East Greenland 1926-1927; specialized on Jurassic fossil plants.

name: Harris, Wilson P(ark?)
description: American cryptogamist; forester; resident of Brooklyn, N.Y.; collected in Western Montana.

name: Harshberger, John William Cleghorn
description: American botanist at Philadelphia.

name: Hart, Henry Chichester
description: Irish botanist, who collected on the British Polar Expedition (1875/6) and in Palestine (1883-1884).

name: Hartig, Theodor
description: German forester; from 1831-1838 lecturer and professor of forestry at Berlin; ultimately Forstrath and professor of forestry at the forestry college in Braunschweig.

name: Harting, Pieter
description: Dutch biologist, and microscopist; Dr. med. Utrecht 1835; practicing physician at Oudewater 1835-1841, from 1841-1843 at Franeker; from 1843 professor of natural philosophy, later of zoology at Utrecht University.

name: Hartinger, Anton
description: Austrian botanical artist.

name: Hartman, Carl
description: Swedish botanist; high school teacher at Gävle (1852-1859); lecturer at the teacher's college of Örebro; son of C. J. Hartman.

name: Hartman, Carl Johan
description: Swedish physician and botanist, pupil of Thunberg at Uppsala, ultimately government physician in Gästrikland.

name: Hartman, Carl Vilhelm
description: Swedish botanist, ethnographer and archeologist, son of Carl Hartman; curator at the Carnegie Museum at Pittsburgh 1903-1908, later at the Stockholm Riksmuseum.

name: Hartman, Robert Wilhelm
description: Swedish botanist, son of C.J. Hartman; teacher at Gävle; Dr. phil. Uppsala 1854.

page_title_longer_max-80: Hartmann, Frans Xaver, Ritter von [std. F. Hartmann]
name: Hartmann, Frans Xaver, Ritter von
description: Austrian botanist.

name: Hartmann, Max
description: German algologist.

name: Hartmann, Wilhelm
description: (= Gottfried Wilhelm Hartmann, ± 1770-1823?).

page_title_long: Hartung, C. A. F. A. Heinrich
page_title_longer_max-80: Hartung, C. A. F. A. Heinrich [std. Hartung]
name: Hartung, C. A. F. A. Heinrich
name_ed: Hartung, C. A. F. A. Heinrich
description: German physician.

name: Hartweg, Andreas
description: German botanist, director of the Karlsruhe botanical Garden.

name: Hartweg, Carl Theodor
description: German botanist; son of Andreas Hartweg; botanical collector for the Horticultural Society of London in North, Central and South America 1836-1843 and 1845-1847; afterwards inspector of the ducal gardens at Schwetzingen (Baden).

name: Harvey, William Henry
description: Irish botanist; colonial treasurer at the Cape 18361841; curator of TCD 1843; professor of botany Dublin 1856; traveller in the United States (1849-1850), South Africa (1835-1841), and Australia, New Zealand and Fiji (1853-1856).

name: Harvey-Gibson, Robert John

name: Harz, Carl [Karl] Otto
description: German pharmacist, seminologist and mycologist; at München with Nägeli (1871); lecturer (1873) and professor (1880) of botany and zoology at the Vetinary College and the Technical University of München.

name: Harz, Kurt
description: German botanist, high school teacher at Bamberg and München.

name: Harzer, Carl August Friedrich
description: German naturalist and artist at Dresden; initiator and co-founder of the Dresden society "Isis".

name: Hassall, Arthur Hill
description: British public analyst, sanitary specialist, and phycologist; from 1877 at San Remo.

name: Hasse, Hermann Edward
description: German-born physician and botanist who studied at St. Louis and settled again in the United States in 1861; Dr. med. Würzburg 1861; serving as a surgeon during the Civil War; practicing medicine in Wisconsin, Arkansas and, ultimately (from 1879) in California, surgeon to the Soldier's Home near Santa Monica 1889-1905.

name: Hasselquist, Fredric
description: Swedish explorer of the Levant, pupil of Linnaeus at Uppsala 1741-1749, travelled in the Orient 1749-1752, died at Smyrna.

page_title_longer_max-80: Hasselt, Arend Ludolf van [std. A. Hasselt]
name: Hasselt, Arend Ludolf van
description: Dutch soldier and later civil administrator on Java and Sumatra, leader of the Central Sumatra Expedition of 1877-1879.

page_title_longer_max-80: Hasselt, Johan Coenraad van [std. J. Hasselt]
name: Hasselt, Johan Coenraad van
description: Dutch surgeon and biologist, member of the "Natuurkundige Commissie" for the Dutch East Indies together with Kuhl.

name: Hasskarl, Justus Karl
description: German botanist; studied in Bonn; in Java 18371843 and 1846 at the Bogor garden; from 1852-1856 involved in introducing Cinchona into the Netherlands East Indies; Dr. phil. h.c. Greifswald 1858; from 1856 as private scientist at Cleve, Germany.

name: Hassler, Émile
description: Swiss botanical collector and physician who settled in Paraguay (1885-1937) with several prolonged stays in Europe; Dr. phil. h.c. Ascunsión 1930.

name: Hattori, Hirotarô
description: Japanese botanist.

name: Haub, Peter Ferdinand

name: Hauck, Ferdinand
description: Austrian algologist (born at Brünn, Brno); post office official stationed at Trieste 1866-1889; Dr. phil. h.c. Zürich 1883.

name: Haughton, Samuel

name: Hauman, Lucien

name: Hauptfleisch, Paul
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Greifswald 1888; lecturer at the Technische Hochschule, Stuttgart.

page_title_longer_max-80: Hausmann zu Stetten, Franz von [std. Hausm.]

description: Austrian botanist, Freiherr zum Stein unter Lebenberg, Lanegg und Greiffenegg.

name: Haussknecht, Heinrich Carl

name: Havaas (Havås), Johan Jonson

name: Havard, Valéry

name: Haworth, Adrian Hardy

name: Hay, George Upham
description: Canadian algologist and high school teacher at St. John, New Brunswick.

name: Hay, William Delisle
description: British popular science author.

name: Hayata, Bunzô
description: Japanese botanist at Tokyo.

name: Hayden, Ferdinand Vanderveer

Pennsylvania 18561872; L.L.D. h.c. Univ. Rochester 1876, id. h.c. Univ. Penn. 1886, "the-man-who-picks-up- stones-running" (Sioux name).

name: Hayek, August (Edler) von
description: Austrian botanist and physician; dr. med. Wien 1895; dr. phil. Wien 1905, from 1912 at the Universität Wien.

page_title_longer_max-80: Haynald, Stephan Franz Ludwig [Lajos], Cardinal [std. Haynald]

description: German botanist and pharmacist at Berlin.

name: Haynes, Carolyn Coventry
description: American hepaticologist at New York.

page_title_longer_max-80: Hedrick, Joyce (Mrs Volney Kurt Jones) [std. J. Hedrick]

name: Hedwig, Romanus Adolf

name: Heim, Georg Christoph

name: Heim, Roger Jean

description: German gardener (–Kunstgärtner–) in Hamburg

name: Hein, Theodor

name: Heinsen, Ernst
description: German botanist.

name: Heinzel, Philipp Gustav
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Breslau 1844.

name: Heister, Lorenz
description: German botanist; professor of medicine at Helmstädt.

name: Heldmann, C.
description: German botanist.

name: Heldreich, Theodor von

name: Hellbom, Pehr Johan

name: Heller, Franz Xaver

name: Henfrey, Arthur

name: Henkel, Johann Baptist

name: Henry, Joseph Kaye

page_title_longer_max-80: Henschel, August Wilhelm Eduard Theodor [std. Hensch.]

name: Henschen, Salomon Eberhard

Hooker; curate of Steyning, Sussex (1858-1861); headmaster of Hampton Lucy Grammar School 1861-1865, id. at London, Stove Street, 1865-1886; lecturer to St. Bartholomew's medical school (18861890); hon. professor of botany to the Royal Horticultural Society.

name: Henslow, John Stevens
description: British clergyman, botanist and mineralogist at Cambridge (1822, 1825); vicar of Cholsey, Berks. (1832), then rector of Hitcham (1837).

name: Hentig, H.
description: German botanist.

name: Hepp, Johann Adam Philipp

name: Herbert, William

name: Herbich, Franz

name: Herbst, William

page_title_long: Herder, Ferdinand Gottfried Maximilian Theobald von

name: Hérincq, François

name: Hering, Constantijn J.

name: Hermann, Friedrich

name: Hermann, Johannes Gotthelf

name: Hermann, Paul

name: Herold, Johann Moritz David
description: German entomologist at Marburg.

name: Herpell, Gustav Jacob

page_title_longer_max-80: Herre, Albert William Christian Theodore [std. Herre]

page_title_longer_max-80: Herrera y Garmendia, Fortunato Luciano [std. Herr.]

description: Peruvian botanist, professor at the University of Cuzco from 1910.

name: Herrmann, Johan (Jean)

page_title_longer_max-80: Herter, Wilhelm Gustav Franz (Guillermo Herter) [std. Herter]

name: Hervey, Alpheus Baker

name: Hervey, Eliphalet Williams
description: American botanist.

page_title_longer_max-80: Hervier, Gabriel Marie Joseph, abbé [std. Hervier]

name: Herzer, Herman[n]

name: Hesse, Rudolph

name: Hessler, Karl

name: Heucher, Johann Heinrich von

name: Heuffel, Johann A.

page_title_long: Heufler zu Rasen und Perdonegg, Ludwig Samuel..., (later) Freiherr von Hohenbühel

description: German botanist and entomologist; high school teacher at Hastenrieth (1815-1817), at Aachen (Aix-la-Chapelle) (1817-1876).

page_title_long: Kamel, Georg Joseph (Georgius Josephus Camellus, Camel, Camelli)
page_title_longer_max-80: Kamel, Georg Joseph (Georgius Josephus Camellus, Camel, Camelli) [std. Kamel]
name: Kamel, Georg Joseph (Georgius Josephus Camellus, Camel, Camelli)
name_ed: Kamel, Georg Joseph (Georgius Josephus Camellus, Camel, Camelli)
description: Moravia born Jesuit (lay brother) missionary and pharmacist in the Phillippines.

name: Kamerling, Zeno
description: Dutch botanist.

name: Kamiénski, Frans (Franciszek)
description: Polish botanist, sometime director of the Odessa botanical garden.

name: Kampe, E.
description: German botanist.

name: Kampmann, Frédéric-Edouard fils ("Fritz")
description: Alsatian pharmacist at Colmar, after 1872 at Genève, from 1907-1914 at Vallorbe, enthusiastic amateur botanist (son of Frédéric-Edouard K. 1797-1873).

page_title_longer_max-80: Kane, Lady Katherine Sophia (née Bailey) [std. Kane]
name: Kane, Lady Katherine Sophia (née Bailey)
description: Irish botanist, married to Sir Robert Kane (1838).

name: Kanehira, Ryôzô,
description: Japanese botanist, director of the Department of Forestry, Formosa, later at Fukuoka.

name: Kanitz, August (Agoston, Agost)
description: Hungarian botanist, who studied with Neilreich in Wien, at Hungarian Altenburg (1869-1872), after 1872 professor of botany and director of the botanic garden at Klausenburg (Cluj, Kolozsvár).

name: Kanjilal, Upendranath N.
description: Indian botanist; extra deputy conservator of forests, Assam, lecturer at Dehra Dun.

name: Kanouse, Bessie Bernice
description: American mycologist; Ph. D. Univ. Mich. 1926; specialist on watermolds and discomycetes; at the Ann Arbor University Herbarium of the University of Michigan (1926-1960).

name: Kappler, August
description: German soldier and naturalist; from 1836-1879 in Suriname and the West Indies; travelled around the world in 1883; the most important author on Suriname of the mid-nineteenth century.

page_title_longer_max-80: Karelin, Grigorij Silyc (Gregor Silitsch, Silovitsch). [std. Karel.]
name: Karelin, Grigorij Silyc (Gregor Silitsch, Silovitsch).
description: Russian botanist, explorer of Siberia.

name: Karling, John Sidney
description: American algologist and mycologist at Columbia and Purdue Universities, Ph. D. Columbia Univ. 1926.

name: Karsch, Anton
description: German botanist, zoologist and physician; Dr. phil. et med. Greifswald 1846; practicing physician at Münster i.W. 1848, professor of medicine at the University 1852 (extraord.), 1856 (ord.), Geheimer Medizinalrath 1874.

page_title_longer_max-80: Karsten, Georg Henry Herman [std. G. Karst.]
name: Karsten, Georg Henry Herman
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Rostock 1885; habit. Leipzig 1892; at Bonn 1899-1909; at Halle 1909-1928; travelled in Indonesia (18881890) and Mexico (1894).

page_title_longer_max-80: Karsten, Hermann [Gustav Karl Wilhelm Hermann] [std. H. Karst.]
name: Karsten, Hermann [Gustav Karl Wilhelm Hermann]
description: German botanist; studied botany in the Stralsund pharmacy; travelled in South America 1844-1847, 18481856; from 1856-1868 professor of botany in Berlin; 1868-1872 in Wien; from 1872 onward in Berlin.

name: Karsten, Petter [Peter] Adolf
description: Finnish mycologist; Ph. D. Helsinki 1859; teacher at the Wasa Gymnasium 1862-1864; lecturer in botany at Mustiala agricultural college 1864-1908; later in Forssa.

name: Kashyap, Shiv Ram
description: Pakistani botanist; from 1919 professor of botany at the University of Panjab, Lahore.

name: Kauffman, Calvin Henry
description: America mycologist of Pennsylvania-Dutch origin at the University of Michigan, Ann Arbor, Michigan; Ph. D. Ann Arbor 1907; instructor of botany 1904; assist. professor 1912; associate professor 1920; full professor 1923; founder of the Ann Arbor mycological school.

name: Kaulfuss, Georg Friedrich
description: German botanist; Dr. jur. et phil. Halle 1816; extra-ord. prof. forestry at Halle 1823; ord. prof. of botany ib. 1818.

name: Kaurin, Christian
description: Norwegian bryologist and clergyman at Opdal and Ager o. Sand vid Drammen.

name: Kausel, Eberhard Max Leopold
description: Chilean dentist and botanist at Santiago; specialist on Myrtaceae.

name: Kavina, Karel
description: Czechoslovakian botanist and mycologist at Praha; pupil of J. Velenovsky.

name: Kawakami, Takiya
description: Japanese botanist; botanist of the Government of Formosa from 1901.

name: Kearney, Thomas Henry
description: American botanist at the Bureau for Plant Industry; in various functions at USDA 1894-1914; cotton breeder; explorer; from 1944 at CAS.

name: Keating, William Hippolitus [Hypolitus]
description: American mineralogist and geologist on the Long expedition to St. Peter's River (1823); professor of chemistry Univ. Pennsylvania 1822-1828.

name: Keck, David Daniels
description: American botanist; Ph. D. Berkeley 1930; collaborated with Clausen and Hiesey in their pioneer experimental systematics at Stanford (1926-1950); specialist on Penstemon; head curator at the New York Bot. Gard. 1950-1959; at the National Science Foundation 1959-1970; subsequently living in New Zealand (1971-1976) and California (1976-x).

name: Keck, Karl
description: Austrian owner of a printing office, botanist and physician at Aistersheim.

name: Kegel, Hermann Aribert Heinrich
description: German gardener at Halle, collected in Surinam 1844-1846.

name: Keissler, Karl von
description: Austrian lichenologist at Vienna; Dr. phil. Vienna 1895; at the Botanical Garden 1895-1899; in various functions at the Botanische Abteilung des Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums 1899-1938; pupil of A. Zahlbrückner; from 1924 with the title Hofrat.

name: Kelaart, Edward Frederick
description: Ceylon-born British botanist; sometime army physician at Gibraltar.

name: Keller, Boris Aleksandrowitsch (Alexandrovic)
description: Russian botanist, from 1913-1931 at Woronesch.

name: Keller, Gottfried
description: Swiss botanist and lawyer at Aarau.

name: Keller, Ida Augusta
description: German-born American botanist and high school teacher; Dr. phil. Zürich 1890; lecturer at Bryn Mawr College, Philadelphia 1891-1892; from 1893at the Girl's High School ib.

name: Keller, Robert
description: Swiss botanist (especially rhodologist) and high school teacher at Winterthur.

name: Kellerman, William Ashbrook
description: American botanist and mycologist, studied at Cornell and Zürich, high school teacher at the Oshkosh State Normal School, Wisconsin (1874-1879), worked for his degree at Zürich (1879-1881), professor of botany at the University of Kentucky, Lexington (1881-1883), id. at Kansas State College of Agriculture, Manhattan (1883-1891), id. at Ohio State University, Columbus (1891-1908); died while botanizing in Guatemala.

name: Kellogg, Albert
description: American physician and botanist in California; one of the seven founders of the California Academy of Sciences (4 Apr 1853); first resident botanist in California (1849).

name: Kelly, Howard Atwood
description: American physician, mycologist and bibliophile at Baltimore.

name: Kelly, James Peter
description: Canadian-born American geneticist and botanist at Pennsylvania State College.

name: Kelsey, Francis Duncan
description: American congregational clergyman and botanist; D. Sc. College of Montana 1890; minister at Helena, Mont. until 1893; professor of botany at Oberlin College 1893-1897; pastor Central Congregational Church, Toledo Ohio 18971905.

name: Kemmler, Carl [Karl] Albert
description: German clergyman and botanist at Untersontheim 1847-1863; from 1863 at Donnstetten, Württemberg.

name: Kennedy, James Domoné
description: British-born Nigerian forest officer.

name: Kennedy, John
description: British nurseryman; partner of James Lee at the Vineyard Nursery, Hammersmith; advised Josephine on the Malmaison gardens.

name: Kent, William Saville
description: British protozoologist at the British Museum (Natural History).

name: Ker, Charles Henry Bellenden
description: British botanist and legal reformer; barrister at Lincoln's Inn; son of John Bellenden Ker.

name: Ker, John Bellenden
description: British botanist at Ramridge; editor of Botanical Register 1815-1824; until 5 Nov 1804, John Gawler.

page_title_long: Kerchove de Denterghem, Oswald Charles Eugène Marie Ghislain de
page_title_longer_max-80: Kerchove de Denterghem, Oswald Charles Eugène Marie Ghislain de [std. Kerch.]
name: Kerchove de Denterghem, Oswald Charles Eugène Marie Ghislain de
name_ed: Kerchove de Denterghem, Oswald Charles Eugène Marie Ghislain de
description: Belgian horticulturist, botanist, politician and administrator.

name: Kern, Frank Dunn
description: American mycologist and phytopathologist; Ph. D. Columbia 1911; specialist on Uredinales; associate botanist at Purdue University (19051910); instructor at Purdue 1910-1913; from 1913-1950 at Pennsylvania State University.

name: Kern, Johannes Hendrikus
description: Dutch botanist, high school teacher at Nijmegen; later at the Rijksherbarium, Leiden, specialist on Cyperaceae.

page_title_long: Kerner von Marilaun, Anton Joseph, Ritter
page_title_longer_max-80: Kerner von Marilaun, Anton Joseph, Ritter [std. A. Kern]
name: Kerner von Marilaun, Anton Joseph, Ritter
name_ed: Kerner von Marilaun, Anton Joseph, Ritter
description: Austrian botanist, Dr. med. Wien 1854; high school teacher at Budapest 1855-1858, at the Polytechnic 1858-1860; director of the Innsbruck (1860-1878), and of the Vienna botanical garden (1878-1898); outstanding floristic botanist, plant geographer and popular writer.

name: Kerner, Johann Simon [von]
description: German botanist and botanical artist at the Württemberg Carl's Universität, Stuttgart.

name: Kernstock, Ernst
description: Austrian botanist and high school teacher at Bozen and Klagenfurt.

name: Kersten, Otto
description: German botanist, participated with Hermann Linck in the Decken expedition (1862-1865); collected later in the Mediterranean area.

name: Kessel, Stephen Lackey
description: Australian forester, conservator of forests W. Australia 1921-1941.

name: Keys, Iasaiah Waterloo Nicholson
description: English botanist, bookseller and printer at Plymouth.

page_title_long: Keyserling, Alexander Friedrich Michael Leberecht Arthur von
page_title_longer_max-80: Keyserling, Alexander Friedrich Michael Leberecht Arthur von [std. Keyserl.]
name: Keyserling, Alexander Friedrich Michael Leberecht Arthur von, [Andreëvich]
name_ed: Keyserling, Alexander Friedrich Michael Leberecht Arthur von
description: Latvian/Russian botanist, geologist and palaeontologist of Baltic German origin; educated at Berlin University; from 1840-1850 handling special missions in the Russian mining department and travelling in Northern and Eastern Russia; from 1850 on his Esthonian estate Raiküll.

name: Kiaer, Frantz Casper
description: Norwegian bryologist and physician; Dr. med. Oslo 1863, hospital physician at Oslo 1864-1893.

name: Kiaerskou, (Kjaerskou) Hjalmar Frederik Christian
description: Danish botanist and high school teacher at Copenhagen; from 1861-1883 assistant at the Botanisk Museum parttime); from 1883-1900 inspector id.

name: Kickx, Jean, Sr.
description: Belgian botanist and mineralogist, professor of botany, pharmacy and mineralogy at the Brussels medical school.

page_title_longer_max-80: Kickx, Jean, Jr. [std. J. Kickx fil.]
name: Kickx, Jean, Jr.
description: Belgian botanist and malacologist, son of Jean Kickx (17751831); Ph. D. Leuven 1830; professor of botany at Brussels 1831-1835, at Gent 1835-1864; one of the founders of the Société de Botanique de Belgique.

name: Kickx, Jean Jacques
description: Belgian botanist at Gent; son of Jean Kickx, Jr. (18031864); Dr. sci. Gent 1864; lecturer 1864, and professor of botany (1867, 1871) at the University of Gent.

name: Kidston, Robert
description: Scottish palaeobotanist; from early boyhood living at Stirling, his private means enabling him to give his time wholly to science; LL.D. Glasgow 1908; D. Sc. h.c. Manchester 1921.

name: Kieffer, Frédéric
description: French botanist of Alsatian origin at Marseille, director of the Petit Lycée.

name: Kieffer, Jean-Jacques
description: French clergyman, entomologist, cecidologist and botanist at the Collège de Bitche.

name: Kielmeyer, Karl Friedrich [von]
description: German naturalist at Tübingen 17961817; at Stuttgart 1817-1839.

page_title_longer_max-80: Kienitz-Gerloff, Johann Heinrich Emil Felix [std. Kien.-Gerl.]
name: Kienitz-Gerloff, Johann Heinrich Emil Felix
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Berlin 1873; part-time assistant of Pringsheim 1874-1878; 1876-1878 teacher at the Friedrichs Realschule, Berlin; from 1878 teacher, later (1908) director of the Landwirtschafts- schule in Weilburg a.d. Lahn.

name: Kiesling, Christian Gotthilf
description: German botanist.

name: Kiggelaer, François ("Franciscus")
description: Dutch botanist, "commies ter secretarye van den Heer van Beaumont."

name: Kihlman, Alfred Oswald [after 1906: Kairamo]
description: Finnish botanist at Helsinki and Hattula

name: Killermann, Sebastian
description: German clergyman and botanist; Dr. rer. nat. Regensburg 1893; ordin. ib. 1895; curate at Arendsberg 1895-1901; teacher (1901) and professor (1910) at the theological-philosophical college at Regensburg; from 1916-1956 president of the Regensburgische botanische Gesellschaft; specialist on Hymenomycetes.

name: Killias, Eduard
description: Swiss botanist, entomologist and physician in Chur, Le Prese (nr. Puschlaf), and Tarasp-Schuls (Nairs).

name: Killip, Ellsworth Paine
description: American botanist at the Smithsonian Institution.

name: Kimball, James Putnam
description: American palaeobotanist, consulting geologist in New York City.

name: Kindberg, Nils Conrad
description: Swedish bryologist; Dr. phil. Uppsala 1857; High school teacher at Linköping (1862-1901).

name: Kindt, Christian Sommer
description: Norwegian botanist and physician at Trondhjem.

name: King, [Sir] George
description: British botanist; MB Aberdeen 1865; superintendent of the Calcutta Botanic Gardens and of the Cinchona cultivation in Bengal 1871-1898; director Botanical Survey of India 1891-1898.

name: Kingdon-Ward, Francis (Frank)
description: British plant collector in China, Burma, Tibet and Thailand (1909-1956), introduced e.g. Meconopsis betonicifolia into cultivation; prolific author on "plant hunting."

name: Kinney, Abbot
description: American popular writer on botany

page_title_longer_max-80: Kirby, Mary (1860 Mrs. H. Gregg) [std. Kirby]
name: Kirby, Mary (1860: Mrs. H. Gregg)
description: British botanist at Leicester.

name: Kirchner, [Emil Otto] Oskar
description: German botanist and flower-biologist; Dr. phil. Breslau 1874; from 1873-1877 at Breslau; from 1877-1917 assistant, from 1881 professor of botany at the Landwirtschaftliche Akademie, Hohenheim; from 1917-1925 living at München.

name: Kirillow, Peter
description: Russian botanist and physician at Charkow.

name: Kirilow, Iwan Petrovic ("Johann")
description: Russian botanist.

name: Kirk, [Sir] John
description: Scottish colonial administrator, explorer and botanist; mainly active in eastern Africa; M. D. Edinburgh 1854; physician and naturalist on Livingstone's second Zambesi expedition (1858-1863); in Zanzibar 1866-1881, 1883-1887; thence onward in England.

page_title_longer_max-80: Kirk, John William Carnegie [std. J.W.C. Kirk]
name: Kirk, John William Carnegie
description: British soldier (retired 1921) and amateur botanist; son of Sir John Kirk.

name: Kirk, Thomas
description: English-born botanist and chief conservator of State forests in New Zealand (1863-1898).

name: Kirkwood, Joseph Edward
description: American botanist; Ph. D. Columbia 1903, from 1901-1907 at Syracuse University; from 1907-1909 involved in guayule-rubber research; from 1909 at the department of botany of the University of Montana, Missoula.

name: Kirmis, Max
description: German high school teacher, archeologist, numismatist and botanist; from 1880 at the Neumünster Progymnasium.

name: Kirschleger, Frédéric
description: Alsatian botanist; M.D. Paris 1829; 1829-1834 physician at Munster; from 1834-1845 at the Strasbourg École de Pharmacie; from 1845 at the Faculté de médécine; Dr. Sc. Strasbourg 1846.

name: Kirschstein, Wilhelm
description: German mycologist; high school teacher at Rathenow (Havel), later at Berlin-Pankov.

name: Kirtikar, Kanhoba Ranchoddâs
description: Indian botanist; surgeon-major in the British-Indian army; stationed at various locations; 1886 assistant, 1887 full professor of materia medica at Bombay; one of the founders of the Bombay Natural History Society.

name: Kitagawa, Masao
description: Japanese botanist at the Biological Institute, Yokohama National University; before 1940 in Manchuria.

name: Kitaibel, Paul
description: Hungarian botanist at Budapest whose herbarium constitutes the basis of BP.

name: Kitamura, Siro
description: Japanese botanist at the Department of Botany, Kyoto University, specialist in Compositae and the flora of Afghanistan, Himalaya, Tibet and Japan.

name: Kittel, Baldwin Martin
description: German naturalist; from 1834-1869 Rector of the Landwirthschaftsund Gewerbsschule zu Aschaffenburg.

name: Kittler, Christian
description: German botanist and high school teacher at Nürnberg.

name: Kittlitz, Friedrich Heinrich [Baron] von
description: German soldier (1813 sic-1825) and ornithologist, on the Senjavin expedition (1826-1829); at Köln 1832-1845; later at Berlin and Wiesbaden as "Privatgelehrter."

name: Kitton, Frederic
description: British diatomist and microscopist.

name: Kjellman, Frans Reinhold
description: Swedish phycologist at Uppsala; collected in Spitzbergen 1872-1873; Novaya Zemlya 1875; botanist with Nordenskjöld on the Vega expedition of 1878-1880; Ph. D. Uppsala 1872; extra ord. professor of botany 1883; ord. professor 1900.

name: Kjoeping, Oläus
description: [fictitious] Swedish botanical explorer.

name: Klášterský, Ivan
description: Czechoslovak botanist, especially rhodologist, curator of PR 1925-1955, later working at the Geobotanical laboratory of the Ceskosl. Akad. ved., Pruhonice.

name: Klatt, Friedrich Wilhelm
description: German botanist; from 1842-1897 high school teacher at Hamburg; Dr. phil. Rostock 1864.

name: Klebahn, Heinrich
description: German mycologist and phytopathologist; Dr. phil. Jena 1884; high school teacher (linguistics) at Bremen 1885-1894, at Hamburg 1894-1899; from 1899-1905 at the Hamburg botanical Garden; from 1905-1930 at the agricultural institute of Bromberg; teaching at Hamburg University 1921-1934.

name: Klebs, Georg Albrecht
description: German botanist, pupil of de Bary, Sachs and Pfeffer; Dr. phil. Strasbourg 1879; at Tübingen 1882; professor of botany at Basel 1887; id. at Halle 1898; id. at Heidelberg 1907.

name: Klein, Jakob Theodor
description: German botanist, born at Königsberg, municipal secretary at Danzig.

name: Kleinhans, Rodolphe
description: French bryologist.

name: Klement, Oscar
description: Bohemian lichenologist; pupil of Anders; in Czechoslovakia until 1945; later in Hannover and Kempten.

name: Klett, Gustav Theodor
description: German botanist at Leipzig.

name: Klinge, Johannes Christoph
description: Estonian botanist; Dr. phil. Dorpat (Tartu) 1893; at the Dorpat botanical garden 1879-1895; from 1895 librarian and botanist at the St. Petersburg botanical garden.

page_title_longer_max-80: Klinggräff, Carl Julius Meyer von [std. C. Klinggr.]
name: Klinggräff, Carl Julius Meyer von
description: German physician and botanist; Dr. med. Königsberg 1832; at first physician at Marienwerder; from 1836 landowner at Paleschken bei Stuhm in Prussia.

page_title_longer_max-80: Klinggräff, Hugo Erich Meyer von [std. H. Klinggr.]
name: Klinggräff, Hugo Erich Meyer von
description: German bryologist; brother of C. J. M. von Klinggräff; educated in Croatia (Zmrock, 1826-1842); on the family estate of Paleschken 1842-1846; Dr. phil. Königsberg 1846; in Croatia 1846-1848; from 1848 active in various parts of Prussia, mainly at Marienwerder.

name: Klingstedt, Frederik Woldemar
description: Finnish botanist and chemist at Turku.

name: Klinsmann, Ernst Ferdinand
description: Danzig botanist and physician; studied at Berlin under F. G. Hayne; Dr. med. Berlin 1823; practiced medicine in Danzig 1824-1865; curator of the botanical collections of the Naturforschende Gesellschaft in Danzig.

name: Kloos, Abraham Willem, Jr.
description: Dutch botanist; Dr. phil. h.c. Leiden 1946; civil engineer; high school teacher at Schiermonnikoog (1904-1905), Goes (1905-1911) and Dordrecht (1911-1945); student of the adventitious flora of the Netherlands.

name: Klotzsch, Johann Friedrich
description: German botanist at Berlin; curator of the herbarium (1833-1860); outstanding mycologist.

name: Knapp, F. H.
description: British botanist at Bath.

name: Knapp, Josef Armin
description: Austrian botanist at first at Cluj, later curator at Wien.

name: Knapp, John Leonard
description: British botanist and soldier, served in the Hereford and Northampton Militia; later residing at Powick near Worcester.

name: Knaut, Christian
description: German botanist at Halle, brother of Christoph Knauth.

name: Knauth, Christoph(orus)
description: German botanist and physician at Halle.

name: Knebel, Gottfried
description: German algologist, Dr. phil. Berlin 1935.

name: Kneiff, Friedrich Gotthard
description: Alsatian botanist and pharmacist (1817-1832) at Strasbourg.

name: Kneucker, Johann Andreas ("Andrees")
description: German high school teacher and botanist at Karlsruhe; from 1905 also curator of KR; botanical explorer of the Near East, especially of the Sinai Peninsula.

name: Knieskern, Peter D.
description: American botanist and physician; resided in eastern New Jersey 1841-1871.

name: Knight, Charles
description: British administrator and botanist (lichenologist) in New Zealand, ultimately auditor general.

name: Knight, Joseph
description: British gardener and nurseryman.

name: Knight, Thomas Andrew
description: British horticulturist; president of the [Royal] Horticultural Society 1811-1838.

name: Kniphof, Johann[es] Hieronymous
description: German botanist, professor of botany at Erfurt (1745-1756).

name: Knoblauch, Emil Friedrich
description: German botanist.

name: Knoche, [Edward Louis] Herman
description: American botanist of German descent at Stanford; studied at Stanford 1895-1899; with Charles Flahault at Montpellier 19041917, in the United States and travelling until 1945.

name: Knoop, Johann Hermann
description: German born gardener at Marienburg near Leeuwarden, later teacher in mathematics and free-lance publicist.

name: Knorr, Georg Wolfgang
description: German engraver, palaeontologist and art merchant at Nürnberg.

name: Knowles, George Beauchamp
description: British surgeon and botanist at the Brimingham School of Medicine.

name: Knowles, Matilda Cullen
description: Irish lichenologist at the [National] Science and Art Museum in Dublin from 1902.

name: Knowlton, Frank Hall
description: American geologist, taxidermist and botanist at Georg Washington [Columbian] University, D. C. (1887-1896); from 1894 palaeobotanist in the U.S. Geological Survey; Ph. D. George Washington Univ. 1896, D. Se. 1921.

page_title_longer_max-80: Knuth, Paul Erich Otto Wilhelm [std. P. Knuth]
name: Knuth, Paul Erich Otto Wilhelm
description: German botanist educated at Greifswald; Dr. phil. 1876; high school teacher at Iserlohn 1876, from 1881 at Kiel; author of a Handbuch der Blütenbiologie.

name: Knuth, Reinhard [Gustav Paul]
description: German botanist; pupil of Engler; Dr. phil. Berlin 1902; high school teacher at Breslau 1900-1905; at Berlin 1905-1937; research associate at the Botanischem Museum, Berlin-Dahlem.

name: Kny, Carl Ignaz Leopold
description: German botanist; pupil of A. Braun; Dr. phil. Berlin 1863; professor of botany at the Landwirtschaftliche Hochschule, Berlin from 1868.

name: Kobus, Jan Derk
description: Dutch botanist, at the Eastern Java Sugar Experiment Station, Pasuruan, Java.

name: Kobuski, Clarence Emmeren
description: American botanist at the Arnold Arboretum of Harvard University, editor of the Journal of the Arnold Arboretum (1949-1958) and of Sargentia; Dr. phil. Univ. Washington 1927

name: Koch, Erwin
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Erlangen 1895.

name: Koch, Georg Friedrich
description: German physician and botanist in the Pfaltz (Dürkheim, Wachenheim, Sembach, Waldmohr).

name: Koch, Heinrich
description: Swiss dendrologist.

page_title_longer_max-80: Koch, Johann Friedrich Wilhelm [std. J. Koch]
name: Koch, Johann Friedrich Wilhelm
description: German botanist and "Consistorialrath" in Magdeburg.

name: Koch, Karl
description: German high school teacher and botanist at Osnabrück.

page_title_longer_max-80: Koch, Karl [Carl] Heinrich Emil [std. K. Koch]
name: Koch, Karl [Carl] Heinrich Emil
description: German botanist; traveller in the Orient; dendrologist; horticulturist; at Würzburg 1831-1833; Dr. med. Würzburg 1833; at Jena 1835; travelled in the Kaukasus and Central Asia 1837-1838 and 1843-1844; from 1847 botanist ("Adjunkt") at the Berlin Botanical Garden.

page_title_longer_max-80: Koch, Wilhelm Daniel Joseph [std. W. Koch]
name: Koch, Wilhelm Daniel Joseph
description: German physician and botanist; Dr. med. Giessen 1794; practiced at Kaiserslautern from 1797 until 1824, then professor of botany at Erlangen.

name: Koehler, Alexander Daniel
description: [fictitious] German botanist stated to have worked with Mutis in Colombia and to have travelled in Brazil, Peru and Chile.

name: Köhler, Hermann Adolph
description: German botanist.

name: Koehne, Bernhard Adalbert Emil
description: German botanist and dendrologist; Dr. phil. Berol. 1869; participated as "Vizefeldwebel beim Alexander Regiment" in the Battle of Gravelotte (18 Aug 1870); teacher at the Friedrich-Werderschen Gewerbschule 1872-1880; from 1880 at the then new Falk-Realgymnasium, both in Berlin; professor's title 1891; from 1913 retired; one of the founders (1881) of the Deutsche botanische Gesellschaft.

name: Kolbing, F, W.
description: German bishop of the Herrnhut Moravian society at Gnadenfeld, Schlesien.

name: Koelderer, Johann Georg
description: German physician; Dr. med. Strasbourg 1748.

name: Koeler, Georg Ludwig
description: German botanist at Mainz.

name: Koelle, Johann Ludwig Christian
description: German physician ("Medicinalrath") and botanist at Bayreuth.

name: Koelliker, Rudolph Albert von
description: Swiss human anatomist and botanist; Dr. phil. Zürich 1841; Dr. med. Heidelberg 1842; professor of anatomy at Heidelberg 18441847; id. at Würzburg from 1847.

name: Koelpin, Alexander Bernhard
description: German physician, botanist and teacher at the academic gymnasium at Stettin.

name: Kölreuter, Joseph Gottlieb
description: German botanist; early student of flower biology and of hybridization; Dr. med. Tübingen 1756; until 1761 at St. Petersburg; until 1763 at Calw; from then on director of the botanical garden at Karlsruhe.

name: König, Johann Gerhard
description: Baltic-German pharmacist and physician; 17591767 in Denmark; from 1767 India, Siam, Malacca and Ceylon as missionary and plant collector.

name: Koenig, Karl
description: German clergyman and botanist at Dürkheim an der Haardt.

page_title_longer_max-80: Koenig, Karl Dietrich Eberhard [std. K.D. Koenig]
name: Koenig, Karl Dietrich Eberhard
description: British botanist (Koenig or König, alias Charles Konig) of German birth; keeper of mineralogy British Museum 1813.

name: Köpff, Friedrich
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Erlangen 1892.

name: Köppen, Friedrich Theodor (Petrowitsch) von
description: Russian (Baltic-German?) botanist at St. Petersburg.

name: Koerber (Körber), Gustav Wilhelm
description: German-Silesian lichenologist; from 1842 high school teacher at the Elisabeth Gymnasium at Breslau; Dr. phil. berol. 1839, royal professor 1862, extraord. prof. at Breslau University 1873; with Massalongo founder of the "Italian-Silesian" school of lichenology.

name: Körnicke, Friedrich August
description: German botanist; 1849 assistant curator at the Berlin herbarium; 1856 at St. Petersburg; Dr. phil. berol. 1856; 1859-1867 lecturer, later professor, at Waldau agricultural college near Königsberg; 1867-1898 at the agricultural college at Poppelsdorf near Bonn as successor to Julius Sachs.

name: Kofoid, Charles Atwood
description: American protozoologist and algologist of Danish descent; Ph. D. Harvard 1894; with Illinois nat. hist. survey 1894-1903; at Univ. California, Berkeley 1903-1936; assistant director San Diego zool. station 1907-1910; of La Jolla zool. station (later: Scripps) 1910-1923; professor of zoology at Berkeley 1904-1936.

name: Kohl, Friedrich Georg
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Leipzig 1881; professor of botany at the University of Marburg i.H. 1891, later in Leipzig.

name: Kohn, Maximilian
description: Austrian botanist; Dr. med. Wien 1846.

name: Koidzumi, Gen-Iti (Gen'ichi)
description: Japanese botanist.

name: Kol, Erszébet [Elizabet]
description: Hungarian botanist at the Budapest Museum of Narural History; interested in cryobiology; Dr. phil. Szeged 1925.

name: Kolb, Max
description: German gardener, worked in botanical gardens in Berlin and Paris; from 1859 "Kön. Oberinspecktor am botanischen Garten in München."

name: Kolbáni, Pál [Paul]
description: Hungarian botanist.

name: Kolbe, Robert Wilhelm
description: Russian born diatomologist with Finnish nationality, of German-Finnish-Russian descent; studied at the Friedrich-Wilhelms-Univer- sität, Berlin 1898-1899 and at the Technische Hochschule Dresden until 1904; business administrator in Russia until 1918; emigrated to Finland 1918/1919, returned to Germany to take his degree in the natural sciences with e.g. Kolkwitz and Engler; diatomologist in Germany until 1946, finally in Sweden at the Stockholm natural history museum.

name: Kolenati, Friedrich August Rudolph
description: Bohemian zoologist and botanist at the polytechnic institute of Brünn, travelled in Russia 1842-1845, founded the society "Lotos".

name: Kolkwitz, Richard
description: German botanist and ecologist at Berlin-Dahlem.

name: Koltz, Jean Pierre Joseph
description: Belgian/Luxemburg botanist; forester in Luxemburg, founder of the société botanique du G. D. de Luxemburg.

name: Komarov, Vladimir Leontjevic
description: Russian botanist.

name: Konrad, Paul
description: Swiss geometrician; amateur mycologist and botanical artist at Neuchâtel, from 1902 with the Compagnie des Tramways de Neuchâtel, director 1938-1948; Dr. sci. h.c. Neuchâtel 1932.

name: Koorders, Sijfert Hendrik
description: Dutch-Indonesian forester and botanist at Buitenzorg (Bogor); Dr. phil. Bonn 1897; in the Dutch East Indian Forest Service from 1885 stationed in Java; from 1892-1903 and 1910-1919 working at BO.

name: Koorders-Schumacher, Anna
description: German-born Dutch botanist; married to S. H. Koorders.

name: Koppe, Carl [Karl] Friedrich August
description: German botanist and high school teacher at Soest.

name: Kops, Jan
description: Dutch agronomist and botanist, professor of botanyat Utrecht.

name: Kornhuber, (Georg) Andreas (von) (Korn-Huber)
description: Austrian botanist at the polytechnical school at Vienna; Dr. med. vindob. 1850; teacher at the Oberrealschule Pressburg [Bratislava] 1852-1861; professor of botany and zoology at the k.k. polytechnisches Institut Wien (now Polytechnical University) 1861-1895; at Pressburg 1897-1905; died in Wien.

name: Korshinsky [Koržinskij], Sergei Iwanowitsch
description: Russian botanist; Dr. Phil. Kasan 1888, professor of botany at Tomsk 1888-1892, botanist at the botanical garden in St. Petersburg 1892-1900; traveller in Siberia and Turkestan; outstanding plant geographer.

name: Korthals, Pieter Willem
description: Dutch botanist and traveller in the East Indies, member of the "Natuurkundige Commissie voor Nederlandsch-Indie" Mai 1831-Feb 1836.

name: Koso-Poliansky, Boris Mikhailovich
description: Russian botanist.

page_title_longer_max-80: Kosteletzky, Vincenz Franz (Kostelecky, Vincenc František) [std. Kostel.]
name: Kosteletzky, Vincenz Franz (Kostelecky, Vincenc František)
description: Czech botanist; Dr. med. Praha 1824; professor of botany at the Carl-Ferdinands Universität and director of the botanic garden at Smichov in Praha (1826-) 1835-1872.

name: Koster, Henry
description: British botanist of Portuguese descent; in Brazil 1809-1815 and 1820.

name: Koster, Joséphine Thérèse
description: Dutch botanist at the Rijksherbarium, Leiden 1930-1967; Ph.D. Leiden 1935; worked on Malaysian Compositae, Cyanophyta and marine algae.

page_title_longer_max-80: Kostermans, André Joseph Guillaume Henri [std. Kosterm.]
name: Kostermans, André Joseph Guillaume Henri

name: Kotschy, Carl (Karl) Georg Theodor
description: Austrian botanical explorer of the Orient 1835-1843; from 1847 assistant, from 1852 curator of the herbarium of the Vienna Natural History Museum (W).

name: Kováts von Szent-Lélek, Julius
description: Hungarian actuoand palaeobotanist at the Hungarian national Museum at Pest from 1850.

name: Krabbe, Gustav [Heinrich]
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Berlin 1882; from 1890 at Berlin University with Schwendener.

name: Kraenzlin, Friedrich (Fritz) Wilhelm Ludwig
description: German orchidologist.

page_title_longer_max-80: Kraepelin, Karl (earlier publ. Carl) [Mathias Friedrich] [std. Kraep.]
name: Kraepelin, Karl (earlier publ.: Carl) [Mathias Friedrich]
description: German botanist and zoologist; Dr. phil. Leipzig 1872; from 1873-1874 high school teacher at Leipzig; from 1878-1889 at the Hamburg Johanneum; from 1889-1914 director of the natural history museum at Hamburg.

name: Kräusel, Richard
description: German palaebotanist; Dr. phil. Breslau 1913 (with F. A. Pax); high school teacher at Frankfurt from 1920; professor of palaeobotany 1928; from 1939 director of the palaebotanical department of the Senckenberg Musuem; Dr. h.c. Durham 1963; student of the Devonian and the Central European mesozoic flora.

name: Kralik, Jean-Louis
description: Alsatian-French botanist; explorer of the mediterranean flora; curator of the Cosson herbarium 1855-1885.

name: Kramer, Franz August
description: German botanist and high school teacher at Chemnitz.

name: Kramer, Wilhelm Heinrich
description: German-born Austrian botanist and physician at Bruck a. Leitha.

name: Kranz, Cajetan Anton
description: German botanist at München.

name: Krapf, Karl J. von
description: Austrian botanist, "kaiserlich-königlicher Hofrath und Leibarzt."

name: Krašan, Franz
description: Austrian botanist, high school teacher at Graz.

name: Krasnov [Krassnov], Andrej Nicolaevic
description: Russian scientist at Kharkov.

name: Krasser, Fridolin
description: Austrian botanist and palaeobotanist; Dr. phil. Wien 1887; from 1887 in various functions in Wien, e.g. assistant at the Naturh. Museum 18961902; 1901-1906 at the ?nologisch-pomologischen Lehranstalt in Klosterneuburg; from 1906-1922 professor of botany at the technical university of Praha.

name: Krasske, Georg
description: German diatomologist; teacher at the Volksschule Wattenbach near Kassel 1908-1913; later at Kassel, from 1923-1951 as high school teacher at the middle school for boys.

name: Krauer, Johann Georg
description: Swiss botanist and physician at Luzern and Rothenburg.

name: Kraus, Gregor Konrad Michael
description: German physiological botanist; Dr. phil. Würzburg 1866; from 1866-1867 at Bonn as pupil of J. Sachs; 1867-1869 "Privatdozent" at Würzburg; 1868-1869 at Leipzig; 1869-1873 professor of botany at Erlangen; 1872-1898 idem at Halle succeeding de Bary; from 1898-1914 idem at Würzburg succeeding Julius Sachs.

name: Krause, Christian Ludwig
description: German botanist and gardener at Berlin.

page_title_longer_max-80: Krause, Ernst Hans Ludwig [std. E.H.L. Krause]
name: Krause, Ernst Hans Ludwig
description: German physician and botanist; Dr. med. Berlin 1881; prolific batologist; longtime "Oberstabarzt" at Saarlouis; later in Rostock.

name: Krause, Ernst Ludwig
description: German botanist; popular writer on botany; used the pseudonym Carus Sterne.

name: Krause, Johann Wilhelm
description: German clergyman and botanist in Taupadel (Sachsen-Weimar).

name: Krause, Kurt
description: German botanist of the Engler school at Berlin.

page_title_longer_max-80: Krauss, Christian Ferdinand Friedrich von [std. C. Krauss]
name: Krauss, Christian Ferdinand Friedrich von
description: German botanist and zoologist; Dr. Phil. Heidelberg 1836; travelled in South Africa 1838-1840; from 1840 in various functions at the natural history museum at Stuttgart.

name: Krauss, G.
description: German gardener at Würzburg.

name: Krauss, Johan Carl
description: German-born professor of medecine at Leiden.

name: Krebs, (Georg) Ludwig Englehard
description: German naturalist; at the Cape 18171844.

name: Krebs, F. L.
description: German forestry botanist; "herzoglich Braunschweiger Forstschreiber."

name: Kreh, Wilhelm
description: German botanist and phytosociologist at Stuttgart.

name: Kremer, Jean Pierre
description: French (Lorraine) botanist at Metz.

name: Krempelhuber, August von
description: German lichenologist and forester; "Königlicher bayerischer Forstrath" in München.

name: Kreutzer, Karl (Carl) Joseph
description: Austrian botanist and librarian at Wien; later University librarian at Graz.

name: Krieger, Karl Wilhelm
description: German mycologist; educated in the seminary at Nossen; high school teacher at Porschdorf nr. Schandau 1869-1876; from then on at Königstein a.E.

page_title_longer_max-80: Krieger, Louis Charles Christopher [std. L. Krieg.]
name: Krieger, Louis Charles Christopher
description: American mycological artist, who painted e.g. for Farlow's Icones farlowianae, for USDA, and for Howard A. Kelly.

name: Krieger, Willi
description: German desmidiologist; Dr. phil. Marburg 1927; from 1923 collaborator of Kolkwitz at the Berlin "Anstalt für Wasser-, Bodenund Lufthygiene".

name: Krocker, Anton Johann
description: German botanist and physician in Breslau (now Wroclaw), Silezia.

page_title_longer_max-80: Krok, Thorgny Ossian Bolivar Napoleon [std. Krok]
name: Krok, Thorgny Ossian Bolivar Napoleon
description: Swedisn botanist, bibliographer, and high school teacher at Stockholm.

name: Krombach, Johann Heinrich Wilhelm
description: German-born Luxemburg botanist and pharmacist; assistant pharmacist at Soest (1810-1811), Mainz (1811-1813), Aachen (1814-1815); pharmacist at Diekirch, Luxemburg 1815-1870; Luxemburg citizen 1830; professor of natural sciences Diekirch 1830-1870, at Luxemburg 1871-1881.

name: Krombholz, Julius Vincenz von
description: Czech mycologist; Dr. med. Erfurt 1811; 1811-1814 prosector, from 1814 professor of theoretical surgery, from 1820-1836 "Professor der Staatsarzneikunde" at Praha.

name: Kronfeld, Ernst Moriz
description: Austro-Hungarian botanist; born at Lemberg (Lwow); editor of the Vienna Fremdenblatt.

name: Krüger, Ernst
description: German bryologist at Eisenach; high school teacher at Sunnabei Vacha 1880-1897; at Eisenach 1897-1924.

name: Krüger, Marcus Salomonides
description: German bibliographer.

name: Krug, Carl Wilhelm Leopold
description: German botanist, businessman and consular official; in Puerto Rico 1857-1876; later working with I. Urban on a flora of the West Indies.

name: Krukoff, Boris Alexander
description: Russian-born American botanical explorer; honorary curator of economic botany at NY 1941-1950, honorary curator 1971-x.

name: Kruse, Friedrich
description: German botanist; professor at the K. Wilhelms-Gymnasium in Berlin.

name: Kuckuck, Ernst Herman Paul

name: Kudô, Yûshun
description: Japanese botanist; at Hokkaido University with Miyabe; later at Taihoku Imperial University.

name: Kühn, Julius Gotthelf
description: German phytopathologist at Halle, Preussischer Geheimer Ober-Regierungsrat.

name: Kühner, Robert
description: French mycologist; Dr. sci. nat. Paris 1926; high school teacher at Lille (1921-1932); botanical assistant, Fac. Sci. Alger and Paris (1932-1934); lecturer, later professor, at the Fac. Sci. Lyon (1938).

name: Kükenthal, Georg
