name: Kützing, Friedrich Traugott (Kuetzing)
description: German algologist; Dr. phil. Marburg 1837; teacher at Nordhausen (1835-1883).

name: Kufferath, Hubert
description: Belgian algologist and bacteriologist; Dr. sci. Bruxelles 1910; from 1904-1920 at the Institut Pasteur du Brabant; from 1920-1947 director of the Institut Meurice-Chimie in Bruxelles.

name: Kuhl, Heinrich
description: Dutch botanical and zoological explorer in the Netherlands East-Indies; member of the "Natuurwetenschappelijke Commissie".

name: Kuhlmann, João Geraldo
description: Brazilian botanist and collector at São Paulo.

name: Kuhn, Friedrich Adalbert Maximilian ["Max"]
description: German pteridologist at Berlin; Dr. phil. Berlin 1867; high school teacher at the Königstädtische Realschule (later Gymnasium) from 1870-1893, from 1889 with the title of professor.

name: Kummer, Georg
description: Swiss botanist born at Tayngen near Schaffhausen; studied at Zürich; high school teacher and school inspector at Schaffhausen.

name: Kummer, Paul
description: German clergyman and lichenologist; private teacher 18571863; from 1863-1877 curate at Zerbst; from 1877 minister at Hann.-Münden.

name: Kunow, Gustav
description: German botanist at Freienwalde a. O.

name: Kunth, Carl Sigismund
description: German botanist; joined A. v. Humboldt in Paris 1813, to work on his New World collections, from 1829 professor of botany at the University of Berlin.

name: Kuntze, Carl Ernst Otto
description: German traveller, botanist and polemic nomenclatural reformer; Dr. phil. Freiburg i.B. 1878; travelled around the world 1874-1876 and in 1904.

name: Kunze, Gustav
description: German botanist; Dr. med. Leipzig 1819; from 1837-1851 director of the Leipzig botanical garden; professor of botany at Leipzig University (1835); induced his pupil Willkomm to go to Spain.

name: Kunze, Johannes
description: German mycologist at Eisleben.

page_title_longer_max-80: Kunze, Karl Sebastian Heinrich [std. K. Kunze]
name: Kunze, Karl Sebastian Heinrich
description: German teacher and botanist at Flensburg.

name: Kurr, Johann Gottlob von
description: German botanist and pharmacist; Dr. mod. Tübingen 1832; from 1812-1825 at various pharmacies, from 1832-1870 teacher at the "Gewerbeschule" at Stuttgart which became the polytechnical school in 1841; collected for the Esslingen Reiseverein.

name: Kurtz, Fritz (Frederico)
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Berlin 1879; from 187880 at Berlin-Dahlem under Eichler; to Argentina 1884, professor of botany at Cordoba 1884- 1915.

page_title_longer_max-80: Kurtz, Karl Marie Max [std. K. Kurtz]
name: Kurtz, Karl Marie Max
description: German botanist, high school teacher and botanist at Ellwangen 1876-1906.

name: Kurz, Herman
description: American bryologist; Ph. D. Chicago 1922; from 1922 at Tallahassee, Fla.

name: Kurz, Wilhelm Sulpiz
description: German botanist in the Dutch East Indian army 1856 (as "Johann Amann"); 1859-1863 at Buitenzorg (Bogor); from 1864 curator of the herbarium at Calcutta.

name: Kylin, Johan Harald
description: Swedish algologist; Dr. phil. Uppsala 1907; from 1920 professor of botany at Lund.

name: Laban, Friedrich Christian
description: German botanist and high school teacher at Hamburg.

page_title_longer_max-80: Labillardière, Jacques Julien Houttou de [std. Labill.]
name: Labillardière, Jacques Julien Houttou de
description: French explorer and botanist; studied medicine at Montpellier; travelled in near East 1786; on expedition to find La Pérouse 1791-1795; from 1828 at Rouen.

name: Labouret, J.
description: French cactus grower at Raffec, Charente.

name: Labram, Jonas David
description: Swiss botanical artist at Basel

name: Lacaita, Charles Carmichael
description: British amateur botanist of Italian descent; country gentleman of independent means; specially interested in the flora of Italy; collected in Sikkim (1913) and Spain (1925-28).

name: Lachenal, Werner de
description: Swiss botanist; Dr. med. Basel 1759; professor of anatomy and botany at Basel (1776-1800)

name: Lachmann, Heinrich Wilhelm Ludolph
description: German physician and botanist at Braunschweig.

name: Lachot, Henri
description: French botanist and high school teacher at Magny-la-Ville, Semur (Côte-d'Or).

name: Lackowitz, August Wilhelm
description: German botanist; high school teacher in Berlin.

name: Lacoizqueta, José Maria de
description: Spanish clergyman and botanist at Navarte in Navarra.

name: Lacouture, Charles
description: French botanist; teacher of natural sciences at the Collège Saint-Clément de Metz until 1872; later at Dijon.

name: Lacroix, Louis-Sosthène Veyron de
description: French clergyman and botanist at Montmorillon, Saint-Romain-sur-Vienne, ultimately "Aumônier des Petites Soeurs des Pauvres" at Poitiers.

name: Lademann, Johann Matthias Friedrich
description: German botanist; born at Hasselberg, Altmark; Dr. phil. Helmstadt 1785.

name: Laestadius, Carl Petter
description: Swedish botanist; high school teacher at Umeå 1861-1913; nephew of Lars Levi Laestadius.

name: Laestadius, Lars Levi
description: Swedish clergyman and botanist; born in Arjepluog (Lapland); clergyman at Karesuando (1825-1848) and Pajala (Norrbotten) (1848-1861); pupil of Wahlenberg.

name: Laffon, J. C.
description: Swiss botanist at Schaffhausen.

page_title_long: La Fons, Alexandre de, Baron de Mélicocq
page_title_longer_max-80: La Fons, Alexandre de, Baron de Mélicocq [std. La Fons]
name: La Fons, Alexandre de, Baron de Mélicocq
name_ed: La Fons, Alexandre de, Baron de Mélicocq
description: French botanist at Noyon.

name: Lagarde, Joannes Joseph
description: Strassburg mycologist; Dr. sci. nat. Paris 1906.

page_title_longer_max-80: Lagasca y Segura [La Gasca], Mariano [std. Lag.]
name: Lagasca y Segura [La Gasca], Mariano
description: Spanish botanist at the Madrid botanical garden; in exile to England 1822; in Jersey 1831-1834; back to Spain 1834-1839.

name: Lagerberg, Karl Erik Torsten
description: Swedish botanist; Dr. phil. Uppsala 1909; from 1910 at Skogshögskolan

name: Lagerheim, Nils Gustaf (von, de)
description: Swedish microbiologist and cryptogamic botanist; Dr. phil. h.c. Uppsala 1893; Dr. jur. h.c. St. Andrews 1911; at Lisboa 1889; at the University of Quito, Equador 1892-1895; at Tromsö 1892; from 1895-1925 professor of botany at Stockholm.

name: Lagerstedt, Nils Gerhard Wilhelm
description: Swedish high school teacher, librarian and botanist at Stockholm (Östermalm); Dr. phil. Uppsala 1869.

name: Lagrèze-Fossat, Adrien Rose Arnaud
description: French lawyer and botanist at Moissac.

name: Laguna y Villanueva, Máximo
description: Spanish botanist and silviculturist, director of the Escuela de Ingenieros de Montes at El Escorial.

page_title_long: Laharpe (La Harpe), Jean Jacques Charles de
page_title_longer_max-80: Laharpe (La Harpe), Jean Jacques Charles de [std. Laharpe]
name: Laharpe (La Harpe), Jean Jacques Charles de
name_ed: Laharpe (La Harpe), Jean Jacques Charles de
description: Swiss botanist; physician at the provincial hospital of Lausanne.

page_title_longer_max-80: Lahm, Johann Gottlieb Franz-Xaver [std. J. Lahm]
name: Lahm, Johann Gottlieb Franz-Xaver

description: German botanist and high school teacher at Laubach (Oberhessen).

page_title_long: Laicharding (Laicharting) zu Eichberg und Lützegnad, Johann Nepomuk
page_title_longer_max-80: Laicharding zu Eichberg und Lützegnad, Johann Nepomuk [std. Laichard.]

name: Lakela, Olga

name: Lakowitz, Conrad Waldemar

page_title_longer_max-80: La Llave, Pablo de [std. La Llave]

page_title_long: Lamarck, Jean Baptiste Antoine Pierre Monnet de

page_title_long: Lamb, Ivan Mackenzie, later Elke Mackenzie

name: Lambert, Wilhelm

name: Lambotte, Jean Baptiste Émile

name: Lamotte, Martial

page_title_longer_max-80: Lamouroux, Jean Vincent Félix [std. J.V. Lamour.]

page_title_longer_max-80: Lamouroux, Jean [Jeanin,] Pierre Péthion [std. J.P. Lamour.]

page_title_longer_max-80: Lamson-Scribner, Frank (originally Franklin Pierce Lamson) [std. Lams.-Scribn.]

page_title_long: Lamy de la Chapelle, Pierre Marie Édouard
page_title_longer_max-80: Lamy de la Chapelle, Pierre Marie Édouard [std. Lamy]
name: Lamy de la Chapelle, Pierre Marie Édouard
name_ed: Lamy de la Chapelle, Pierre Marie Édouard
description: French cryptogamist and banker at Limoges.

page_title_long: Lanessan, Jean Marie Antoine de [Jean Louis de]

description: British-Ceylonese forester and botanist at the Ceylon Forestry Department.

name: Lewis, Isaac McKinney
description: American botanist; educated at Indiana State University; instructor of botany at New Hampshire State College (1908-1909); idem, later professor of botany at the University of Texas from 1909.

name: Lexarza, Juan Martinez de
description: Mexican physician and botanist.

name: Leybold, Friedrich
description: German botanist and pharmacist; pupil of Martius; settled in Chile (1855) as pharmaceutical industrialist.

name: Leydolt, Franz
description: Austrian mineralogist and botanist at Vienna: Dr. med. Wien 1837; assistant with J. F. von Jacquin 1838; from 1843 at the Vienna polytechnic, from 1847 as professor of mineralogy and geognosy.

name: Leysser, Friedrich Wilhelm von
description: German administrator and botanist; "Preussischer Kriegsund Domänenrat" at Halle a. Saalc.

name: L'Héritier de Brutelle, Charles-Louis
description: French magistrate and amateur botanist, at Paris; from 1775-1789 counsellor at the" Cour des Aides"; after the revolution at the Department of Justice; died by murder in unclarified circumstances.

name: L'Herminier, Ferdinand
description: Guadeloupe physician and botanist of French descent at Point à Pitre, son of the French pharmacist and plant collector Félix Louis L'Herminier.

name: Lhotsky [Lhotzky], Johann [baptized Jan]
description: Austro-Hungarian naturalist and plant collecter born in Poland of Czech parentage; Dr. Med. Wien 1830; in Brazil (1830), in Australia (New South Wales) (1832-1836); Tasmania 1836-1838; in London 1838-1840.

name: Li, Hui-Lin
description: Chinese botanist, MS Yenching University; Ph. D. Harvard 1942; at Univ. of Pennsylvania 1943-1946; professor of botany at Soochow Univ., China, 19461947; id. at National Taiwan University 1947-1950; from 1952 in various functions at the University of Pennsylvania, from 1974 John Bartram professor of botany; naturalized U.S. citizen 1962.

name: Libert, Marie-Anne
description: Belgian botanist, born in Malmédy.

name: Liboschitz, Joseph
description: Russian (Austro-Hungarian) botanist and physician in St. Petersburg; later in Vienna.

page_title_longer_max-80: Lichtenstein, August Gerhard Gottfried [std. A. Licht.]
name: Lichtenstein, August Gerhard Gottfried
description: German botanist at Helmstädt.

name: Lichtenstein, Georg Rudolph
description: German botanist; 1774-1804 professor of medicine at the Julius-Carl-Universität at Helmstädt.

name: Lickleder, Max
description: German Benedictine clergyman; ordained Metten 1851; high school teacher and bryologist at the Studien-Anstalt Metten.

name: Licopoli, Gaetano
description: Italian botanist at Napoli; high school teacher and assistant at the Napoli botanical garden; student of Gasparrini

name: Lid, Johannes
description: Norwegian botanist; curator of the Botanical Museum of Oslo University from 1919-1956.

name: Lidbeck, Eric Gustaf
description: Swedish botanist at Lund; Dr. phil. Uppsala 1749; adjunct nat. hist. Lund 1750, curator ("prefekt") of the botanical garden 1752; professor of natural history at Lund University 1756-1795.

name: Lidforss, Bengt
description: Swedish batologist; Dr, phil. Lund 1893; lecturer in botany at Lund university 1897-1905, 1906-1911; professor of botany at Uppsala 1910-1911, at Lund 1911-1913.

page_title_longer_max-80: Liebe, Karl Leopold Theodor [std. K.L.T. Liebe]
name: Liebe, Karl Leopold Theodor
description: German ornithologist, mineralogist, geologist, and botanist; Dr. phil. Jena 1852; high school teacher at Hamburg (1852-1855); id. Gera (1855-1861 at the" Gewerbeschule", 1861-1894 at the "Rutheneum"); student of Oken and Schleiden.

name: Liebe, Theodor
description: German botanist, high school teacher at the FriedrichsWerdersche Gewerbeschule in Berlin.

name: Lieblein, Franz Kaspar
description: German botanist and high school teacher at Fulda," Hochfürstlich-Fuldischen Hofkammerrath und Hofapotheker".

name: Liebmann, Frederik Michael
description: Danish botanist; from 1837-1840 and 18451853 lecturer at the Copenhagen veterinary college; travelled in Cuba and Mexico 1840- 1843; from 1845-1852 extraordinary professor of botany at Copenhagen University; in 1852 succeeding Schouw as ordinary professor and director of the Copenhagen botanical garden.

name: Liégard, Auguste
description: French physician and botanist.

name: Lienau, W.,
description: German pharmacist and botanist at Eutin, later court chemist at Rendsburg.

name: Lightfoot, John
description: British clergyman and botanist; domestic chaplain to the Dowager Duchess of Portland at Bulstock, Bucks.; later at Uxbridge; one of the founders of the Linnean Society of London.

name: Lignier, Elie Antoine Octave
description: French palaeobotanist; Dr. Sci. Paris 1887; "préparateur" at Lille with C. E. Bertrand 1880-1887; lecturer (1887) and professor of botany (1889), as well as director of the botanical garden (1896) at the University of Caen.

name: Lilja, Nils
description: Swedish botanist, publicist and (from 1843) organist (klockare) at Billinge in Skåne.

name: Liljeblad, Samuel
description: Swedish botanist and rural economist; Dr. phil. Uppsala 1788; Dr. med. ib. 1793; amanuensis at the Uppsala nat. hist. museum 1789; "Borgströmiansk adjunkt" 1790; keeper of the library and collections of the Uppsala Vetenskapsso- cietet (1793-1802); from 1802 professor Borgströmianus.

name: Lillo, Miguel
description: Argentine self-taught botanist; Dr. h.c. Univ. Plata 1914; from 1892 active at the Tucuman "Oficina Químia."

page_title_long: Limminghe, Alfred Marie Antoine Comte de
page_title_longer_max-80: Limminghe, Alfred Marie Antoine Comte de [std. Limm.]
name: Limminghe, Alfred Marie Antoine Comte de
name_ed: Limminghe, Alfred Marie Antoine Comte de
description: Belgian cryptogamist at Namur and Gentinnes (nr. Marbais, Brabant); assassinated in the streets of Rome, April 1861.

name: Limpricht, Hans Wolfgang
description: German botanist, Dr. phil. Breslau 1902; traveller in China and Japan; son of Karl Gustav L.

name: Limpricht, Karl Gustav
description: German (Silesian) bryologist; high school teacher at a girl's College at Bunzlau (1858-1869); idem at the evangelical high school Breslau (1869-1902), from 1895 as principal ("Oberlehrer").

name: Lincke, Johann Rudolf
description: German compller of illustrated works.

name: Linczevski, Igorj Alexandrovicz
description: Russian botanist and botanical explorer, collected in central Asia 1925-1950 and south-west China (1955-1956); co-author of the Flora URSS; specialist on botanical nomenelature.

name: Lind, Jens Wilhelm August
description: Danish pharmacist and mycologist; assistant at the state phytopathological service 1913-1917; pharmacist at Østbirk 1919-1926, from then on id. at Viborg.

name: Lindau, Gustav
description: German lichenologist; student of Schwendener; Dr. phil. Berlin 1888; 1888-1890 at Münster with Brefeld; from 1892-1923 (after 1899 "Kustos", 1902 professor) at Berlin-Dahlem.

name: Lindberg, Gustaf Anders
description: Swedish botanist and city treasurer at Stockholm; travelled in Brazil with A. F. Regnell (1854-1855); brother of S. O. Lindberg; specialist on Rhipsalis.

name: Lindberg, Harald
description: Finnish botanist of Swedish origin; Dr. phil. Helsinki 1909; from 1910 at the Helsinki Botanical Museum; son of S. O. Lindberg.

name: Lindberg, Sextus Otto
description: Swedish bryologist (from 1865 Finnish); educated at Stockholm and Uppsala; teacher at the Pharmaceutical Institution of Stockholm (18621865); professor of botany at Helsingfors University (successor to W. Nylander) 1865-1889.

name: Lindblad, Matts Adolf
description: Swedish botanist; Dr. phil. Ups. 1854; lecturer in botany at Uppsala 1855-1873.

name: Lindblom, Alexis Edvard
description: Swedish botanist; founder and first editor of Botaniska Notiser; Dr. phil. Lund 1826, lecturer at Lund 1831-1851; travelled in Norway 1826, 1837, 1839.

name: Lindeberg, Carl Johan
description: Swedish botanist and high school teacher at Göteborg 1859-1889.

name: Lindemann, Eduard Emanuilovitch von
description: Russian botanist at Elisabethgrad (Cherson), son of Emanuel von Lindemann, studied natural sciences and medicine at St. Petersburg 1841-1847; military surgeon in the Russian army from 1848; Dr. phil. h.c. Odessa 1877.

name: Lindemann, Emanuel von
description: Russian botanist and entomologist at Mitau; studied at Erfurt (1813) and Dorpat (1814-1816); high school teacher at Mitau 1820-1845.

name: Linden, Lucien
description: Belgian horticulturist, son of J. J. Linden,

name: Lindenberg, Johann Bernhard Wilhelm
description: German bryologist, lawyer at Lübeck, later at Hamburg, ultimately Amtsverwalter (administrator) at Bergedorf.

name: Linder, David Hunt
description: American mycologist; Ph. D. Harvard 1926; author on fungi imperfecti; at the Shaw School of Botany, Washington, Univ., and the Missouri botanical Garden, St. Louis 1926-1931; curator of the Farlow herbarium (1932-1946).

name: Lindgren, Sven Johan
description: Swedish botanist; teacher at the Degeberg agricultural college in Västergötland.

name: Lindheimer, Ferdinand Jacob
description: German botanist; in 1834 as political refugee to the United States; settled in 1840 at New-Braunfels, Texas, in which state he collected extensively.

name: Lindinger, Karl Hermann Leonhard
description: German botanist at Hamburg.

name: Lindley, John
description: British botanist; Dr. phil. München 1832; professor of botany at University College London 1829-1860.

name: Lindman, Carl Axel Magnus
description: Swedish botanist and traveller; Dr. phil. Uppsala 1886; teacher at Stockholm 1887-1904; from 1905 at the Natural History Museum at Stockholm; travelled widely in Europe and North Africa; in Brazil 1892-1894.

name: Lindroth [later: Liro], Johan Ivar
description: Finnish botanist; 1921-1928 at Turku; later director of the phytopathological institute at Helsinki.

name: Lindsay, William Lauder
description: Scottish lichenologist and physician; MD Edinburgh 1852; at Murray's Royal Asylum, Perth 1854-1879; collected in Iceland and New Zealand.

name: Lindstedt, Karl
description: German mycologist at Berlin, Dr. phil. Berlin 1872.

name: Lingelsheim, Alexander von
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Rostock 1906; at the Botanical Museum and Garden, Breslau, 1904-1929; pharmacist 1929-1937; lecturer in pharmacognosy 1926, professor 1932-1937.

name: Linhart, Gyögy (Georg)
description: Hungarian mycologist.

name: Link, Johann Heinrich Friedrich
description: German nature philosopher and botanist; Dr. med. Göttingen 1789; at Rostock 1792; director botanical garden Breslau 1811- 1815; professor of botany at Berlin 1815-1851; successor to Willdenow.

name: Linkola, Kaarlo (until 1906 Collan)
description: Finnish botanist; Dr. phil. Helsinki 1919; assistant at the Botanical Institute of the agricultural section of Helsinki Univ. 19131922, from 1917 also working at the Tammisto experiment station; professor of botany at Turku Univ. 1923-1925, id. at Helsinki 1925-1942.

page_title_longer_max-80: Linnaeus, Carl (from 1761 Carl von Linné) [std. L.]
name: Linnaeus, Carl (from 1761: Carl von Linné)
description: Swedish botanist, physician and zoologist; Dr. med. Harderwijk 1735; in the Netherlands 1735-1738, for the greater part of the time as physician to George Clifford at the Hartecamp near Haarlem; from 1738-1741 practicing physician at Stockholm; professor of medicine and botany at Uppsala 1741-1778; founder of modern plant systematics and nomenclature.

page_title_longer_max-80: Linné, Carl von, filius [std. L. fil.]
name: Linné, Carl von, filius
description: Swedish botanist; studied at Uppsala, Dr. med. 1765, professor of medicine and botany ib. 1777-1783.

name: Linney, William Marcus
description: American botanist in Kentucky.

name: Linton, Edward Francis
description: English botanist of independent means; Univ. College Oxford D. A. 1871, M. A. 1874; 1871-1875 curate at St. Paul's, Preston; 1875-1878 rector at St. George's-in-the-Fields; 1878-1888 vicar at Sprowston, Norfolk; 1888-1901 retired at Bournemouth; 1901-1920 rector at Edmondsham, Dorset; ultimately at Southbourne, Hampshire.

name: Linton, William James
description: British engraver, botanist and political reformer; to United States, at Appledore nr. New Haven, Conn. from 1866 as private printer and publisher.

page_title_longer_max-80: Linton, Rev. William Richardson [std. W.R. Linton]
name: Linton, Rev. William Richardson
description: English botanist; ultimately vicar of Shirley (1886); brother of E. F. Linton.

name: Liou, Tchen-ngo
description: Chinese botanist.

name: Lipp, Franz Joseph
description: German botanist at Freiburg im Breisgau, "Protomedikus von Vorderösterreich."

name: Lippert, Xaver Joseph
description: German botanist and physician.

name: Lippmaa, Teodor (until 1924: Lipman)
description: Estonian botanist; Dr. phil. Tartu 1926; at Tartu University as assistant lecturer (1923), lecturer (1927) and professor of botany (1930-1943); worker on vegetable pigments, geobotany and Estonian floristics.

name: Lipschitz, Sergej Julievitsch
description: Soviet botanist, bibliographer and biohistorian at Leningrad.

name: Lipsky, Vladimir lppolitovitch (Wladimir Hippolitowitsch)
description: Russian botanist; explorer of Central Asia; until 1917 at Leningrad, later at Kiew and Odessa.

name: Lisa, Domenico
description: Italian botanist in Piemonte, head gardner at the Torino botanical garden.

name: Lisboa, José Camillo
description: Indian botanist and physician at Bombay; died at Poona.

name: List, Friedrich Ludwig
description: German botanist and high school teacher at Tilsit, Western Prussia.

name: Lister, Arthur
description: English wine merchant and mycologist living in Bedfordshire, then at Bradford, since 1857 at Leytonstone nr. London; retired from business 1888 and often residing also at Lyme Regis; leading authority on myxomycetes.

name: Lister, Guilielma
description: British botanist; daughter of Arthur Lister; educated at home; constant companion of her father in his studies on Mycetozoa.

name: Litardière, René de
description: French botanist; Lic. Sci. Univ. Poitiers 1908, Dr. Sci. nat. Paris 1921; 1920-1931 at the University of Lille, from 1931-1954 at the Faculté des Sciences, Grenoble; retired at Mazières-en-Gâtine; botanical explorer of Corsica.

name: Litschauer, Viktor
description: Austrian mycologist; studied at Vienna under v. Höhnel 1899-1903; lecturer at the Vienna "Gewerbemuseum" 1903-1908; from 1908-1936 professor of natural history at the "Handelsakademie", Innsbruck.

name: Little, Elbert Luther, Jr.
description: American botanist; dendrologist at Washington, D. C.

name: Litvinov [Litwinow], Dimitri Ivanovich
description: Russian botanist and explorer of central Asia.

name: Liu, Ju-ch'iang
description: Chinese botanist

name: Ljungström, Ernst Leopold
description: Swedish botanist, at Lund 1883-1903; later at Stockholm.

name: Llano, George Albert
description: Cuban-born American lichenologist; student of C. W. Dodge.

name: Llanos, Antonio
description: Philippine botanist; calceate Augustinian friar at Manila.

name: Llenas y Fernández, Manuel
description: Spanish lichenologist; originally at Madrid; later at Barcelona.

name: Lloyd, Curtis Gates
description: American pharmaceutical industrialist, wholesale druggist and mycologist at Cincinnati.

name: Lloyd, George N.
description: British botanist at Edinburgh.

name: Lloyd, James
description: British-born botanist educated and living at Thouaré and Nantes in France.

name: Lobarzewski, Hyacinth Strzemù von
description: Galician bryologist, professor of botany at Lemberg.

name: Lobb, Thomas
description: British plant collector and explorer for Veitch and Son (1843-1860) who collected in India and the Malesian area.

name: Lobb, William,
description: British plant collector and explorer for Veitch & Son who collected mainly in the Americas; brother of Thomas Lobb.

name: L'Obel, Mathias de [Lobel, Lobelius]
description: Flemish botanist; worked with Rondelet at Montpellier 1565-1566; from 1566-1572 in England; from 1572-1584 in the Netherlands, from 1584 again in England; botanist to James I; curator of Lord Edward Zouche's garden at Hackney.

name: Locke, John
description: American geologist, botanist, physician, inventor; M. D. Yale 1819; from 1823 living at Cincinnati (Ohio), leading a preparatory school from 1823; professor of chemistry in the Medical College of Ohio from 1835; collaborator in the geological survey of Ohio.

name: Lodder, Jacomina
description: Dutch mycologist at Delft; specialist on yeasts.

name: Loddiges, Conrad [L.]
description: Dutch-born British horticulturist who settled in England about 1761 as nurseryman at Hackney and who introduced many plants into the British Isles, especially from the United States.

name: Loddiges, George
description: British horticulturist, nurseryman at Hackney; son of Conrad Loddiges.

name: Löfgren, Albert [Loefgren, Alberto]
description: Swedish-born botanist who settled (1874) in Brazil; director of the São Paulo botanical garden 1898-1906; ultimately at the botanical garden of Rio de Janeiro

name: Löfling, Pehr (Loefling)
description: Swedish botanist and explorer; to Spain 1751; from 1754-1756 in northern S. America; "Linnaei bästa discipel."

name: Loehr, Egid von
description: German botanist.

name: Loehr [Löhr], Matthias Joseph
description: German pharmacist and botanist at Koblenz; later at Koln.

name: Lönnegren, August Valfrid
description: Swedish mycologist and linguist; teacher at Lule high school

name: Lönnrot, Elias
description: Finnish botanist.

name: Lönnroth, Knut Johan
description: Swedish botanist; from 1859 ecclesiastical administrator at Kalmar.

name: Lörch, Ph, J.
description: German botanist, high school teacher at Heckingen

name: Loescher, Eduard
description: German horticulturist.

name: Lösecke, August Georg von
description: German mycologist and pharmacist.

name: Loesel, Johannes [Loeselius]
description: German botanist and physician; Dr. phil. Königsberg 1632; Dr. med. Leiden 1639, professor of medicine at Königsberg University 1639-1655.

name: Loesener, Ludwig Eduard Theodor
description: German botanist of the Engler school; Dr. phil. Berlin 1890; from 1896-1920 at the Botanical Museum, Berlin-Dahlem.

name: Loeske, Leopold
description: German amateur bryologist, journalist, later administrator.

name: Loew, Ernst
description: German botanist and flower-biologist; Dr. phil. Berlin 1865; from 1867-1906 teacher at the (later) Kaiser-Wilhelm-Realgymnasium.

name: Löw, Immanuel
description: Hungarian rabbi and scholar; rabbi of Szeged 1878-1944; specialist in talmudic and rabbinic lexicography.

name: Loher, August
description: German botanist; wholesale dealer in pharmaceuticals; from 1889 resident in the Philippines.

name: Lohwag, Heinrich
description: Austrian cryptogamist: student of R. Wettstein; Dr. phil. Wien 1907; professor at the Staatsgymnasium in Brüx (Bohemia) 1908-1914; from 19141918 at Reichenberg; from 1918 at the first Academic Gymnasium in Wien; from 1928 lecturer, from 1940 professor at the Universität Wien.

name: Loiseleur-Deslongchamps, Jean Louis Auguste
description: French physician and botanist; in the French armée des Alpes 1793-1797; Dr. med. Paris 1806; physician at the "bureau de charité du neuvième arrondissement" later working mainly on botany.

name: Loitlesberger, Karl
description: Austrian cryptogamist, high school teacher e.g. at the Stella matutina at Feldkirch.

name: Lojacono-Pojero, Michele
description: Italian botanist at Palermo.

name: Lojka, Hugo
description: Hungarian lichenologist; born in Galicia; studied in Vienna; later high school teacher at Budapest.

name: Londes, Friedrich Wilhelm
description: German botanist at Goettingen.

name: Long, William Henry
description: American mycologist; studied at Baylor University, Waco, Texas; A. B. 1888; professor of natural history at Waco 1888-1892, from 1892-1899 at Greenville, Texas; A. M. Univ. Texas 1900; Ph. D. id. 1917; 1900-1910 at Denton, Texas; from 1910-1911 at USDA, Washington, with USDA at Albuquerque, New Mexico 1911-1937.

name: Longo, Biagio
description: Italian botanist; assistant at the botanical institute in Rome 1896, professor of botany at Siena 1907-1915; director of the botanical garden of Pisa 19151929; professor of botany at Napoli 1929-1942.

name: Longyear, Burton Orange
description: American forester and botanist in Colorado.

name: Lonitzer [Lonicerus], Adam
description: German physician and botanist at Frankfurt and Mainz (1545-1553), Marburg (1553-1554) and Frankfurt a. M. (1555-1586). (Lonitzer)

name: Looser, Gualterio
description: Chilean botanist at Santiago de Chile.

name: Loosjes, Adriaan
description: Dutch botanist, poet, novelist and bookseller; studied at Amsterdam, at Haarlem from 1782.

name: Lopriore (Lo Priore), Giuseppe
description: Italian botanist; Dr. agr. Portici 1887; assistant at Portici but often working in Berlin 1887-1895; professor of botany at the enological institute of Catania 1895-1909; director of the agricultural experiment station at Modena 1909-1925; professor of botany at the agricultural university of Portici 1925-1928.

name: Lorch, Wilhelm
description: German botanist; studied at München; high school teacher at Berlin.

name: Lorek, Christian Gottlieb
description: German botanist and high school teacher at Königsberg; Dr. phil. Königsberg 1812; taught at the Burgschule 1811-1850, retired because of increasing loss of eye-sight.

page_title_longer_max-80: Lorente y Asensi, Vicente Alfonso [std. Lorente]
name: Lorente y Asensi, Vicente Alfonso
description: Spanish botanist; professor of botany and director of the botanical garden at Valencia (1804-1813).

name: Lorentz, Paul (Pablo) Günther
description: German botanist: in Germany until 1869; professor of botany at Cordoba, Argentina until 1874; later high school teacher at Concepción, Uruguay.

name: Lorenz, Annie
description: American hepaticologist; high school teacher at Hartford, Conn.

name: Lorenz, B.
description: German botanist; high school teacher at Zittau.

name: Loret, Henri
description: French botanist; originally from Charente-Inférieure; at Montpellier from 1860 in charge of the botanic garden and herbaria of the Université de Montpellier.

name: Loret, Victor
description: French archeologist and botanist.

name: Lorey, A.
description: German botanist and high school teacher at Apolda.

name: Lorey, Félix-Nicolas
description: French botanist at Dijon, later at Marseille.

name: Lorinser, Friedrich Wilhelm
description: Austrian (Bohemian-born) botanist and physician; "Landes-Sanitätsrath" and surgeon at the Wiedner hospital in Wien; brother of Gustav Lorinser

name: Lorinser, Gustav
description: Bohemian physician and botanist; Dr. med. Praha 1838; practicing physician at Mimon (Niemes) 1838-1850; high school teacher at Eg(g)er 18501852, at Bratislava 1852-1863.

page_title_longer_max-80: Lortet, Mme. Clémence, née Richard [std. C. Lortet]
name: Lortet, Mme. Clémence, née Richard
description: French botanist at Lyon; pupil and botanical companion of Gilibert, one of the founders of the Société linnéenne de Lyon.

name: Lortet, Louis-Charles
description: French physician, parasitologist and botanist at Lyon; grandson of Clémence Lortet; Dr. med. Paris 1861; Dr. sci. nat. Lyon 1867; lecturer medical school, 1867, professor ib. 1868; lecturer in zoology at the Factulté des Sciences 1869; director of the Muséum d'histoire naturelle de Lyon 1869; professor of zoology Faculté des Sciences 1874-1877; professor of natural history at the Faculté mixte de Medecine et de Pharmacie 1877-1906.

name: Loscos y Bernál, Francisco
description: Spanish pharmacist and botanist at Chiprana in Castelseras.

name: Lotsy, Johannes Paulus
description: Dutch botanist at Leiden, moving spirit behind the "Association internationale des botanistes;" Dr. phil. Göttingen 1890; lecturer at Johns Hopkins Univ. 1895; in Java 1895-1900; from 1904-1909 lecturer, from 1906-1909 director of the Rijksherbarium at Leiden; from 1909 working privately at Haarlem and Velp.

page_title_longer_max-80: Loudon, Jane Wells (née Webb) [std. J.W. Loud.]
name: Loudon, Jane Wells (née Webb)
description: British botanist and horticulturist; married (1830) John Claudius Loudon.

name: Loudon, John Claudius
description: British gardener, horticultural writer and botanist at Bayswater nr. London.

name: Louis-Marie, Père (Louis Lalonde)
description: French-Canadian botanist; entered Trappist order at Oka 1917; Ph. D. Harvard 1928; at the Institut agricole, Oka from 19231962.

name: Lounsberry, Alice
description: American dendrologist at New York.

name: Loureiro, João de
description: Portuguese missionary and naturalist in Moçambique, Goa, and Cochinchina.

name: Lousley, Job Edward
description: British botanist; employee of Barclays Bank.

name: Lovén, Fredrik August
description: Swedish botanist; Dr. phil. Lund 1874; with the Skogsinstitut (wood and forestry) 1875-1802, at Uddeholmsverken 1884-1908.

name: Lowe, Charles William
description: British-born botanist; M. Sc. Birmingham 1915; settled in Canada; lecturer at the University of Manitoba until 1931, professor until 1950, from then on in Victoria, Canada

name: Lowe, Edward Joseph
description: British botanist and meteorologist of independent means at Shirenewton Hall, near Chepstow; "passionately devoted to raising varieties of ferns from spores", prolific author during the Victorian fern craze.

name: Lowe, Ephraim Noble
description: American geologist and botanist; director of the State Geological Survey of Mississippi

name: Lowe, Josiah Lincoln
description: American lichenologist and mycologist at Syracuse; Ph. D. Mich. Univ. 1938; assistant botanist Syracuse 1933-1938; Instructor ib. 1938-1944; assistant professor ib. 1944-1947; associate professor 1947-1951; professor of forest botany 1952-1959; research prof. 1959.

name: Lowe, Richard Thomas
description: British clergyman and botanist; chaplain in Madeira 1832-1854; rector of Lea, Lincolnshire, ca. 1854; botanised in Orkney Isl., Canary Isl., Cape Verde Isl., Madeira, Marocco.

name: Lubbers, Louis
description: Belgian horticulturist; chef des cultures de Jardin botanique de l'État, Bruxelles 1870-1903; longtime secretary of the Société de Flore.

name: Lucae, August Friedrich Theodor
description: German pharmacist and botanist.

name: Lucand, Jean Louis
description: French soldier and botanist; army officer in the 29th infantry regiment 1842-1873; from 1874 retired at Autun.

page_title_longer_max-80: Lucas, Arthur Henry Shakespeare [std. A. Lucas]
name: Lucas, Arthur Henry Shakespeare
description: British-born Australian botanist and science master; at Wesley College, Melbourne 1883, at Stanmore, N.S.W. 1892, at Sydney 1899-1923.

page_title_longer_max-80: Lucé, Johann Wilhelm Ludwig von [std. Lucé]
name: Lucé, Johann Wilhelm Ludwig von
description: Estonian (Baltic German) botanist

name: Ludlow, Frank
description: British explorer of Bhutan, Tibet and the inner Himalaya.

name: Ludwig, Christian Friedrich
description: physician and botanist; professor of natural history and pathology at the University of Leipzig 1782-1823.

name: Ludwig, Christian Gottlieb
description: German physician and botanist at Leipzig.

name: Ludwig, Clinton Albert
description: American mycologist and phytopathologist; studied at Purdue University (M. Sc. 1914); Dr. phil. Univ. Mich. 1917; plant pathologist at the South Carolina Experiment Station, Clemson College until 1928; from then on plant pathologist with USDA, Washington, D. C.

name: Ludwig, Friedrich
description: German botanist; from 1875 teacher at the gymnasium of Greiz

page_title_longer_max-80: Ludwig, Rudolph August Birminhold Sebastian [std. R. Ludw.]

name: Meigen, Wilhelm
description: German high school teacher and botanist at Wesel.

page_title_long: Meijer, Frans Nicholaas (after 1908 Frank Nicholas Meyer)
page_title_longer_max-80: Meijer, Frans Nicholaas (after 1908 Frank Nicholas Meyer) [std. F.N. Meyer]
name: Meijer, Frans Nicholaas (after 1908 Frank Nicholas Meyer)
name_ed: Meijer, Frans Nicholaas (after 1908 Frank Nicholas Meyer)
description: Dutch botanist, gardener and botanical explorer; with Hugo de Vries before 1900; travelled through the United States and Mexico 1901-1904; at the Missouri Botanical Garden 1904-1905; with USDA as plant collector at the initiative of David Fairchild in 1905-1908, 1909-1912, 1913-1915 and 1916-1918; naturalised U.S. citizen 1908; drowned (murdered?) in the Yang-tsze-kiang.

page_title_longer_max-80: Meinecke, Emilio Pepe Michael [std. E. Meinecke]
name: Meinecke, Emilio Pepe Michael
description: California-born American botanist and phytopathologist of German descent; Ph. D. Heidelberg 1893; until 1907 at Heidelberg, Copenhagen and München; from 1907-1909 at La Plata, Argentina; U.S. Forest Service pathologist in California 1910-1928; id. in National Park Service 1928-1939.

name: Meinecke, Johann Ludwig Georg
description: German physicist and biologist; high school teacher at Halle 1805-1811; idem at Kassel 1811-1814; professor of technology at Halle 1814-1823

name: Meins, Claus
description: German theologist and botanist; high school teacher at the Glückstadt gymnasium 1848-1865; from 1865 clergyman at St. Margarethen.

name: Meinshausen, Karl [Friedrich]
description: Riga (Livonia)-born BalticGerman/Russian botanist at St. Petersburg; travelling for the botanical garden 1839-1844, curator of the garden herbarium until 1851; from 1851-1896 curator at the botanical museum of the Academy of Sciences

name: Meisel, Max
description: American bibliographer and historian of natural history; B.Sc. New York 1914, librarian at New York public library 1916-1917; at Battle Creek, Mich. 1917-1918, at Brooklyn 1918-?

name: Meisner, Carl Friedrich
description: Swiss botanist; Dr. med. Goettingen 1824; at Genève with A. P. de Candolle 1825-1828; professor of physiology Basel 1828-1836, professor of botany 1836-1867.

name: Meister, Friedrich
description: Swiss diatomologist; high school teacher at Horgen nr. Zürich.

name: Meister, Jakob
description: Swiss botanist and geologist; high school teacher at Zürich 1871-1880, at Schaffhausen 1880-1926.

name: Mejer, Ludwig
description: German botanist at Hannover.

page_title_long: Mela, Aukusti Juhana (until 1876 August Johan Malmberg)
page_title_longer_max-80: Mela, Aukusti Juhana (until 1876 August Johan Malmberg) [std. Mela]
name: Mela, Aukusti Juhana (until 1876 August Johan Malmberg)
name_ed: Mela, Aukusti Juhana (until 1876 August Johan Malmberg)
description: Finnish zoologist and botanist; high school teacher in Helsinki; active promoter of Finnish culture and language.

name: Melchior, Hans
description: German botanist; student of Engler; 1917 assistant with G. Haberlandt, Berlin; Dr. phil. Berlin 1920; at the Botanical Museum as Assistant 1920; Oberassistent 1929; Kustos 1932-1955; from 1940 professor; Wissenschaftlicher Oberrat 1955; kommissarischer Leiter 1958-1959.

name: Melén, Eric Gustaf
description: Swedish physician and botanist; student of C. P. Thunberg; Dr. med. Upsal. 1826; hospital physician at Kalmar 1826-1828

name: Melhus, Irving E.
description: American phytopathologist and pteridologist; B. Sc. Iowa State 1906, Ph. D. Madison 1912; plant pathologist in the Agricultural Experiment Station and Botany Dept. of Iowa State University 1912-1946; director of the Iowa State University Guatemala Tropical Research Center 1946-1953.

name: Melliss, John Charles
description: British botanist and commissioner of Crown property, surveyor on St. Helena ca. 1860-1891.

name: Melsheimer, Marcellus
description: German botanist and forester; studied at the Eisenach forestry college 1852-1854; from 1856-1896 Oberförster at Linz a. Rhein; in retirement ibid, until 1920.

name: Melvill, James Cosmo
description: British businessman and naturalist at Manchester; B. A. Cantab. 1868; D. Sc. Manchester 1908.

name: Melville, Ronald
description: British botanist; Cheshunt Exp. Sta. 1930-1933; at the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, from 1934; specialist on the Australasian flora and British Rosa.

name: Memminger, Edward Read
description: American botanist in North Carolina

name: Mendel, Gregor Johann
description: Czech geneticist, clergyman and teacher at Brno.

name: Mendonça, Francisco de Ascensão
description: Portuguese botanist; specialist on Capparidaceae and Malvaceae; travelled in Angola 1927, 1937, 1955, in Moçambique 1942- 1948.

name: Meneghini, Giuseppe Giovanni Antonio
description: Italian algologist and palaeobotanist; educated at University of Padua (M. D. 1834); assistant (1834-1839) and professor of botany 1834-1838 at Padua; id. of Science faculty 1838-1849; professor of physical geography and geology at Pisa 1849-1889.

name: Menezes (Meneses), Carlos Azevedo de
description: Portuguese botanist; municipal librarian at Funchal, Madeira.

name: Menge, Franz Anton
description: German high school teacher, palaeontologist, arachnologist and botanist; studied at Bonn 1828-1832; high school teacher at Graudenz 1833- 1836, and at the Petrischule, Danzig 1836-1877; specialist on amber fossils.

name: Mennega, Alberta Maria Wilhelmina
description: Dutch wood anatomist and plant systematist at the University of Utrecht; Dr. phil. Utrecht 1938.

name: Mentz, August
description: Danish botanist; Dr. phil. 1912; professor of botany at an agricultural college at Copenhagen from 1923-1931.

name: Menyhárth, Lászlò (Ladislav), S. J.
description: Austro-Hungarian missionary and botanist; originally at Innsbruck; later at Kalocsa; travelled in the Zambesi region.

name: Menzel, Paul Julius
description: German palaeontologist; Dr. med. Greifswald 1889; practicing physician at Heinitz-Grosspostritz, 1889-1898; id. at Dresden 1898-1914; id. in the German army 1914-1918; again at Dresden 1918-1927.

name: Menzies, Archibald
description: British physician, gardener, botanist, zoologist and plant collector; assistant-surgeon in the Royal Navy 1782; in N.W. America 1786-1789; with Capt. Vancouver on the Voyage of the Discovery and Chatham 1791-1795.

page_title_longer_max-80: Mérat de Vaumartoise, François Victor [std. Mérat]
name: Mérat de Vaumartoise, François Victor
description: French botanist and physician at Paris; Dr. méd. Paris 1803; at the Charité hospital 1803-1813; editor of the Dictionnaire des sciences médicales.

name: Mercier de Coppet, Elysée
description: Swiss botanist.

name: Mercier, Marie Philippe
description: French botanist, born on Martinique; soldier, police officer, salesman, refugee in Genève 1822-1831 working with A. P. de Candolle.

name: Mercklin, Carl Eugen [Eugeniewitsch] von
description: Livonian (Baltic-German) botanist and paleontologist; studied at Dorpat and Jena, Dr. phil. Jena 1846; from 18481855 plant physiologist at St. Petersburg; professor of forestry botany at St. Petersburg 1847-1865; professor of botany at the medical academy of St. Petersburg 1867.

page_title_longer_max-80: Meredith, Louisa Anne, née Twamley [std. Meredith]
name: Meredith, Louisa Anne, née Twamley
description: British botanical artist, bush naturalist, writer and poetess; settled in Australia 1839 (mainly N.S.W. and Tasmania)

page_title_longer_max-80: Mereschkowski, Konstantin Sergejewicz [pseudonym Kuno Mower] [std. Mereschk.]
name: Mereschkowski, Konstantin Sergejewicz [Mérejkovski, Constantin Sergeevic; pseudonym in Switzerland: Kuno Mower]
description: Russian algologist and liche- nologist from Kasan; later (from 1925) in exile in Switzerland.

name: Merino y Román, [Père] Baltasar
description: Spanish jesuit and botanist in Galicia.

name: Merker, Gustav
description: Bohemian botanist; teacher at the forestry college of Mährisch-Weisskirchen (Hranice, E. Bohemia)

name: Merklein, Friedrich
description: Swiss botanist at Schaffhausen.

page_title_longer_max-80: Merlet de la Boulaye, Gabriel-Eléonor [std. Merlet]
name: Merlet de la Boulaye, Gabriel-Eléonor
description: French botanist at Angers; director of the Angers botanical garden.

name: Merrem, Blasius
description: German botanist, mathematician and physicist; lecturer at Göttingen 1781-1784; professor of physics and political economy at Duisburg 1784-1804; from 1804-1821, professor of political economy and botany at Marburg.

name: Merriam, Clinton Hart
description: American botanist, zoologist and ethnologist; M. D Columbia 1879; practicing physician in Locust Grove 1879-1885; ornithologist in the office of the"Commissioner of agriculture" (now USDA) and leader of the Bureau of Biological Survey 1885-1910; working with the support of the Harnman Trust (Smithsonian Institution) from 1910; outstanding mammalogist and zoogeographer

name: Merrill, Elmer Drew
description: American botanist; in the Philippines 1902-1924; at Berkeley 1924-1930; director of the New York Botanical Garden 1930-1935 succeeding N. L. Britton; at Harvard 1935-1948 (retirement as Arnold Professor); active until 1954; outstanding plant systematist ("get-the-job-done").

name: Merrill, George Knox
description: American lichenologist, journalist and photographer; active at Rockland, Maine were he kept an art studio.

name: Merriman, Paul Rossiter
description: American botanist.

name: Mertens, Franz Karl (Carl)
description: German botanist, director of a business school in Bremen.

name: Mertens, Karl (Carl) Heinrich
description: German botanist at St. Petersburg; son of F. K. Mertens.

name: Meschinelli, Aloysius (Luigi)
description: Italian palaeomycologist; assistant in geology and palaeontology Univ. Napoli 1889-1890, president of the Comizio agrario di Vicenza 1904.

name: Metcalfe, Charles Russell
description: British botanist, especially plant anatomist.

name: Metsch, Johann Christian
description: German botanist; Dr. med. Berlin 1821; from 1822 public health officer at Suhl.

name: Mettenius, Georg Heinrich
description: German pteridologist; professor of botany and director of the Leipzig botanical garden from 1851-1866; succeeding Gustav Kunze; married Cecilie Braun, daughter of Alexander Braun; died of cholera.

name: Metz, Sister Mary Clare
description: American botanist and nun at the Congregation of the Sisters of Divine Providence San Antonio, Texas; Ph. D. Cathol. Univ. Amer. 1934; later at Our Lady of the Lake College.

name: Metzger, Johann
description: German botanist and gardener at Heidelberg; from 1851 director of the agricultural garden and college at Karlsruhe.

name: Metzler, Jakob Adolf ("H")
description: German banker, landowner and cryptogamist at Frankfurt a. M.

name: Meulenhoff, J. S.
description: Dutch mycologist; president of the Nederlandse mycologische Vereniging 1919-1933

name: Meunier, Alphonse F.
description: Belgian algologist.

name: Meurer, Franz Ferdinand
description: German lawyer, administrator, Regierungsrat, entomologist and botanist at Rudolstadt.

name: Meurer, Pfarrer
description: German clergyman and botanist; high school teacher at Rinteln.

name: Meurling, Petrus
description: Swedish physician.

name: Meusel, Hermann
description: German botanist at Halle; Dr. phil. Halle 1935 (student of W. Troll); assistant Bot. Inst. Halle 1935-1947; professor of botany ib. 1947 (ord. 1952); Nationalpreis DDR 1966; specially interested in the chorology of the eurasiatic flora.

name: Mexia, Ynes Enriquetta Julietta
description: American botanical explorer (of Mexican descent) of Alaska and Latin America.

name: Meyen, Franz Julius Ferdinand
description: Prussian physician and botanist; Dr. med. Berlin 1826; travelled around the world with W. Wendt on the Prinzess Luise (18301832); Dr. phil. h.c. Bonn 1834; professor of botany at the University of Berlin.

name: Meyer, Adolf
description: German botanist and pharmacist; Dr. phil. Heidelberg 1897.

name: Meyer, Albert
description: German botanist from Müllrose; Dr. phil. Marburg 1884.

name: Meyer, August
description: German botanist at Oldenburg.

name: Meyer, Bernhard
description: German botanist and ornithologist in the Wetterau; 1791-1796 practicing physician at Hanau; from 1796 pharmacist and dentist at Offenbach.

page_title_long: Meyer, Carl Anton von [Karl Anton; Carl Andreevic]
page_title_longer_max-80: Meyer, Carl Anton von [Karl Anton; Carl Andreevic] [std. C.A. Mey.]
name: Meyer, Carl Anton von [Karl Anton; Carl Andreevic]
name_ed: Meyer, Carl Anton von [Karl Anton; Carl Andreevic]
description: Russian botanist and explorer; studied at Dorpat, 1813-1814; in the Crimea 1818, in the Baltic area 18211824; in the Altai with Ledebour and Bunge 1826-1827; in the Caucasus 1829-1830; assistant (1832-1850) and director (1850-1855) of the botanical garden of St. Petersburg.

page_title_longer_max-80: Meyer, Ernst Heinrich Friedrich [std. E. Mey.]
name: Meyer, Ernst Heinrich Friedrich
description: Prussian botanist; Dr. med. Göttingen 1819; lecturer Göttingen 1819-1826; from 1826 professor of botany and director of the botanical garden in Königsberg; Dr. phil.h.c. Königsberg 1829.

page_title_longer_max-80: Meyer, Georg Friedrich Wilhelm [std. G. Mey.]
name: Meyer, Georg Friedrich Wilhelm
description: German botanist in Göttingen; from 1820 physiographer of the Kingdom of Hanover.

name: Meyer, J. C.
description: German botanist and pharmacist at Bayreuth.

name: Meyer-Abich, Adolf
description: German biologist, philosopher and historian of biology; Dr. phil Jena 1916; assistant librarian Univ. Göttingen 1917-1919, id. Kiel 1919-1921; librarian Univ. Hamburg 1921-1937 ("Bibliothekrat"), professor's title 1930; professor of philosophy Santiago, Chili 1929-1932; dir. Domin.-German Inst. Rep. Dominicana 19371939; from 1956 professor Univ. Hamburg.

name: Meylan, Charles
description: Swiss cryptogamist at Lausanne, high school teacher at La Chaux nr. Ste.-Croix (Lausanne) 1888-1923; Dr. sci.h.c. Lausanne 1922.

name: Meyran, Octave
description: French botanist at Lyon

name: Mez, Carl Christian
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Berlin 1888; habil. Breslau 1890; in München with Radlkofer 1888-1890; at the University of Breslau 1890-1899; 18991910 professor of botany at Halle; director of the Königsberg botanical garden 1910-1935, ultimately at Freiburg i.Br.; main promotor of serodiagnostics ("Königsberger Stamm- baum") in systematic botany.

name: Miall, Louis Compton
description: British botanist, entomologist, and palaeontologist; professor of biology at Yorkshire College of Science (Leeds University) 1876-1907.

name: Michael, Edmund
description: German mycologist.

name: Michael, Paul Oskar
description: German botanist from Oelsnitz i.V., Dr. phil. Leipzig 1885

name: Michalet, [Louis] Eugène
description: French botanist and magistrate at Besançon.

name: Michaux, André
description: French botanist and explorer of Iran (1782-1785), North America (1785-1796); later on a French exploring expedition (1800-1805) under Capt. Baudin as far as Madagascar, where he died.

name: Michaux, François-André
description: French botanist; son of André M., whom he accompanied to the United States 1785-1790; travelled again in the U.S. 1801-1803 and 1806-1807.

name: Michel, Etienne
description: French publisher and (in part) editor of the "Nouveau Duhamel"

name: Michel, Mathieu Joseph
description: Belgian self-taught botanist and workman at Fraipont; founder, 1876, of the "Société de Botanique de Fraipont et de Nessonvaux" consisting of workmen only.

name: Micheletti, Luigi
description: Italian army officer, lichenologist and general floristic botanist.

name: Micheli, Marc
description: Swiss botanist and landowner at Geneva; pupil of Hofmeister and Sachs; later collaborator of Alphonse de Candolle; burgomaster of Jussy; owner of the Jardin du Crest(Jussy), maintained as a private botanical garden for plant introduction and agricultural experiments.

page_title_longer_max-80: Micheli, Pier Antonio (Pietro Antonio) [std. P. Mich.]
name: Micheli, Pier' Antonio (Pietro Antonio)
description: Italian botanist, "oculatissimus Michelius" (L.), curator of the botanical garden of Firenze, "father of cryptogamy", founder of the Società botanica fiorentina; botanist to the grand duke of Tuscany.

name: Michelin, Jean-Louis Hardouin
description: French administrator; magistrate, palaeontologist and algologist; one of the founders of the Société géologique de France.

name: Michelis, Friedrich Bernard Ferdinand
description: German clergyman and botanist; priest at Albachten 1855-1864; subsequently professor of philosophy at the Braunsberg Lyceum.

name: Michener, Ezra
description: American physician, conchologist and botanist in Chester County, Pennsylvania; M. D. Univ. Penn. 1817.

name: Michot, Norbert Louis
description: Belgian botanist; educated at Thuin and Tournay; abbé at Mons from 1840; almoner of the Carmelites

page_title_long: Middendorff, Alexander Theodor von (Aleksandr Fedorovic Middendorf)
page_title_longer_max-80: Middendorff, Alexander Theodor von (Aleksandr Fedorovic) [std. Middend.]
name: Middendorff, Alexander Theodor von (Aleksandr Fedorovic Middendorf)
name_ed: Middendorff, Alexander Theodor von (Aleksandr Fedorovic Middendorf)
description: Russian biologist and explorer; Dr. med. Dorpat 1837; professor of zoology at Kiew 1839; to Siberia 1843-1844; at St. Petersburg 1845-1865; imperial counsel 1873.

name: Miège, Émile
description: French botanist; Dr. Sci. Paris 1910; agricultural botanist at the École nationale d'agriculture de Rennes.

name: Miégeville, Joseph
description: French clergyman, botanist and explorer of the Pyrenees.

name: Miers, John
description: British botanist and metallurgist; travelled in South America 1819-1838; later in London as private scientist.

name: Migout, Abel
description: French botanist; high school teacher at Moulins (Allier).

page_title_longer_max-80: Migula, Emil Friedrich August Walther [std. Mig.]
name: Migula, Emil Friedrich August Walther
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Breslau 1888; lecturer, from 1893 professor of botany at the Technical University of Karlsruhe (1888-1904) and at the Forestry School of Eisenach (1904-1915).

name: Mik, Josef
description: Moravian botanist and dipterologist; studied at the Olmütz gymnasium 1850-1857; at the University of Vienna 1857-1861; high school teacher at Görz 1861-1865 at Linz 1865-1867, at Freistadt 1867-1871; from 1871-1899 professor at the academic gymnasium in Wien and school inspector; Schulrath 1894; Franz Joseph Order 1899.

page_title_longer_max-80: Mikan, Johann Christian [std. J. C Mikan]
name: Mikan, Johann Christian
description: Bohemian (Czech) botanist and entomologist; Dr. med. Praha 1793; professor of natural history Praha 1800-1831; travelled in Brazil with Pohl 1817-1819.

name: Mikan, Joseph Gottfried
description: Bohemian (Czech) botanist at Praha; founder and director of the botanical garden in Smichow (Praha) 1775-1811; father of J. C. Mikan.

name: Miki, Shigeru
description: Japanese palaeobotanist and botanist at Kagawa and Osaka; described Metasequoia.

name: Mikutowicz, Johann Mattias
description: Baltic German botanist in Livonia.

name: Milani, Giovanni Battista
description: Italian botanist; high school teacher at the lyceum of Salerno, later id. at Avellino.

name: Mildbraed, Gottfried Wilhelm Johannes
description: German botanist of the Engler school (Dr. phil. Berlin 1904) at Berlin-Dahlem (1903-1953); explorer of tropical Africa (1907-1908, 1910-1912, 1913-1914, 1928); prisoner of war in France 1914-1919.

name: Milde, Carl August Julius
description: German high school teacher and botanist at Breslau; Dr. phil. Breslau (with Goeppert) 1850; from 1851 at the Realschule zum Grauen Kloster "zum heiligen Geist"; royal professor 1870; curator of the botanical Museum of the Schlesische Gesellschaft für vaterländische Cultur.

name: Miliarakis, Spyridon
description: Greek botanist; curator, from 1893 professor of botany, at the Botanical Museum of the University of Athens; director of the Botanical Garden of the University 1893-1917.

name: Militzer, Max
description: German botanist, trained to be Volksschullchrer; in French captivity in Marocco after the Marne battle; exchange prisoner of war in Switzerland 19161917; teacher at Langebrück 1917-1919, Marienberg 1919-1921, Bautzen (Lutherschule) 1921-1945; from 1951-1959 with the nature conservancy at Dresden.

name: Millais, John Guille
description: English naturalist, gardener, sportsman and popular writer on birds, hunting and cultivated plants; Victoria medal of honor, R. H. S. 1928.

name: Millardet, Pierre Marie Alexis
description: French cryptogamist; pupil of Montagne, Hofmeister, Sachs and de Bary; Dr. Sci. nat. Strasbourg 1869; professor of botany at Strasbourg (1869), Nancy (1872), Bordeaux (1876-1902); inventor of the Bordeaux mixture "bouillie bordelaise" and hybridiser of Vitis; resuscitated the French wine industry.

name: Miller, Elihu Sanford
description: American botanist and horticulturist; at Wading River, N.Y. 1848-1888, 1902-1904, at Floral Park 1883-1902.

name: Miller, John Frederick
description: British botanical artist; son of Johann Sebastian Müllier (Miller).

name: Miller, John
description: American botanist active in Erie County, Pennsylvania,

name: Miller, Philip
description: British gardener; superintendent of the Society of Apothecaries at Chelsea ("Chelsea Physick Garden") 1722-1770; "hortulanorum princeps."

name: Miller, Robert Barclay
description: American botanist and forester, MA Wabash 1906, MS Yale 1908, chief forester, Department of Conservation, Illinois.

name: Miller, Samuel A.
description: American politician and lawyer at Cincinnati; amateur geolist and palaeontologist.

name: Miller, William
description: British botanist and school-master.

name: Mills, Frederick William
description: British solicitor (until 1922) and diatomologist.

name: Millspaugh, Charles Frederick
description: American physician and botanist; M. D. New York Med. coll. 1881; practicing physician at Binghamton, N.Y. 1881-1890, and Waverly, N.Y. 1890-1891; professor of botany Univ. W. Virginia 1891-1894; from 1894 at Chicago (Field Museum, Chicago University Medical College).

name: Milne, Colin
description: British clergyman and botanist; rector of North Chapel, Petworth, Sussex; LL. D. h. c. Aberdeen

name: Milne-Edwards, Alphonse
description: French-born (English parents) palaeontologist, especially palaeo-ornithologist; Dr. med. Paris 1860; Dr. sci. id. 1861; aide-naturaliste Muséum 1862-1865; professor at the Paris School of Pharmacy 1865-1895; from 1876 in various functions again at the Muséum d'Histoire naturelle, Paris, director 1891-1900.

page_title_longer_max-80: Milne-Redhead, Edgar Wolston Bertram Handsley [std. Milne-Redh.]
name: Milne-Redhead, Edgar Wolston Bertram Handsley
description: British botanist; B. A. Cantab. 1928; at Kew (1929-1971).

page_title_long: Miltitz, Friedrich Joseph Franz Xaver von
page_title_longer_max-80: Miltitz, Friedrich Joseph Franz Xaver von [std. Miltitz]
name: Miltitz, Friedrich Joseph Franz Xaver von
name_ed: Miltitz, Friedrich Joseph Franz Xaver von
description: German botanical bibliographer at Dresden.

name: Minà-Palumbo, Francesco
description: Italian botanist and physician at Castelbuono.

name: Minden, Max D. von
description: German mycologist; assistant at the botanical institute Giessen 1898.

name: Miner, Harriet Stewart
description: American botanist.

name: Minio, Michelangelo
description: Italian cryptogamist and historian ofbotany

name: Minks, Arthur
description: German physician and lichenologist at Stettin.

name: Minuart, Juan
description: Spanish botanist and pharmacist; born in Barcelona; later in Madrid.

name: Miquel, Friedrich Anton Wilhelm
description: Dutch botanist; Dr. med. Groningen 1833; practicing physician and director of the Rotterdam botanical garden 1835-1846; professor of botany and director of the botanical garden Amsterdam 1846-1859; idem at Utrecht 1859-1871, from 1862 also director of the Leiden Rijksherbarium.

name: Miranda, González, Faustino

Madrid 1929; from 1933-1935 at the marine biological laboratory at Pontevedra, Spain; to Mexico 1939; naturalized 1941; director Instituto botánico de Chiapas at Tuxtla Gutiérrez 1949-1954, from 1941-1949 and from 1954 at the Instituto de Biologia, Mexico.

page_title_longer_max-80: Mirbel, Charles François Brisseau de [std. Mirb.]

description: French botanist; in Paris 17981806 at the Muséum; from 1802-1806 head-gardener at Malmaison; in Holland with Louis Napoléon 1806-1810; from 1829 again attached to the Muséum (1829 professeur de culture); mainly plant anatomist and physiologist.

name: Missbach, Ernst Robert
description: German botanist and teacher at Dresden, after his retirement curator of the botanical garden of the Landesverein Sächsischer Heimatschutz in Schellerhau; early promotor of school gardens.

name: Mitchell, John
description: Virginia-born British physician and botanist; physician at Urbanna, Virginia; 1735-1746, 1746-1768 in London.

page_title_longer_max-80: Mitchell, John (of Stanstead, Sussex) [std. J. Mitch. Stanst.]
name: Mitchell, John (of Stanstead, Sussex)
description: British land steward and botanist at Stanstead, Sussex and Keighley, Yorks.

page_title_longer_max-80: Mitchell, Sir Thomas Livingstone [std. T. Mitch.]
name: Mitchell, Sir Thomas Livingstone
description: Scottish-born soldier, explorer and botanist; deputy surveyor general New South Wales 1827, surveyor general 1828.

name: Mitscherlich, Gustav Alfred
description: German botanist at Berlin University.

name: Mitten, William
description: British pharmaceutical chemist and bryologist at Hurstpierpont Sussex.

name: Mix, Arthur Jackson
description: American mycologist, Ph. D. Cornell 1916; LL. D. h. c. Hamilton College 1953; at the University of Kansas from 1916; authority on Taphrina.

name: Miyabe, Kingo
description: Japanese botanist; D. Sc. Harvard 1889; at Hokkaido University, Sapporo and Tokyo, director of the Botanic garden of the Faculty of Agriculture 1884-1927.

name: Miyoshi, Manabu
description: Japanese botanist; studied with Pfeffer 1891-1895; Dr. Sc. Tokyo 1895; professor of botany at Tokyo University from 1895; director of the Botanic gardens of Tokyo Univ. 1922-1924.

page_title_long: Moçiño, José Mariano [Moziño Suarez de Figueroa]
page_title_longer_max-80: Moçiño, José Mariano [Moziño Suarez de Figueroa] [std. Moc.]
