name_ed: Moçiño, José Mariano [Moziño Suarez de Figueroa]
description: Mexican botanist, with Sessé on the Botanical Expedition to Nueva España 1795-1804.

name: Moe, Asche
description: Norwegian botanist at Stavanger.

name: Moe, Nils Green
description: Norwegian botanist; gardener at the University of Kristiania (Oslo).

name: Moebius, Martin August Johannes
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Heidelberg 1883, habil. 1887; at Heidelberg 1887-1893, from 1893-1933 librarian and botanist at the Forschungsinstitut Senckenberg, and director of the Senckenberg botanical garden (1893-1928), Frankfurt a.M.; professor of botany at Frankfurt 1914-1925; from 1939 at Homburg v.d. Höhe.

name: Möhring, Paul Heinrich Gerhard
description: East Frisian (German) botanist, ornithologist and physician; Dr. med. Wittemberg, practicing physician at Jever (Oldenburg).

page_title_longer_max-80: Möller, Friedrich Alfred Gustav Jobst (Alfred) [std. A. Möller]
name: Möller, Friedrich Alfred Gustav Jobst ("Alfred")
description: German (Prussian) forester and mycologist; pupil of O. Brefeld; Dr. phil. Eberswalde 1887; visited Brazil as diplomatic courier and "naturalista viajante do museu nacional" (Blumenau, Santa Catarina 1890-1893); later teacher (1899) and director (1906) of the forestry college at Eberswalde (Brandenburg).

name: Møller, Birgitte Christina
description: Danish botanist.

name: Möller, Hjalmar August
description: Swedish botanist; lecturer at a teachers college at Kalmar; from 1917 at the Riksmuseum, Stockholm.

name: Möller, Johann Diedrich
description: German (Holstein) botanical technician at Wedel, Holst., collaborator of P. T. Cleve.

page_title_longer_max-80: Möller, Ludwig Heinrich Ferdinand [std. L. Möller]
name: Möller, Ludwig Heinrich Ferdinand
description: German high school teacher and botanist at Mühlhausen in Thüringen.

name: Moench, Conrad
description: German botanist, chemist and pharmacist; Dr. med. Marburg 1781; pharmacist at Hannover (1764), Bern (1765-1768), Strassburg (17681770), Kassel (1770-1785); assessor and from 1781 professor of botany at the medical college of Kassel 1780-1785; professor of botany and in other functions at Marburg University 1785-1805.

name: Mönkemeyer, Wilhelm
description: German bryologist; "Garteninspektor" at Leipzig.

name: Moerch, Otto Josias Nicolai
description: Danish botanist, curator of the Copenhagen botanical garden

name: Mörner, Count Carl Thore
description: Swedish botanist; Dr. phil. Uppsala 1892; professor of medicine and physiological chemistry Uppsala 1894, ord. professor 1909.

name: Mössier, Johann Christoph
description: German teacher and botanist; in Hamburg 18041806.

name: Moesz, Gusztáv (Gustav von)
description: Hungarian botanist; high school teacher at Brassó, from 1906 id. at Budapest and specializing mainly on mycology; from 1910 curator, later director of BP.

name: Moffatt, Will (William) Sayer
description: American mycologist; MD Chicago 1868; practiced medicine at Wheaton, Ill., and Sycamore, Ill.; to Los Angeles 1926.

name: Moggridge, John Traherne
description: British botanist at Mentone.

name: Mohl, Hugo von
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Tübingen 1827; 1828-1831 physician at München; 1832 professor of physiology at Bern; 1835 professor of history at the University of Tübingen; outstanding plant anatomist and physiologist.

name: Mohler, J. C.
description: American botanist at Topeka, Kansas.

page_title_longer_max-80: Mohr, Charles Theodore (baptized Karl Theodor) [std. C. Mohr]
name: Mohr, Charles Theodore (baptized Karl Theodor)
description: German-born American botanist who studied at Stuttgart; collected in Suriname 1845-1846; emigrated to the United States 1848, joined the "forty-niners" in the gold-rush of 1859; spent a year in gold- mining in the Sacramento valley (Calif,); two years farming in Indiana; then at Louisville, Ala., and in Mexico; from 1857-1899 druggist at Mobile, Ala., 1899-1901 at Asheville, N. C.

page_title_longer_max-80: Mohr, Daniel Matthias Heinrich [std. D. Mohr]
name: Mohr, Daniel Matthias Heinrich
description: German botanist; from 1805 "Adjunct," from 1807 professor of philosophy at the University of Kiel.

name: Mohr, Nicolai (i Pedersen)
description: Faeroes-born Danish botanist; visited Iceland 1780, Groenland 1787; employed by the Royal Danish China factory.

name: Moisan, Charles Auguste
description: French botanist and pharmacist at Nantes.

name: Moldenhawer, Johann Jacob Paul
description: German botanist; born at Hamburg; professor of botany at Kiel University and director of the Düsternbrook forestry school

name: Moldenke, Charles Edward
description: German-born American clergyman, egyptologist and botanist; emigrated to U.S. in early youth; B. A. Columbia college 1879, M. A. id. 1883; Dr. phil Strasbourg 1886; ordained 7 Oct 1885; pastor at Jersey City 1885-1890; in New York City 1890-1896, at Mt. Vernon 1897-1909; retired 1909 to Watchung, N.J. to engage in travelling and private study.

name: Moldenke, Harold Norman
description: American botanist; Ph. D. Columbia 1934; curator at the New York Botanical Garden 1934-1951; son of C. E. Moldenke.

name: Molendo, Ludwig
description: German bryologist and journalist, editor of the Bayreuther Zeitung (1866-1868), Passauer Zeitung (1868-1875), Oberpfälzer Kurier (Regens- burg) 1875-1877; from 1877 of various journals in Bayreuth (1877-1878) and München.

page_title_longer_max-80: Molina, Giovanni Ignazio (orig. Juan Ignacio) [std. Molina]
name: Molina, Giovanni Ignazio (orig. Juan Ignacio)
description: Chilean jesuit priest, missionary, botanist and plant collector; to Italy 1768; professor of natural sciences Bologna 1774.

name: Molisch, Hans
description: Moravian (Austrian) botanist; Dr. phil. Wien 1879; habil. id. 1885; at the Pflanzenphysiol. Inst. Wien 1880-1889; at Graz and Praha 1889-1908; from 1909-1928 director of the Pflanzenphysiol. Inst. Wien.

name: Molkenboer, Julianus Hendrik
description: Dutch botanist; Dr. med. Leiden 1840; practicing physician at Leiden 1840-1854.

name: Moll, Jan Willem
description: Dutch phytographer; Dr. Phil. Leiden 1876; high school teacher at Utrecht 1876-1890; from then on professor of botany at Groningen and director of the botanical garden until 1917.

page_title_long: Moll, Karl Maria Ehrenbert, Freiherr von
page_title_longer_max-80: Moll, Karl Maria Ehrenbert, Freiherr von [std. K. Moll]
name: Moll, Karl Maria Ehrenbert, Freiherr von
name_ed: Moll, Karl Maria Ehrenbert, Freiherr von
description: German scientist, director of the mathematical-physical class of the Kgl. bayerische Akademie der Wissenschaften at München.

name: Molon, Francesco
description: Italian palaeobotanist at Vicenza

name: Moloney, Sir Cornelius Alfred
description: British colonial administrator in W. Africa from 1867; governor of Lagos 1887-1891; in the West Indies 1891-1904.

name: Monckton, Horace Woollaston
description: British barrister, botanist and geologist in Berkshire; treasurer of the Linnean Society 1905-1930.

name: Monguillon, Eugène Louis Honoré
description: French teacher and cryptogamist; at various schools in the département Sarthe; after 1923 retired at Mans.

name: Monnard, Jean Pierre
description: Swiss botanist and high school teacher at Nyon.

name: Monnet, Paul-Louis
description: French botanist, consul-general of France in San Francisco 1912; died on the battle fields of France in World War I.

name: Monnier, Auguste.
description: French botanist at Nancy.

name: Monroe, Charles Edwin
description: American botanist, LL.B. Univ. Mich. 1880; lawyer at Elyria (1880-1881), Washington, D.C. 1881-1884 and Madison, Wisconsin 18841930; at Oberlin 1930-1931.

page_title_longer_max-80: Montagne, Jean Pierre François Camille [std. Mont.]
name: Montagne, Jean Pierre François Camille
description: French crytogamist; military physician 1815-1830; afterwards private scientist at Paris.

name: Montandon, F.Jules
description: French botanist and physician in the Jura.

name: Monti, Gaetano Lorenzo
description: Italian botanist; professor of botany and director (1760-1792) of the botanical garden at Bologna.

name: Montin, Lars Jonasson
description: Swedish botanist; pupil of Linnaeus; physician at Lund 1751; regional physician in Halland 1782.

name: Montrouzier, Rev. Père Xavier
description: French botanist and apostolical missionary of the Society of Mary; "Christianae fidei inter paganus oceaniae (Nova Caledonia etc.) interpres" 1846-1897 (Wittrock).

name: Moody, Sophy
description: British author.

name: Moon, Alexander
description: Scottish botanist and gardener for Kew, collected at Gibraltar and N. Africa (Barbary), superintendent of the royal botanic gardens in Ceylon (1817- 1825).

name: Moore, Albert Hanford
description: American botanist; AM Harvard 1906; worked at the Arnold Arboretum, Smithsonian Institution, USDA and with the United Fruit Co.

name: Moore, Charles
description: Scottish-born Australian botanist; director of the Botanical Garden at Sydney (1848-1896); younger brother of David Moore.

name: Moore, David (until 1828: Muir)
description: Scottish botanist; brother of Charles Moore; at Trinity College Garden Dublin 1829-1834; botanist to Ordnance survey of Ireland 1834-1838; curator of Glasnevin Garden 1838-1879; Dr. phil. h.c. Zürich 1863.

name: Moore, George Thomas
description: American algologist; Ph. D. Harvard 1900; plant physiologist at Washington Univ. 1909-1912; director of the Missouri Botanical Garden 1912-1953

name: Moore, John William
description: American botanist; Ph. D. Univ. Minnesota 1933, on Raiatea Island 1926-1927.

name: Moore, Lucy Beatrice
description: New Zealand botanist; M. Sc. Auckland 1929; at the Botany Division, Dept. Scientific and Industrial Research, Wellington.

page_title_longer_max-80: Moore, Spencer Le Marchant [std. S. Moore]
name: Moore, Spencer Le Marchant
description: British botanist and explorer; B. Sc. London 1872; at Kew 1872-1879; to Matto Grosso 1891-1892; to Western Australia 1894-1896; from 1898 connected with BMNH.

name: Moore, Thomas
description: British botanist and gardener; curator of the Chelsea botanic garden (1848-1887); assistant, later co-editor of Gardeners Chronicle (1841-1881) and of several other gardening magazines.

page_title_longer_max-80: Moquin-Tandon, Christian Horace Bénédict Alfred [std. Moq.]
name: Moquin-Tandon, Christian Horace Bénédict Alfred
description: French naturalist and botanist; pupil of A. P. de Candolle; Dr. Sci. Montpellier 1826, high school teacher at Marseille 1829-1833; director of the botanic garden of Toulouse 1834-1853; subsequently professor of botany at the Faculté de Médecine, Paris; best known for his work on teratology; one of the founders of the Société botanique de France.

name: Morandi, Giambattista (Giovanni Battista)
description: Italian medical botanist and artist at Milano.

name: More, Alexander Goodman
description: British botanist, entomologist, and ornithologist; assistant, later curator of the Natural History museum, Dublin (1867-1887).

name: Moreau, Fernand
description: French mycologist and lichenologist; Dr. Sci. Paris 1913; at Clermond Ferrand (Faculty of Sciences) and director of the biological station at Besse, Puy-de-Dôme; from 1936 director of the Jardin botanique de la ville de Caen.

page_title_longer_max-80: Morel, J. F. Nicolas [std. J.F.N. Morel]
name: Morel, J. F. Nicolas
description: French botanist at Besançon.

name: Morel, Jean-Marie
description: French landscape architect and horticulturist at Lyon.

name: Morel, L. F.
description: French clergyman, high school teacher and mycologist.

name: Moretti, Giuseppe
description: Italian botanist; professor of botany and director of the Botanical Garden at the University of Pavia 1826-1853.

name: Morgan, Andrew Price
description: American mycologist who introduced C. G. Lloyd to mycology; high school teacher at Dayton, Ohio.

name: Morgan, Robert
description: British artist and lithographer; contributed plates to e.g. J. Bot. 1882-1900; illustrated Fryer's Potamogeton.

name: Morgenroth, Eduard
description: German palaeobotanist; Dr. phil. Leipzig 1883; ultimately "Oberstudienrat" in Berlin

name: Mori, Antonio
description: Italian botanist; acting director botanical garden of Pisa 1880-1881; director of the botanical garden of Alodena (1883-1902), professor of botany from 1888.

name: Mori, Tamezô
description: Japanese botanist; AB Tokyo 1909; teacher in Korea from 1909.

name: Moriarty, Henrietta Maria, Mrs,
description: British novelist.

page_title_longer_max-80: Moricand, Moïse Étienne, called Stefano [std. Moric.]
name: Moricand, Moïse Étienne, called Stefano
description: Swiss botanist; commercial traveller in Italy for the Swiss watch industry; later in Genève working (in his spare time) with A. P. de Candolle.

page_title_longer_max-80: Morière, Pierre Gilles, calles Jules [std. Morière]
name: Morière, Pierre Gilles, calles Jules
description: French botanist and palaeontologist; high school teacher at Condé-sur-Noireau 1837-1838, at Caen from 1838-1859; director Jardin botanique de la ville de Caen (1859-1871); professor of botany at the Faculté des Sciences de Caen from 1859; longtime secretary of the Société Linnéenne de Normandie (c. 1859-1888); Dr. sci. Lyon 1859.

page_title_longer_max-80: Morin, François Malat Marie [std. F. Morin]
name: Morin, François Malat Marie
description: French clergyman and botanist; Dr. Sci. Rennes 1893; high school teacher at Dinan; from 1895-1897 professor of botany at the free University of Lyon.

name: Morini, Fausto
description: Italian mycologist; originally at Bologna; director of the botanical garden and professor of botany at Sassari 1888-1892; idem at Messina 1892-1897; professor of botany and director of the R. Istituto ed Orto Botanico at Bologna, succeeding Mattirolo, 1897-1927.

name: Moris, Giuseppe Giacinto Joseph Hyacinthe)
description: Italian botanist; from 1822-1829 at the University of Cagliari; from 1829 professor of botany at Torino; director botanical garden ib. 1831-1869.

name: Morison, Robert
description: British botanist; in France at Angers and Blois 1640-1660; in London 1660; at Oxford (first professor of botany) 1669. "Morisonus est Fructista cum Physiognomis & Corollistis conspirans" (Linnaeus, Phil. bot. 18. 1751)

name: Moritz, Johann Wilhelm Karl
description: German botanical explorer of the West Indies (1831-1835); lived in Venezuela 1835-1837, 1840-1866.

name: Moritzi, Alexander
description: Swiss botanist; worked for some time with A. P. de Candolle in Genève, afterwards high school teacher at Solothurn.

name: Morong, Thomas
description: American congregational clergyman and botanist; resigned his pastoral charge in 1888; collected in Paraguay 1888-1890 and in Chile; specialist on Potamogeton; curator of the Columbia College herbarium in New York 1890-1894.

page_title_longer_max-80: Morot, Louis René Marie François [std. Morot]
name: Morot, Louis René Marie François
description: French botanist and editor; préparateur at the École des Hautes Études, Paris 1883; Dr. sci. Paris 1885; assistant at the Muséum d'Histoire naturelle 1889.

page_title_longer_max-80: Morren, Charles François Antoine [std. C. Morr.]
name: Morren, Charles François Antoine
description: Belgian botanist and horticulturist; born at Gent; studied natural sciences at Gent University; Dr. phil. ib. 1829; teacher physics at a secondary school until 1835, from then on professor of botany at Liège; director of the Jardin botanique de l'Université de Liège 1855-1856.

page_title_longer_max-80: Morren, Charles Jacques Édouard [std. E. Morr.]
name: Morren, Charles Jacques Édouard
description: Belgian botanist; professor of botany and director of the botanical garden at Liège 1857-1886; Dr. sci. Liège 1855; Dr. spéc. sci. bot. Gent 1858; son of C. F. A. Morren; specialist on Bromeliaceae.

name: Morris, (Sir) Daniel
description: British botanist, administrator and tropical agriculturist; D. Sc. Dublin; at the Botanic Gardens, Peredeniya, Ceylon 1877-1879; dir. public gardens Jamaica 1879-1886; assistant director Kew 1886-1898; imperial commissioner of agriculture, West Indies 1898-1908.

name: Morris, Edward Lyman
description: American botanist; M. A.Amherst 1895; instructor in botany at Amherst, Mass. 1893-1895; at Western High School, Washington, D. C. 1895-1896; head of the dept. of biology in the Washington high schools from 1896-1907; curator of natural sciences Brooklyn Institute of Arts 1907-1913; expert on Plantaginaceae.

name: Morris, George Edward
description: British-born American mycologist; drawingmaster in the public schools of Waltham, Mass.

name: Morris, John
description: British geologist and palaeontologist; pharmaceutical chemist in Kensington until 1855; with Roderick Murchison on geological tours in Europe 18531855; from 1855-1877 professor of geology at University College, London.

name: Morris, Patrick Francis
description: Australian botanist; from 1913-1961 at the National Herbarium of Victoria at Melbourne.

name: Morris, Richard
description: British surveyor, landscape gardener and planter.

name: Morrison, Alexander
description: Scottish physician and botanist; to Australia 1877; practiced in Melbourne, travelled in the New Hebrides 1892; West Australian Government botanist in the Bureau of Agriculture 1897-1906.

name: Morse, Elizabeth Eaton
description: American Wellesley trained (School of Art 1891) art teacher (1891-1924), re-entered Wellesley 1924, B.A. 1926; subsequently with Lee Bonar at the University of California, Berkeley specializing in fleshy fungi of the Pacific Coast; sometimes temporarily working at the Farlow Herbarium; but in general living at Berkeley 1926-1955.

name: Mortensen, Hans
description: Danish botanist; teacher at Naesgaard Agricultural College, 1849-1853; at Jonstrup training school from 1856-1896.

name: Mortensen, Morten Larsen
description: Danish botanist and phytopathologist.

name: Morthier, Paul
description: Swiss botanist at Neuchâtel (Corcelles), director of the Société helvétique pour l'échange des plantes.

name: Morton, Conrad Vernon
description: American botanist; AB, Univ. Calif., 1928; at the Smithsonian Institution (1928-1972), specialist on pteridophytes, Gesneriaceae and Solanaceae.

name: Morton, Friedrich [von]
description: Austrian botanist; Dr. phil. Wien 1916; high school teacher at Wien; from 1925 curator at the Botanical Station of Hallstatt.

name: Moruzi, Constance
description: Roumanian mycologist and lichenologist; Dr. Sci. Paris 1932; active at the University, the Agronomical Institute and the Pedagogical Institute in Bucarest.

name: Moscoso Puello, Rafael M.
description: Dominican physician and amateur botanist; teacher at various high schools and teachers' colleges, serving also in administrative functions; first director of the Instituto de Botanica of the Universidad de Santo Domingo 1941; Dr. h.c. 1944.

name: Moseley, Edwin Lincoln
description: American botanist and teacher at Sandusky high school, Ohio.

name: Moseley, Henry Nottidge
description: British naturalist on the Challenger expedition 1873-1876; travelled in the American Northwest in 1877; ultimately Linacre professor of human and comparative anatomy at Oxford (1881-1887).

name: Mosén, Carl Wilhelm Hjalmar
description: Swedish botanist; Dr. phil. Uppsala 1875; collector on Regnell's expedition (1873-1876), curator of the Brazilian collections of the Stockholm Riksmuseum 1872-1873, 1876-1883.

name: Moser, Heinrich Christoph
description: German botanist

name: Moss, Charles Edward
description: British botanist; studied at Leeds 1895-1900 (B. Sc. 1898); high school teacher at Bruton and Manchester; from 1907-1914 curator of the Cambridge Herbarium (CGE); served in the O.T.C. 1914-1917; from 1917 professor of botany at Witwatersrand University.

name: Moss, Ezra Henry
description: Canadian botanist; Dr. phil. Toronto 1925; at the Department of Botany of the University of Alberta, 1929 (from 1938 as full professor)-1957; student of the vegetation of Alberta.

name: Mosseray, Raoul
description: Belgian botanist and high school teacher; studied at the teachers' college of Carlsbourg; Ing. agron. Louvain 1930, Dr. sci. nat. ib. 1931; died on the battlefield in 1940.

name: Motelay, Léonce
description: French shopkeeper and botanist at Bordeaux; active in the Société Linnéenne de Bordeaux.

name: Motley, James
description: British civil engineer and botanist; collected in Malaysia 18521853; later at Borneo; murdered at Kampong Kalangan (Bandjermasin).

name: Mott, Frederick Thompson
description: British botanist; wine merchant at Leicester.

name: Motte, Jean
description: French botanist at Montpellier.

name: Mottet, Séraphin Joseph
description: Freneh horticulturist; chef des cultures expérimentales de la Maison Vilmorin-Andrieux et Cie.

name: Motyka, Józef
description: Polish botanist (lichenologist); Dr. phil. 1925; professor of botany at the University of Lublin.

name: Mougeot, (Joseph) Antoine
description: French physician and botanist at Bruyères; son of Jean Baptiste Mougeot; studied medicine at Strasbourg (M. D. 1837); mayor of Bruyères 1854-1855, 1861-1868, 1871-1876; member and president of the Conseil général des Vosges (1859-1879).

name: Mougeot, Jean Baptiste
description: Alsatian physician and botanist; 1798-1802 French army health officer in Germany; from 1803 physician at Bruyères; 1833-1858 member of the Conseil général des Vosges.

name: Mouillefert, Pierre
description: French dendrologist, "professeur de sylviculture à l'École nationale d'Agriculture de Grignon."

name: Mounce, Irene (Stewart)
description: Canadian mycologist and phytopathologist; M. S. Univ. Manitoba 1922, Ph. D. Toronto 1929; at Ottawa 1924-1938, at Saanichton, D. C. 1938-1945

name: Mouret, Marcellin
description: French soldier and botanist; in the 3rd colonial infantry in Martinique, Tonkin and Marocco; died at Argonne on the battle fields of World War I.

name: Mousnier, Jules
description: French pharmacist born at Saujon (Charente-Inférieure); Dr. pharm. Paris 1873.

name: Mouterde, Paul
description: French jesuit and botanist; from 1929 at the Université Saint-Joseph at Beyrouth; botanical explorer of Syria and Lebanon; specialist in the syrian, coptic, greek and hebrew languages.

name: Mouton, Victor
description: Belgian mycologist at Liège.

page_title_long: Mouton-Fontenille de la Clotte, Marie Jacques Philippe
page_title_longer_max-80: Mouton-Fontenille de la Clotte, Marie Jacques Philippe [std. Mouton-Font.]
name: Mouton-Fontenille de la Clotte, Marie Jacques Philippe
name_ed: Mouton-Fontenille de la Clotte, Marie Jacques Philippe
description: French botanist and ornithologist; studied at Montpellier under Gouan; from 1808-1815 professor of natural history at the faculty of sciences at Lyon; from 1815-1830 at the Lyon Palais des Arts and director of the natural history cabinet at Lyon; pensioned off in 1830 because of his ultra-royalist attitude.

name: Moxley, George Loucks
description: American botanist, methodist missionary in Liberia 1896-1897; in Southern California from 1898.

name: Moyen, J.
description: French clergyman and botanist; spent some time in Canada; later "Prêtre de Saint-Sulpice, Professeur d'Histoire naturelle à la Maison d'Alix" (Lyon).

name: Moyer, Isaac Shoemaker
description: American physician and botanist; studied at Pennsylvania Medical College, grad. 1859; practiced in Quakertown, Pennsylvania.

name: Mudd, William (A.)
description: British gardener and lichenologist; at first at Great Ayton, Cumb.; later (1865) curator of the Cambridge botanic garden.

name: Mudie, Robert
description: British journalist and popular writer on natural history; 1802-1808 teacher in Scotland; to London 1808 as reporter with the Morning Chronicle and editor of the Sunday Times.

name: Mühlberg, Friedrich ("Fritz")
description: Swiss botanist and geologist; studied at Zürich; high school teacher at Zug (Aargau) 1862-1865; from 1865-1911 id. in Aarau; Dr. phil. h.c. Basel 1888.

name: Mühlenbach, Viktor
description: Latvian bacteriologist, physician and botanist; Dr. Med. Riga of Dorpat 1933; habil. Riga 1936; emigrated to the U.S.A 1951; from 1953 associated with the Missouri Botanical Garden and actively interested in the adventive flora of St. Louis.

name: Muehlenbeck, Heinrich Gustav
description: Alsatian botanist and physician; Dr. med. Paris; practicing physician in Gebweiler 1822-1833; from then on at Mulhouse (Mühlhausen); friend of W. P. Schimper.

name: Mueller, Anton
description: Moravian naturalist; educated at the Gymnasium of Brünn (Brno); administrator in the "Kreisamt" Brünn until 1858.

page_title_longer_max-80: Müller, E. G. Otto [std. E.G.O. Müll.]
name: Müller, E. G. Otto
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Breslau 1886; contributed to "Engler and Prantl."

page_title_long: Mueller, Sir Ferdinand Jacob Heinrich (Baron) von
page_title_longer_max-80: Mueller, Sir Ferdinand Jacob Heinrich (Baron) von [std. F. v. Muell.]
name: Mueller, Sir Ferdinand Jacob Heinrich ("Baron") von
name_ed: Mueller, Sir Ferdinand Jacob Heinrich (Baron) von
description: Australian botanist of German birth; studied pharmacy at Kiel; to Australia for health purposes 1847; assistant pharmacist at Adelaide 1847-1853; from 1857-1896 Government botanist of Victoria; 1857-1873 director of the Melbourne botanical garden; title of Freiherr (Baron) from the king of Württemberg; leading Australian botanist and botanical explorer.

name: Müller, Franz August ["Friedrich"]
description: German pharmacist and plant collector; travelled for the Württembergische Reiseverein (Esslingen) in Algeria, Austro- Hungary and Sardinia (1826-1828); ultimately from 1831-1867 pharmacist at Schneeberg (Erzgebirge) in Sachsen.

page_title_longer_max-80: Müller, Fritz [Johann Friedrich Theodor] [std. Fritz Müll.]
name: Müller, Fritz [Johann Friedrich Theodor]
description: German zoologist and flower biologist; studied at Berlin and Greifswald; Dr. phil. Berlin 1844; studied medicine at Greifswald 1845-1848; to Brazil 1852 as farmer and physician in the primeval forest of Santa Catharina (Rio Garcia); from 1856-1857 high school teacher at Desterro; from 18671897 at Blumenau as private scientist and (1867-1891) "naturalista viajante" for the Brazilian government.

page_title_long: Müller, Heinrich Ludwig Hermann [Hermann Müller von Lippstadt]
page_title_longer_max-80: Müller, Heinrich Ludwig Hermann [Hermann Müller von Lippstadt] [std. H. Müll.]
name: Müller, Heinrich Ludwig Hermann ["Hermann Müller von Lippstadt"]
name_ed: Müller, Heinrich Ludwig Hermann [Hermann Müller von Lippstadt]
description: German bryologist, pollination biologist; studied at Erfurt and Berlin, examen profac. doc. Berlin 1852; from 1855-1883 high school teacher at Lippstadt; brother of Fritz Müller.

name: Müller, (Thurgau), Herman
description: Swiss botanist; director of the plantphysiological experiment station of the Kgl. Anstalt für Obst- und Weinbau, Geisenheim; involved in the improvement and phytopathology of grape cultivars; from 1891 director of the Versuchsstation und Schule für Obst-, Wein- und Gartenbau at Wädenswyl nr Zürich.

page_title_longer_max-80: Mueller [called] Argoviensis [of Aargau], Johannes [Jean] [std. Müll. Arg.]
name: Mueller [called] Argoviensis [of Aargau], Johannes [Jean]
description: Swiss botanist; studied at Zürich (Dr. phil., 1857); curator of the Candolle herbarium 1851-1869, of the Delessert herbarium (at Genève) 1869-1896; director of the Genève botanic garden 1870-1874; professor of botany 1871-1889.

name: Mueller, Jean Baptiste [Baptista]
description: German pharmacist and botanist at Mesebach, Emmerich and Berlin

name: Müller, Johannes
description: German botanist, born at Aurich, Ostfriesland; Dr. phil. Berlin 1893.

name: Mueller, Johann Sebastian
description: German botanical artist who settled in London (1744) and afterwards called himself John Miller.

name: Mueller, Joseph M.
description: German botanist and high school teacher at Aachen (Aix-la-Chapelle).

name: Müller, J. P.
description: German botanist; high school teacher at Remscheid; later at the German school in Antwerpen.

name: Mueller, Karl ("Carl")
description: German botanist; continued the publication of Walpers Annales.

name: Müller, Karl
description: of Freiburg, German hepaticologist; Dr. phil. Freiburg 1905; from 1905-1921 at the phytopathological station Augustenberg nr. Karlsruhe and as phytopathologist involved in the wine industry; from 1921-1937 director of the Badische Weinbauinstitut; from 1937-1955 working full time on hepaticology.

page_title_longer_max-80: Müller, Karl (recte Carl) Alfred Ernst [std. K.A.E. Müll.]
name: Müller, Karl (recte: "Carl") Alfred Ernst
description: German botanist, mainly plant physiologist; Dr. phil. Berl. 1883; from 1886-1895 at Pringsheim's plant-physiological institute; from 1895 at the Technische Hochschule Berlin (Charlottenburg); from 1896 as professor; from 1886 also part time and from 1903 fully paid by the Gärtnerlehranstalt at Dahlem while remaining associated with the Technische Hochschule.

page_title_longer_max-80: Müller, Johann Karl [Carl] August [Friedrich Wilhelm] [std. K. Müll. hal.]
name: Müller, Johann Karl [Carl] August [Friedrich Wilhelm]
description: German bryologist at Halle; practicing pharmacist in various parts of Germany until 1843; from then on at Halle, associated with D. F. L. von Schlechtendal, but essentially a self-made scientist.

page_title_longer_max-80: Mueller, Nicolaus Jacob Carl [std. N.J.C. Muell.]
name: Mueller, Nicolaus Jacob Carl
description: German plant physiologist and morphologist; Dr. phil. Heidelberg 1866; from 1866-1872 Privat-Dozent at Heidelberg; from 1872- 1901 at the Forestry College of Münden (Hannover).

name: Müller, [Georg Ferdinand] Otto ["Otto"]
description: German diatomologist; book publisher in Berlin 1862-1901; Dr. h.c. Berlin 1897.

page_title_longer_max-80: Müller, Otto Friedrich [Frederik, Friderich, Fridrich] [std. O.F. Müll.]
name: Müller, Otto Friedrich [Frederik, Friderich, Fridrich]
description: Danish botanist, zoologist, theologian and linguist; cand. jur. Copenhagen 1760; private tutor to Sigismund Schulin at Frederiksdal; from 1771-1773 secretary to the Danish ministry for Norway; from 1773 financially independent by marriage and devoting himself exclusively to science; one of the editors of Flora danica.

page_title_longer_max-80: Müller, Philipp Jakob (Muller, Philippe Jacques) [std. P.J. Müll.]
name: Müller, Philipp Jakob (Muller, Philippe Jacques)
description: Alsatian botanist (batologist) at Weissenburg am Rhein (Wissembourg); from 1872 with French nationality at Nyon (Waadt).

name: Müller, Theodor
description: German lichenologist; war-invalid World War I; working on the lichens of the Eiffel at Klein Vernich.

name: Müller, Walther Otto
description: German gardener and cryptogamist at Gera (Thüringen).

name: Mueller, Wilhelm
description: German botanist and high school teacher at Stettin.

name: Münch, Ernst
description: German forest botanist and phytopathologist; Dr. phil. München 1909; at the München Forestry Institute 1904-1914; at the Berlin Biological Institute for Agriculture and Forestry 1914-1921; Professor of forestry botany at the Forestry College of Tharandt 1921-1933; at the Staatswirtschaftliche Fakultät Munchen 1933-1946.

name: Münchhausen, Otto, Freiherr von
description: German "Landdrost" (sheriff) at Hannover and Schwölbern where he created a large Landschaftspark.

name: Muenscher, Walter Leopold Conrad
description: German-born American botanist; naturalized 1899; Ph. D. Cornell University 1921; teaching botany at Cornell 1916-1954.

page_title_longer_max-80: Münster, Georg Graf zu [std. G. Münster]
name: Münster, Georg Graf zu
description: German financial administrator and palaeontologist at Bayreuth.

page_title_long: Münter, Johann Andreas Heinrich August Julius
page_title_longer_max-80: Münter, Johann Andreas Heinrich August Julius [std. Münter]
name: Münter, Johann Andreas Heinrich August Julius
name_ed: Münter, Johann Andreas Heinrich August Julius
description: German botanist; Dr. med. Berlin 1841; physician at the Charité, Berlin 1845-1848; habil. Berlin 1848; from 1849 (extra ord.), 1851 (ordinary); later professor of botany and zoology at Greifswald; Geh. Regierungsrath 1884; published mainly on plant physiology

page_title_longer_max-80: Muhlenberg, Rev. Gotthilf Henry Ernest [std. Muhl.]
name: Muhlenberg, Rev. Gotthilf Henry Ernest
description: (Mühlenberg), American botanist, native of Pennsylvania; educated in Germany (1763-1770), Lutheran clergyman at Lancaster, Pa. 1780-1815.

name: Muir, John
description: Scottish-born American conservationist, botanist and explorer of California and Alaska.

name: Mulder, Nicolaas "Claas"
description: Dutch botanist; Dr. med. Leiden 1818; practicing physician at Makkum 1818-1822; professor of botany, chemistry and pharmacy at the Franeker Athenaeum 1822-1841; professor of chemistry at Groningen 1841-1852, id. natural history 1852-1866.

page_title_longer_max-80: Muller [before 1937 Mueller], Cornelius Herman [std. C. Mull.]
name: Muller [before 1937: Mueller], Cornelius Herman
description: American ecologist and botanist at the University of Texas and later at Santa Barbara; A.M. Univ. Texas 1933; specialist on Quercus

name: Muller, (Pierre) Félix (Müller)
description: Belgian botanist.

name: Munby, Giles
description: British botanist; studied at Edinburgh and in Paris (under Adrien de Jussieu); in Algeria 1839-1861.

name: Mundkur, Bhalchendra Bhavanishankar
description: Indian botanist; Ph. D. Iowa State 1930; mycologist with the Imperial Institute of Agricultural Research, Pusa, later deputy plant protection adviser, ministry of agriculture, India; ultimately at Poona.

name: Munro, Sir William
description: British botanist in the Indian colonial army; collected in Barbados (1870-1875), Crimea and India

name: Munson, Thomas Volney
description: American grape breeder at Denison, Texas

name: Munting, Abraham
description: Dutch botanist, professor of medicine at Groningen, 1658-1683.

name: Munz, Philip Alexander
description: American botanist in Southern California, longtime director of the Santa Ana Botanic Garden; Dr. phil. Cornell 1917; professor of botany at Pomona College 1917-1944; id. Cornell University 1944-1946; botanist and director of the Rancho Santa Ana Botanic Garden from 1946

name: Murbeck, Svante Samuel
description: Swedish botanist; Dr. phil. Lund 1891; lecturer in botany at Lund 1891-1892; curator at Riksmuseum Stockholm 1892-1893, teacher at Alnarps agricultural College 1897-1902; professor of botany at Lund 1902-1924; discovered parthenogenesis in Alchemilla; botanical explorer of the Mediterranean, specialist on Verbascum.

name: Murchison, Roderick Impey
description: British palaeontologist; director of the British geological survey.

name: Murillo, Adolfo
description: Chilean botanist and physician; professor of gynecology at the University of Santiago

name: Murith, Laurent Joseph
description: Swiss clergyman and botanist in Wallis (Valais), "chanoine regulier du St. Bernard, prieur de Martigni." ordained 1766, curate at Liddes 1778, prior of Martigny 1791.

name: Murphy, Edmund
description: Irish horticulturist and botanist; professor of horticulture, Queen's College, York 1849.

name: Murr, Josef
description: Austrian botanist and high school teacher at Hall (1888-1890), Innsbruck (1890-1891), Marburg (1891-1894). Linz (1894-1897), Trient (1897-1906), Feldkirch (1906-1919), ultimately at Innsbruck.

name: Murray, Alexander
description: Scottish physician and botanist at Aberdeen.

name: Murray, Andrew
description: Scottish entomologist and botanist; trained to be a lawyer and practicing at Edinburgh until 1860; from 1861-1864 assistant-secretary to the Royal Horticultural Society in London.

page_title_longer_max-80: Murray, George Robert Milne [std. G. Murray]
name: Murray, George Robert Milne
description: British cryptogamist; pupil of de Bary; assistant (1876-1895) and keeper of the Department of Botany of BM(NH) 1895-1905; naturalist on the West Indian Eclipse Expedition of 1886; scientific director, National Antarctic Expedition "Discovery" 1901 (organisation only).

name: Murray, Johan Andreas (Anders)
description: Swedish botanist; pupil of Linnaeus 1756-1760; studied at Göttingen 1760-1763; Dr. med. ib. 1763; professor of medicine and botany at Göttingen 1764 (ordin. 1769)-1791.

page_title_longer_max-80: Murray, Rev. Richard Paget [std. R.P. Murray]
name: Murray, Rev. Richard Paget
description: British clergyman and botanist; ordained 1868; curate of Plymstock, Beckenham and Baltonsborough (1868-1882, in succession); vicar of Shapwick (Dorset; 1883-1908); botanized in Ireland, Portugal and Canary Is.

name: Murray, Stewart
description: Scottish botanist, superintendent of the Glasgow botanic Garden.

name: Murrill, William Alphonso
description: American mycologist; M. A. Randolph Macon Coll. 1891; Dr. phil. Cornell Univ. 1900; ass. curator New York Bot. Garden 1905, ass. director 1908, supervisor publ. instr. 1919; retired to Gainesville, Florida 1924.

name: Muschler, Reinhold "Reno" Conrad
description: German botanist and poet; Dr. phil. Berlin 1908; in Egypt for health reasons 1902-1904; from 1908-1913 at the Botanical Museum, Berlin; from then on active as poet and novelist.

name: Mussche, Jean Henri
description: Belgian botanist; curator of the botanical garden at Gent.

name: Musset, Charles Raymond
description: French botanist at Toulouse; from 1878-1883 lecturer, 1883-1892 professor of botany at the Faculté des Sciences, Grenoble.

name: Mutel, (Pierre) Auguste (Victor)
description: French botanist and soldier, sometime military administrator at Le Hâvre.

page_title_long: Mutis y Bosio, José Célestino Bruno
page_title_longer_max-80: Mutis y Bosio, José Célestino Bruno [std. Mulis]
name: Mutis y Bosio, José Célestino Bruno
name_ed: Mutis y Bosio, José Célestino Bruno
description: Spanish physician and botanist at Madrid; went to New Granada in 1750, discovered Cinchona; director of the Expedición botánica and its flora; founder of the first astronomical observatory in South America; subsequently professor of mathematics at Santa-Fé de Bogota; founder of a botanic garden and ultimately clergyman at Santa Fé.

name: Mygind, Franz (Frauds von
description: Austrian imperial counsel ("Hofrat") at the ministry of commerce; friend of N. J. von Jacquin.

name: Myrin, Claës Gustaf
description: Swedish botanist and agricultural economist at Uppsala.

name: Nábelek, František
description: Moravian botanist; studied at Vienna University under R. v. Wettstein (1902-1907); Dr. phil. Wien 1907; from 1908-1920 high school teacher at Lipníka (Leipnik); visited Near East (1909-1911); from 1921-1928 id. at Brno, from 1925-1934 lecturer, from 1934-1939 professor of botany at Masaryk University, Brno; from 1939-1950 professor of botany and head of the Botanical Institute of Comenius University, Bratislava.

name: Naccari, Fortunato Luigi
description: Italian botanist; high school teacher at the seminary of Chioggia; later university librarian at Padova

name: Nachtigal, Gustav Hermann
description: German collector and explorer of Africa; military physician; from 1861 in Algeria, from 1863 in Tunisia; travelling in northern Africa 1868-1875; from 1882-1884 German consul at Tunis; first colonizer of Togo and Cameroon (1884-1885); died at sea when returning to Germany.

name: Nadeaud, Jean
description: French physician (naval surgeon), botanist, explorer of the Southern Pacific.

name: Nádvornik, Joseph (Josef)
description: Czechoslovak lichenologist and high school teacher (from 1925-1966) at Uzhgorod, Hlinsko and Praha.

name: Nägeli, Carl Wilhelm [von], [Naegeli]
description: Swiss-born botanist; Dr. phil. Zürich 1840; Dr. med. h.c. Freiburg 1854; habil. 1842; professor of botany at Zürich 18481852; at Freiburg i.Br. 1852-1855; at the ETH Zürich 1855-1857; at München 1857-1891.

name: Nägeli, Otto
description: Swiss botanist and physician; habil. int. med. Zurich 1900; professor of medicine at Tübingen 1912-1918; id. at Zürich 1918 (from 1921 as ord. prof.).

name: Naezén, Daniel Eric
description: Swedish physician and botanist; studied with Linnaeus fil.; Dr. phil. Uppsala 1779; Dr. med. ib. 1783; regional physician for the Umeå district from 1782-1808.

name: Nairne, Alexander Kyd
description: British botanist; clergyman in the Bombay Civil Service

name: Nakai, Takenoshin [Takenosin]
description: Japanese botanist; Ph. D. Tokyo Univ. 1907; Dr. Sci. Tokyo 1914; from 1908-1947 assistant, lecturer (1917), assistant professor (1922) and professor of botany (1927) at the University of Tokyo; from 1943-1945 director of the Buitenzorg (now Bogor) Botanical Gardens in occupied Java; from 1947 director of the National Science Museum.

name: Nam, Vincenzo
description: Italian physician and botanist; Dr. med. Univ. Torino.

name: Nannfeldt, John [earlier Johan] Axel [Frithiof]
description: Swedish botanist; Dr. phil. Uppsala 1932; from 1939-1970 director of the Botanical Museum at Uppsala.

name: Nannizzi, Arturo
description: Italian botanist; lecturer in mycology at the University of Siena; from 1935 also director of the Siena botanical garden.

name: Nardo, Giovanni Domenico (Giandomenico)
description: Italian botanist; Dr. med. Padua; practicing physician and director of the orphanage at Venetia and director of the cholera hospital at S. Alviso.

name: Nascher, Friedrich Wilhelm
description: fictitious German botanist, stated to have resided in Havana and to have travelled in South America.

name: Nash, George Valentine
description: American botanist and horticulturist; at the New York Botanical Garden from its initiation as collector (1896), curator of plantations (1899) and head gardener (1900); collected extensively in Florida and the West Indies.

name: Nathorst, Alfred Gabriel
description: Swedish palaeobotanist; Dr. phil. Lund 1874; lecturer at Lund 1874-1879; with the Swedish geological survey 1879-1884; from 18851917 professor and director of the palaeobotanical division of the Naturhistoriska Museum.

name: Nattras, Roland Marshall
description: British plant pathology; Univ. Lond. B.Sc. 1921

name: Naudin, Charles Victor
description: French botanist and horticulturist; Dr. sci. Paris 1842; botanist at the Muséum d'Histoire naturelle 1845 (aide-naturaliste 1854); owner of a private experimental garden at Collioure 1869-1878; from 1878 director of the botanical garden of the Villa Thuret at Antibes; early plant hybridiser.

name: Naumann, Einar Christian Leonard
description: Swedish limnologist and algologist; Dr. phil. Lund 1917; lecturer (1917) and professor (1919) of limnology at Lund; one of the founders, with A. Thienemann, of the Soc. int. Limnol.

name: Naumburg, Samuel Johann
description: German botanist; professor of botany at Erfurt

name: Naumov, Nikolai Alexandrovic
description: Russian mycologist; Dr. phil. St. Petersburg 1910; later at the Jaczevski Institute of mycology of Leningrad.

page_title_longer_max-80: Navarro de Andrade, Edmundo [std. E. Navarro]
name: Navarro de Andrade, Edmundo
description: Brazilian entomologist, botanist and forester at São Paulo.

name: Nave, Johann
description: Bohemian financial administrator and botanist; educated at Brünn (Brno), studied in Vienna with Unger 1850-1854; from 1854-1864 again in Brünn as civil servant in the regional finance department.

name: Naveau, [Georges] Raymond [Léonard]
description: Belgian bryologist; director of the botanic garden and of the natural history museum at Antwerp; teacher at the Belvers agricultural college.

name: Náves, Andres
description: Spanish Augustinian friar; collected in the Philippine Islands

name: Nawaschin, Sergius Gawrilowitsch [Navashin, Sergei, Gavrilovich]
description: Russian botanist (cytologist); lecturer at St. Petersburg 1888-1894; from 1894-1915 director of the botanical garden at Kiew; from 1915-1923 at Tiflis; from 1923 at Moscow as head of the Timiriazev Inst., from 1929 at the Gytological Laboratory of the Academy of Sciences, Detskoje Selo nr. Leningrad.

name: Neal, Adam
description: British gardener to J. Blackburne at Warrington.

name: Neal, Marie Catherine
description: American botanist; B. A. Smith Coll. 1912; M. Sc. Yale 1925; from 1920 at B. P. Bishop Museum, Honolulu; after 1930 in charge of the herbarium.

name: Nealley, Greenleaf Cilley
description: American botanist; in Burlington, Iowa 18631882; with Texas A & M 1882-1883, in Houston 1886-1891; at San Antonio and San Diego, Texas 1892-1896; collected grasses for USDA

name: Necker, Noel Joseph de
description: French-born botanist and historiographer; later "kurpfälzischer Botaniker" in Mannheim

name: Nectoux, Hipolyte (Hippolyte)
description: French botanist who accompanied Napoleon to Egypt.

page_title_longer_max-80: Née, Isidore Charles Sigismond [std. Née I.C.S fictitious]

name: Née, Luis
description: French botanist, later naturalized Spaniard; on the Malaspina expedition in La Descubierta and La Atrevida, 1789-1794

page_title_long: Nees von Esenbeck, Christian Gottfried Daniel
page_title_longer_max-80: Nees von Esenbeck, Christian Gottfried Daniel [std. Nees]
name: Nees von Esenbeck, Christian Gottfried Daniel
name_ed: Nees von Esenbeck, Christian Gottfried Daniel
description: German naturephilosopher, physician and botanist; Dr. med. Giessen, 1800; physician at Sickershausen 1802; president of the "Leopoldina" 1818-1858; professor of botany at Erlangen (1818- 1819), Bonn (1819-1830) and Breslau (1831-1851), formally dismissed 1851.

page_title_long: Nees von Esenbeck, Theodor Friedrich Ludwig
page_title_longer_max-80: Nees von Esenbeck, Theodor Friedrich Ludwig [std. T. Nees]
name: Nees von Esenbeck, Theodor Friedrich Ludwig
name_ed: Nees von Esenbeck, Theodor Friedrich Ludwig
description: German botanist; pharmaceutical assistant at Basel 1811-1816, at Hanau 1816-1817; inspector of the Leiden botanical garden 1817-1819; Dr. phil. Erlangen 1818; garden inspector and lecturer at Bonn University 1819; professor of pharmacy ib. (1822 extraord., 1827 ord.), co-director of the botanic garden 1833; brother of C. G. Nees von Esenbeck.

name: Neger, Franz Wilhelm
description: German forest botanist and mycologist; Dr. phil. München 1892; high school teacher at Weihenstephan 1892-1893; with the Chilean boundary commission 1893-1897; curator of the herbarium at München 1894-1902; professor of botany at the forestry college of Eisenach 1902-1905, id. at Tharandt nr. Dresden 1905-1920; director of the botanical institute and botanical garden of the Technisch Hochschule, Dresden 1920-1923.

name: Neger, Johannes
description: German botanist at Nürnberg.

name: Negri, Giovanni
description: Italian botanist, Dr. phil. Torino 1925; assistant at the Istituto botanico Torino 1903-1924, at Cagliari 1925; from 1925-1947 professor of botany and director of the Istituto botanico, Firenze.

name: Neill, Patrick
description: Scottish publisher and botanist at Edinburgh; founder and longtime secretary of the Caledonian Horticultural Society and Wernerian Society.

name: Neilreich, August
description: Austrian botanist; in various positions with Vienna law courts from 1828-1856, ultimately as Civilgerichtsrath; from 1857 (retirement because of tuberculosis) devoting himself entirely to botany; Dr. phil. h.c. Wien 1865.

name: Nel, Gert Cornelius
description: South African botanist; Dr. phil. Berlin 1914 (under Engler); professor of botany at Stellenbosch, South Africa 1921-1950.

name: Nelmes, Ernest
description: British botanist; associated with Kew as gardener, herbarium assistant and librarian from 1921-1958; specialist on Carex.

name: Nelson, Aven
description: American botanist, plant collector and educator at the University of Wyoming, as professor of biology from 1887; founder of the Rocky Mountain herbarium (RM); Dr. phil. Denver 1904; president of the University of Wyoming 19171922.

name: Nelson, David
description: British gardener, collector and explorer on the voyage of the "Resolution" and the "Discovery" 1776-1780 (Capt. Cook's third voyage); from 17801787 gardener at Kew; on the "Bounty" 1787-1789; escaped with Bligh from the mutiny but died on Timor.

name: Nelson, Edward Milles
description: British microscopist and diatomologist.

name: Nelson, Edward William
description: American naturalist; explorer of Alaska, the Arctic and Mexico; with the USDA 1890-1929; Dr. phil. l.c. George Washington Univ. 1920.

name: Nelson, Elias Emanuel
description: Swedish-born American botanist; pupil of Aven Nelson at Laramie, Wyoming; scientific aid USDA 1900; assistant in horticulture Univ. Wyoming 1901-1905; superintendent experimental farm Bend, Oregon 1905.

name: Nelson, John ("Senilis")
description: British arboriculturist of Lymington, Hants.

name: Nemec, Bohumil Rehor
description: Bohemian (Czechoslovakian) botanist; Dr. phil. Praha 1896; mycologist and physiologist; professor of plant anatomy and physiology at the Charles University at Praha from 1904.

name: Němejc, František
description: Bohemian (Czechoslovakian) palaeobotanist; Dr. phil. Praha 1924; assistant (1924) later (1939) director of the geological-palaeontological department of the Natural History Museum, Prague; extraord. (1929), later (1948) ordinary professor at the Charles University.

name: Nemoto, Kwanji
description: Japanese botanist.

page_title_long: Nendtvich, Carl Maximilian von Cserkut (Károli Miksa)
page_title_longer_max-80: Nendtvich, Carl Maximilian von Cserkut (Károli Miksa) [std. Nendtv.]
name: Nendtvich, Carl Maximilian von Cserkut (Károli Miksa)
name_ed: Nendtvich, Carl Maximilian von Cserkut (Károli Miksa)
description: Hungarian botanist, Dr. med. Budapest 1836; connected from 1839(?) with the Joseps-Industrieschule (later: the Budapest Polytechnic) from 1850 as professor; also connected with Budapest University.

name: Nervander, Johan Hugo Emmerik
description: Swedish-born botanist; studied in Helsinki, fil. mag. 1853; high school teacher in Viborg 1857-1901.

name: Nessel, Hermann
description: German botanist and gardener; originally assistant at the Institute for Plant Physiology of Berlin University; subsequently in charge of the University of Giessen Botanical Garden; specialist on Lycopodiaceac.

name: Nestler, Chrétien Géofroy [Christian Géofroy]
description: Alsatian botanist of German origin; studied with L. C. Richard at Paris; army pharmacist 1806-1810; from 1813 assistant to Villars; professor of botany and pharmacy at Strasbourg 1817-1832.

page_title_long: Netto, Ladislau de Souza Mello e
page_title_longer_max-80: Netto, Ladislau de Souza Mello e [std. Netto]
name: Netto, Ladislau de Souza Mello e
name_ed: Netto, Ladislau de Souza Mello e
description: Brazilian botanist; director of the botanical section óf the Rio de Janeiro National Museum 1866-1875; director of the entire museum from 1875-1893.

name: Neuberger, Joseph
description: German botanist; studied at Freiburg im Breisgau 1874-1878; high school teacher at Heidelberg 1878-1881 and 1884-1890; id. at Donaueschingen 1881-1884; id. at Freiburg i.Br. 1890-1919.

name: Neubner, Jacob Eduard
description: German lichenologist; Dr. phil. Leipzig 1883; high school teacher at Plaven/Vogtland from 1882.

name: Neuman, Julius John
description: American botanist with the Wisconsin geological and natural history survey.

name: Neuman, Leopold Martin
description: Swedish botanist, Dr. phil. Lund 1881; teacher at Sundsvall high school 1883; rector at Ystad high school 1889-1918; at Österhalm, Stockholm 1904.

name: Neumann, Ferdinand
description: German horticulturist at Erfurt.

name: Neumayer, Georg Balthasar von
description: German naturalist; director of the Hamburg naval observatory 1876-1903.

name: Neureuter, Franz
description: German botanist; high school teacher at Heiligenstadt.

name: Neuweiler, Ernst
description: Swiss botanist and palaeontologist; Dr. phil. Zürich 1901

name: Newberry, John Strong
description: American botanist and palaeontologist; trained as a physician at Western Reserve College and Cleveland Medical College (M.D. 1848); in Paris 1849-1850; practicing medicine in Cleveland 1851-1855; surgeon and geologist on various transcontinental exploring expeditions into the American West; professor of Geology at Columbia College 1866-1892; LL.D.h.c. Columbia 1867; chief geologist to the Geological Survey of Ohio 1869-1872.

name: Newbould, William Williamson
description: British botanist and clergyman; BA Cantab 1842; Curate Bluntisham, Hunts, 1845; id. Camberton, Cambr. 1846; later living at Turnham Green and Kew.

name: Newcombe, Frederick Charles
description: American botanist (plant physiologist); Dr. phil. Leipzig 1893; Instructor of botany (from 1905 full professor of botany) at the University of Michigan 1890-1923; in retirement at Honolulu 1923-1927.

name: Newhall, Charles Stedman
description: American clergyman and dendrologist; BA. Amherst 1869, MA 1892; studied at Union Theological Seminary; filled various pastorates; ultimately superintendent of the forest reserves of Northern California.

name: Newman, Edward
description: British printer, editor, pteridologist and entomologist; prolific author

name: Newman, Francis William
description: Australian botanist; superintendent botanical garden, Hobart from 1845.

name: Newton, Isaac
description: British-Portuguese businessman and bryologist at Porto, Portugal.

name: Newton, James
description: British physician and botanist; acquainted with J. Ray and J. Commelijn.

name: Newton, Lily
description: British botanist, married William Charles Frank Newton 1925; Ph. D. Bristol 1925.

name: Neygenfind, Friedrich Wilhelm
description: German physician and botanist at Schmiedeberg in Liegnitz.

name: Nicholls, William Henrey
description: Australian bookbinder, orchidologist, propagator and gardener at the Footscray (Melbourne) municipal gardens.

name: Nichols, George Elwood
description: American bryologist and ecologist; Dr. phil. Yale 1909; with Yale from 1904 as assistant, instructor (1909), ass. professor (1915), assoc. professor (1924), Eaton professor of botany 1926-1939.

name: Nicholson, George
description: British gardener at Kew 1873-1886, curator id. 18861901; Veitch medal R. H. S. 1894.

name: Nicholson, Henry Alleyne
description: Scottish palaeobotanist; Dr. phil. Göttingen 1862; M. D. Edinburgh 1869; professor of natural history Toronto 1871, Durham 1874, St. Andrews 1875, Aberdeen 1882.

name: Nicholson, William Edward
description: British lawyer and bryologist at Lewes, Sussex.

name: Nicklès, Napoléon
description: French Alsatian pharmacist and botanist at Benfelden.

name: Nicolai, Ernst August
description: German botanist and practicing physician at Arnstadt (nr. Erfurt, Thüringen)

name: Nicolas, [Léon Marie Joseph] Gustave
description: French biologist, mainly working on physiology, genetics, mycology, and bryology; Dr. phil. Paris 1909; in academic functions in Algeria (1910-1919) and Nancy (1919-1920); professor of general botany at Toulouse (1920-1927), id. of applied botany 1927-1945.

name: Nicolson, (Père)
description: Dominican priest in Paris who lived about four years on Santo Domingo.

name: Nicolucci, Giustiniano
description: Italian anthropologist, physician, ethnologist, and botanist at the University of Naples.

name: Nicotra, Leopoldo
description: Italian physician and botanist, professor of botany and curator of the botanical garden of Sassari 1892-1900; professor of botany at Messina 19001900; at Cagliari 1911-1914.

name: Niebuhr, Carsten

name: Niederlein, Gustavo

name: Nielsen, Peter

name: Nienburg, Karl Ortgies Wilhelm

name: Niessen, Joseph

page_title_long: Nieuwland, Julius [Aloysius] Arthur, C. S. C.

name: Noehden, Heinrich Adolph [August]
description: German botanist at Göttingen.

name: Noll, Henry R.
description: American botanist

name: Nonne, Johann Philipp
description: German botanist at Erfurt.

name: Nordenskiöld, [Nils] Adolph Erik [von]

name: Nordmann, Alexander [Davidovic] von

name: Nordstedt, Carl Fredrik Otto ["Otto"]
description: Swedish phycologist of independent means; med. fil. kand. Lund 1861; amanuensis at the Lund botanical institute 1878- 1886; curator at id. 1886-1909; Dr. phil. h.c. Lund 1881; Prof. id. 1903.

name: Norén, Carl Otto Gustaf
description: Swedish botanist; Dr. phil. Uppsala 1907; high school teacher in Stockholm (1910), Karlskrona (1911), and Vänersborg (1914).

name: Norlindh, Nils Tycho
description: Swedish botanist at the Botanical Museum, Lund,

name: Norman, George

page_title_long: Northrop, Alice Belle (née Rich; Alice R(ich) Northrop)

Kansas State College of Agriculture (now Kansas State University), Manhattan (1896, 1900) under the direction of A. S. Hitchcock, assistant professor at Kansas State (1894-1896); botanical assistant, Missouri Botanical Garden (1896-1901): professor of botany, Maryland Agricultural College (now University of Maryland), College Park (1901-1942); professor emeritus (1942-1966).

name: Notcutt, William Lowndes

name: Noter, Raphaël de

name: Notø, Andreas
description: Norwegian botanist; high school teacher at Tromsø (18881909), Levanger (1909-1920) and Bodø (from 1920):

name: Novák, Josef

name: Nuttall, Lawrence William

name: Nyárády, Erasmus Julius

name: Nylander, Andreas Edvinus

name: Nyman, Carl Fredrik

page_title_longer_max-80: Nyman, Erik Olof August [std. E. Nym.]

name: Ochoterena, Isaac
description: Mexican botanist, director of the botanical section of the Directión Estud. Biol. Mex. from 1915.

name: Østrup, Ernst Vilhelm

name: Oettel, Karl Christian
description: German botanist.

name: Ohlendorff, J. H.
description: German gardener at Hamburg.

name: Ohlert, [Otto Ludwig] Arnold

name: Okamura, Kintarô

Harvard 1904; instructor in phanerogamic botany Wabash 1893-1895; high school teacher at Frankfort, Ind. 1895-1896, botanist at Harvard 1897-1903; at Madison, Wisc. 1904-1907; at State Agricul- tural College S. Dakota 1907-1912; curator of the Brooklyn botanical garden 1912-1920.

name: Oliver, Francis Wall
description: British ecologist and palaeobotanist; lecturer in (1888) and professor (1890-1929) at University College, London; professor of botany at Cairo University 1929-1935; son of Daniel Oliver.

name: Olivi, Giuseppe

name: Olivier, [Joseph] Ernest

name: Olivier, Guillaume Antoine

Gent 1963.

page_title_longer_max-80: Ortega, Jesús González [std. J. Gonz. Ort.]

description: Mexican botanist.

name: Ortloff, Fr.

page_title_longer_max-80: Osborn, Theodore George Bentley [std. T. Osborn]
name: Osborn, Theodore George Bentley
description: British botanist; MSc. Manchester 1911, D. Sc. ib. 1920; lecturer Manchester 1908-1912; professor of botany Adelaide 19121927; id. Sydney 1928-1937; id. Oxford 1937-1953; returned to Adelaide 1953.

name: Oskamp, Dirk Leonard
description: Dutch botanist and physician at Utrecht.

name: Osten, Cornelius
description: German botanist and business man in Uruguay; Dr. phil. h.c. Göttingen 1934.

page_title_long: Osten-Saken, Baron Friedrich von der (Fedor Romanovic)
page_title_longer_max-80: Osten-Saken, Baron Friedrich von der (Fedor Romanovic) [std. Osten-Saken]
name: Osten-Saken, Baron Friedrich von der (Fedor Romanovic)
name_ed: Osten-Saken, Baron Friedrich von der (Fedor Romanovic)
description: German botanist in Russia.

name: Ostenfeld, Carl Emil Hansen
description: Danish botanist; Ph. D. Kjøbenhavn 1906; inspector of the Botanical Museum from 1900-1918; professor of botany, at the Veterinary College, 1918-1923, and director of the Botanical Garden of Kjøbenhavn 1923-1931.

name: Osterhout, George Everett
description: American lumberman and amateur botanist; collected in Colorado between 1893 and 1930.

name: Otero Jañez, José Idilio
description: Porto-Rican botanist; librarian and botanical bibliographer at the Insular Exp. Sta., Porto-Rico.

name: Otis, Charles Herbert
description: American botanist and curator of the botanical garden of and lecturer at the University of Michigan (1910-1913); Ph. D. ib. 1913; instructor and later professor of botany at Cornell (1913-1915); Univ. New Hampshire 1915-1916; Western Reserve Univ. (1916-1927) Univ. of Wisconsin, Madison (19271930); Bowling Green State, Ohio (1930-1956).

name: Ott, Johann
description: Bohemian physician and botanist at Praha.

name: Otth, [Carl] Adolph
description: Swiss physician and naturalist; pupil of A.-P. de Candolle; collaborator of Seringe; physician at Bern, travelling widely; died of the plague while in Jerusalem.

name: Otto, Bernhard Christian
description: German botanist; Dr. med. 1789, professor of medicine at Frankfurt a. Oder.

name: Otto, [Christoph] Friedrich
description: German botanist and gardener; at the Berlin botanical garden 1801-1843; director of the Schöneberg horticultural school 1823-1843.

name: Otto, [Carl Friedrich] Eduard
description: German botanist and horticulturist at Hamburg; son of C. F. Otto; collected in Cuba, North America and Venezuela 1838-1841; curator of the Hamburg botanical garden 1844-1866; later commercial nurseryman at Altona.

name: Otto, Ernst von
description: German botanist; landowner at Possendorf nr. Dresden 1826-1856; ultimately at Dresden.

name: Otto, Johann Gottfried
description: German botanist; Dr. med. Jena 1784.

page_title_longer_max-80: Oudemans, Corneille Antoine Jean Abram [std. Oudem.]
name: Oudemans, Corneille Antoine Jean Abram
description: Dutch physician and botanist; Dr. med. Leiden 1847; practicing physician and lecturer at the Rotterdam medical school 1848-1859; professor of medicine and botany at the Amsterdam Athenaeum 1859- 1877; professor of botany and pharmacognosy at Amsterdam University 1877-1896; general secretary of the Royal Netherlands Academy of Sciences 1879-1895; in retirement at Arnhem from 1896.

name: Over, William Henry
description: American botanist; curator of the Museum of the University of South Dakota at Vermillion.

name: Overeem [-de Haas], Casper van
description: Dutch mycologist; Ph. D. Zürich 1920; at Buitenzorg (Bogor) 1921-1927 as mycological assistant at the Herbarium bogoriense.

name: Overholts, Lee Oras
description: # American mycologist; A.B. Miami Univ. 1912; Ph.D. St. Louis 1915; instructor in botany at Pennsylvania State College 1915-1917; professor of botany at id. 1917-1946.

name: Owen, Maria Louisa (née Tallant)
description: American botanist at Springfield, Mass.

page_title_longer_max-80: Oye, Paul Herman Gustave van [std. Oye]
name: Oye, Paul Herman Gustave van
description: Belgian zoologist, hydrobiologist and botanist at Gent; Dr. phil. Gent 1911, MD. Gent 1924; at the Tasikmalaya fisheries station (Java) 1918-1922; professor of zoology at the State University of Gent 1926-1956; president of Dodonaea 1937-1969; specialist on Desmidiaceae and history of botany.

name: Oyster, John Houck
description: American botanist at Paola, Kansas.

name: Pabst, Carl
description: German (Saxonian) botanist from Halle; collected plants for Van Houtte at the Cape Verde island Mayo (Jun 1846) and subsequently on the Brazilian island of Santa Catharina; settled as a colonist in Itajahi in the Donna Franziska settlement of the Hamburger Colonisations-Gesellschaft.

name: Pabst. Gustav
description: German (Thuringian) botanist, artist and surveyor at Gera.

name: Paccard, Ernesto
description: Uruguayan botanist.

name: Pacher, David
description: Austrian clergyman and botanist; ord. 29 Jul 1840; in various clergical ranks in Carinthia 1841-1902, at Leoben ober Gmünd 1840-1843, Glödnitz and St. Lorenzen 1843-1845, at Sagritz 1845-1851, at Tröppolach 1851-1861, at Tiffen 1861-1875, from 1875-1902 dean at Obervellach.

name: Packard, Alpheus Spring,
description: American geologist, zoologist and botanist; MD Harvard 1864; professor of zoology and geology at Brown University 1878-1905; secretary of the U.S. Entomological Commission (to investigate the Rocky Mountain locust) 1876; Dr. med. Bowdoin 1864, LL.D. id. 1891.

name: Packe, Charles
description: British naturalist and mountaineer of independent means in Leicestershire; B.A. Oxford 1849; explorer of the Alps, Pyrenees and the Sierra Nevada.

name: Paczoski (Patschosky, Patschotsky), Joseph Conradovich
description: Ukranianborn Polish botanist; assistant at the Dept. Botany, Univ. Kiew 1888-1894, id. at the botanical garden St. Petersburg 1894-1895, at Dublany 1895-1897; director of the Natural History Museum, Cherson 1897-1920 and professor at the Polytechnic ib. 1918- 1922; director of the Steppe Reserve at Ascania Nova 1922-1923; repatriated to Poland 1923; director National Park Bialowieza 1923-1928; professor of phytosociology at the University of Poznan 1925-1931; Dr. phil. h.c. Poznan 1932; from 1931 active as a private scientist; early phytosociologist and ecologist.

name: Page, William Bridgewater
description: British nurseryman at Hammersmith and Southampton.

name: Paget, Sir James
description: British surgeon and botanist, baronet 1871 LL.D. Cambridge 1874.

name: Paglia, Enrico
description: Italian botanist at Mantua.

name: Pahnsch, Gerhard
description: Esthonian botanist.

name: Paiche, Philippe
description: Swiss botanist at Genève; studied Potentilla, Hieracium and Rosa.

name: Paige, Edward Winslow
description: American lawyer and botanist at New York; A.B. Union Coll. 1864; LL.D. Hobart Coll. 1887.

name: Pailleux, [Nicolas] Auguste
description: French botanist; owner and director of an embroidery firm at Saint Pierre-lez-Calars ca. 1840-1871; in retirement at Crosnes nr. Villeneuve-Saint-Georges dedicating himself to horticulture developing new cultivars of vegetables; introduced the chinese artichoke ("Crosne").

name: Paillot, Justin
description: French botanist; high school teacher at Nans; from 18631885 pharmacist at Besançon; from 1886 at Rougemont.

name: Paine, John Alsop
description: American botanist; M.A. Hamilton College 1862; Dr. phil. id. 1874; employed by the board of regents of the State of New York in connection with the flora of the State in 1862-1867; teaching at various colleges and editing journals from 1868; in Eastern Palestine for the Palestine Exploration Society 1872-1873; curator at the Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York, from 1889.

name: Painter, William Hunt
description: British clergyman (entered Church of England 1861) and botanist at Barbon, High Wycombe, Edgbaston, Derby and Bristol; rector of Stinchley 1894-1901; died in Shrewbury.

name: Palacký, Johann Baptist [Jan]
description: Bohemian politician, geographer, botanist and ichthyologist; Dr. phil. Praha 1850; lecturer in geography, later also in botany at Praha 1856-1866; 1878-1885; extraordinary professor 1885-1902; travelled widely mainly in Europe.

name: Palanza, Alfonso
description: Italian botanist and plant collector; sometime private teacher at Napoli; from 1894 high school teacher at the Liceo di Bitonto.

name: Palassou, Pierre Bernard (Palasso)
description: French clergyman; naturalist and explorer of the Pyrenees.

name: Paláu y Verdéra, Antonio
description: Spanish botanist at the Madrid botanical garden.

name: Paley, Frederick Apthorp
description: British Greek scholar and botanist; BA Cantab. 1838; LL.D. Aberdeen 1883.

name: Palézieux, Philippe de
description: Swiss botanist at Genève; student of L. Radlkofer; Dr. sci. nat. münchen 1899; from 1900-1939 as "Privatgelehrter" in Germany, often at Berlin-Dahlem, and traveling widely; returned to Genève 1939; curator of the Herbier Boissier 1943-1952.

name: Palhinha, Ruy Telles
description: Azores-born Portugese botanist; high school teacher at Lisbon, later at the Botanical Institute of the University of Lisbon (director 1921-1941).

name: Palibin, Ivan Vladimirovich
description: Russian botanist; Dr. phil. 1934; in various ways associated with the St. Petersburg botanical garden, later Komarov Botanical Institute, from 1895; from 1906-1910 at the Jeneve University; from 1910-1915 at the St. Petersburg botanical garden; from 1915-1922 at Batoem; 1923-1929 head botanist, 1929-1932 director of the Botanical Museum and Garden at Leningrad; from 1932-1949 head of the Palaeobotanical Department at Leningrad; organized a palaeobotanical cabinet at the Petroleum Institute 1931.

page_title_long: Palisot de Beauvois, Ambroise Marie François Joseph
page_title_longer_max-80: Palisot de Beauvois, Ambroise Marie François Joseph [std. P. Beauv.]
name: Palisot de Beauvois, Ambroise Marie François Joseph
name_ed: Palisot de Beauvois, Ambroise Marie François Joseph
description: French traveller and botanist; from 1786-1787 in Oware and Bénin; 1788-1791 on Haiti; 1791-1798 in the United States (briefly in Haiti again 1793); back in Paris as teacher at the Athenée des Étrangers; member Institut de France 1806; councillor Université de Paris 1815.

name: Palla, Eduard
description: Moravia-born Austrian botanist; Dr. phil. Wien 1887; from 1888 at the University of Graz; habil. 1891; titular professor and "Adjunct" 1901; extra-ordinary professor 1909; ordinary professor 1913.

name: Pallas, Johann Dietrich
description: German botanist.

name: Pallas, Peter [Pyotr] Simon
description: German (Berlin) botanist and geographer; explorer of Russia and Siberia, pioneer naturalist of Northern Asia; Dr. med. Leiden 1759; 1761-1766 working in Holland and England; to Russia 1767; from 1768-1774 in the Ural Mts. and Western Siberia; 1774-1793 in St. Petersburg; 1793-1794 in S. Russia and the Crimea; settled later in the Crimea 1795-1810; retired to Berlin 1810-1811.

name: Palm, Björn Torvald
description: Swedish botanist and traveller; Dr. phil. Stockholm, lecturer at the University of Stockholm 1915-1918 and 1932-1939, assistant for plant pathology at Buitenzorg, Java, 1916, director at a plant-breeding station for tob- acco at Deli, Sumatra, 1920, on plantations in Guatemala 1926-1929; professor at the University of Illinois, Urbana, 1930-1932; expert of plant-pathology at Stockholm 1945- 1947; travelled in Madagascar 1912-1914, in Dutch East Indies 1915-1926, in Central America and the West Indies 1926-1930.

name: Palmberg, Johannes Olai
description: Swedish physician, clergyman and botanist; studied medicine and botany at Turku from 1663, "med. et phys. lector" at Strängnäs (near Stockholm) from 1672; parish priest at Turinge (Södermanland) from 1688.

name: Palmer, Charles Mervin
description: American botanist; MS Pennsylvania State Coll. 1925; subsequently assistant, instructor and professor of botany at Butler University, Indianapolis.

name: Palmer, Edward
description: English-born American surgeon and botanist; professional collector of botanical, archeological and ethnological materials; emigrated to the U.S. 1849; from then on travelling and collecting mainly in the American West and in Mexico.

name: Palmer, Elmore
description: American botanist and physician at Dexter, Mich.

name: Palmer, Ernest Jesse
description: English-born American botanist and forester; came to the U.S. in 1878; collector for the Missouri Botanical Garden and the Arnold Arboretum; on the staff of the Arnold Arboretum 1921-1948; student of Crataegus.

name: Palmer, Frédéric T.
description: French horticulturist

name: Palmér, Johan Ernst
description: Swedish farmer and botanist at Tånga (Bohuslän), later at Ör (Dalsland).

name: Palmer, Johann Ludwig
description: German physician at Marbach; Dr. med. Tübingen 1817.

name: Palmer, Julius Auboineau
description: American mycologist.

name: Palmgren, Alvar
description: Finnish botanist; Dr. phil. Helsinki 1914; lecturer in botany at the College of technology, Helsinki 1916; professor of botany at Helsinki University 1928-1950.

name: Palmstruch, Johan Wilhelm
description: Swedish soldier [ryttmästare, cavalry capt.)] and botanical artist.

name: Palouzier, Émile
description: French botanist and pharmacist at the "École supérieure de Pharmacie", Montpellier.

name: Palun, Maurice
description: French botanist at Avignon.

name: Palustre
description: French physician and botanist.

name: Pammel, Louis Hermann
description: American botanist and conservationist; M.S. Univ. Wisc. 1889; Dr. phil. St. Louis 1896; assistant to W.G. Farlow 1885-1886; assistant Shaw school of Botany, St. Louis, 1886-1889; from 1889 at Ames, Iowa, as professor of botany; Dr. Sci. Univ. Wisc. 1925.

name: Pampanini, Renato
description: Italian botanist; studied at Fribourg, Lausanne and Genève (with R.H. Chodat); Dr. phil. Fribourg 1902; from 1904-1933 at the Istituto botanico di Firenze, from 1912 as assistant; professor of botany at Cagliari 1933-1948, ultimately at Torino.

name: Pamplin, William
description: British botanist; from 1839 botanical bookseller and publisher in Soho; retired to Llanderfel, North Wales 1863.

name: Pampuch, Albert
description: German botanist, high school teacher at Tremessen (Trzemessno, now Poland) near Bromberg.

name: Pancher, Jean Armand Isidore
description: French gardener, botanist and collector ("jardinier colonial") in Tahiti (1849-1857) and in New Caledonia 1857-1869, in France 1869-1874; again to New Caledonia, for J. Linden 1874-1877.

page_title_longer_max-80: Pancic, Josef (Giuseppe Pancio; Josif Panchic) [std. Pancic]
name: Pancic, Josef (Giuseppe Pancio; Josif Panchic)
description: Croatian botanist and physician; M.D. Budapest 1842; regional physician in Serbia 1846-1853; high school teacher (natural history) at the Belgrad Lyceum and director of the Belgrad botanical garden.

name: Pandé, S.K.
description: Indian bryologist; D. Sc. Lucknow 1936; from 1899-1959, demonstrator, professor of botany at Lucknow and chairman of the Department of Botany of Saugar University.

name: Panizzi-Savio, Francesco
description: Italian pharmacist at San Remo; author on the flora of San Remo.

name: Pansch, Adolf
description: German (Eutin/Lübeck) physician and botanist; at Kiel from 1864; participated in the second German North Polar Expedition 1869-1870 under K. Koldewey.

name: Pantanelli, Dante
description: Italian palaeontologist and geologist; Dr. math. phys. Pisa 1865; from 1882-1913 professor of mineralogy and geology at the University of Modena; student of Meneghini.

name: Pantanelli, Enrico Francesco,
description: Italian mycologist; son of Dante Pantanelli; Dr. sci. Modena 1902; with Pfeffer at Leipzig 1902-1903; with E. Schulze at Zürich 1903-1904; with L. Kny at Berlin 1904; at the Istituto di Botanica, Roma, 1904-1906; at the Roma Stazione di Patologie vegetale 1906-1913; at Naples 1913-1914; with the Italian Department of Agriculture at Roma 1914-1920; at the Bari Stazione de Agric. sperimentale 1920-1947.

name: Pantel, C.
description: French botanist and geographer

name: Pantling, Robert
description: British botanist; trained at Kew as a gardener; assistant Cinchona Dept., Bengal, 1879; curator Royal Botanic Gardens, Calcutta Dec 1879; at the Cinchona Dept. 1880; from 1897 as deputy superintendent.

name: Pantocsek, Josef
description: Hungarian botanist and provincial physican; district physician at Tavarnok; from 1896 director of the hospital and "wirklicher Sanitätsrat" at Bratislava (Pozsony); botanical explorer of Montenegro.

name: Pantu, Zacharia C. (Pantzu)
description: Roumanian botanist; at the Bucarest botanical institute 1890 (as naturalist), 1891-1934 (as curator).

name: Panzer, Georg Wolfgang Franz
description: German (Oberpfalz) physician, botanist and entomologist; Dr. med. Erlangen 1777; travelled in C. Europe 1778-1780; from 1780 regional physician and lecturer at the Collegium medicum, Nürnberg.

name: Paoletti, Giulio
description: Italian botanist; 1890-1897 assistant at the Padova botanical garden; professor of natural history at the technical college of Melfi 1897.

name: Paolucci, Luigi
description: Italian zoologist and botanist; professor of natural history at the Ancona technical School.

name: Pape, Georg Karl von
description: German (Prussian) botanist and magistrate at Lüneburg.

name: Papenfuss, George Frederick [Frederik]
description: South African-born American algologist; came to U.S. 1926, naturalized 1945; Dr. phil. Johns Hopkins 1933; assistant and lecturer Johns Hopkins 1929-1934; at Univ. of Cape Town 1935-1939; at University of Lund 1939-1940; at Univ. of Hawaii 1940-1942, with Univ. of California, Berkeley, from 1942-1971, from 1953-1971 as full professor.

name: Papp, Constantin
description: Roumanian botanist; Dr. phil. Iasi 1926; in various functions at Iasi University 1920-1964.

name: Pappe, Karl [Carl] Wilhelm Ludwig
description: German-born (Hamburg) South African botanist; Dr. med. Leipzig 1827; to South Africa 1835 as practicing physician; colonial botanist from 1848.

name: Pâque, Égide (Pâques)
description: Belgian clergyman (Jesuit priest) and botanist; ord. 7 Sep 1886; from 1888-1892 at Charleroi; from 1892-1906 id. at the Collège NotreDame de la Paix at Namur; from 1906-1910 at Antwerp; ultimately at Bruxelles.

name: Pardé, Léon Gabriel Charles
description: French dendrologist; trained at the École nationale forestière (1888); teacher and later director of the Arboretum national des Barres nr. Nogent-sur-Vernisson (Loiret).

page_title_long: Pardo de Tavera, Trinidad Herménégilde José
page_title_longer_max-80: Pardo de Tavera, Trinidad Herménégilde José [std. Pardo]
name: Pardo de Tavera, Trinidad Herménégilde José
name_ed: Pardo de Tavera, Trinidad Herménégilde José
description: Philippine physician, anthropologist, philologist and botanist; studied medicine at Paris; professor of anatomy at the Universidad de Santo Tomás; later heavily involved in local politics as well as representing the Philippines abroad.

name: Parfitt, Edward
description: British gardener, entomologist, mycologist and lichenologist; gardener in Norfolk and from 1848-1860 in Exeter; librarian of the Devon and Exeter Institution 1861-1893.

name: Paris, [Jean] Édouard Gabriel [Narcisse]
description: French soldier and bryologist; collected in France and Algeria; retired from the military as général de brigade 1889; commander of the Légion d'Honneur.

name: Parish, Samuel Bonsall
description: American botanist; B.A. New York Univ. 1858; collected extensively in Southern California; settled as fruit grower in the San Bernardino Valley, Calif. 1872; from 1920 hon. curator of the herbarium and lecturer in Californian botany at Stanford University.

name: Parisot, Charles Louis
description: French botanist and pharmacist at Belfort.

name: Parke, Mary
description: British phycologist at the Marine Biological Association, Plymouth, until March 1973.

name: Parker, Richard Neville
description: British botanist in the Indian Forest Service 1905-1939, forest botanist Dehra Dun 1922-1932, conservator of forests Punjab, 1932.

name: Parkhurst, Howard Elmore
description: American botanist.

name: Parkinson, Charles Edward
description: Scottish botanist; assistant conservator of forests, Andaman Isl. 1912; India Forest Service, Burma, 1916; Forest Botanist Burma 1925; Forest Research Institute, Dehra Dun 1929.

name: Parkinson, James
description: English surgeon, apothecary and palaeontologist at Hoxton, East London.

name: Parkinson, John
description: British apothecary and herbalist; King's herbarist; had a garden in Long Acre, London.

name: Parkinson, Sydney
description: British woollen draper; employed by Joseph Banks to work on the latter's collections, 1767; sent out with Cook on the Endeavour; died at Batavia.

page_title_longer_max-80: Parks, Harris Bradley [std. Har. B. Parks]
name: Parks, Harris Bradley
