description: American botanist, insect ecologist and agriculturist; B.S. Blackburn, Col. 1900; teacher at Sitka, Alaska 1905-1911, at Palmer College 19121917; entomologist at Texas A. and M. 1918-1920; agriculturist id. from 1922.

name: Parks, Harold Ernest
description: American mycologist and plant collector; in the U.S. army in China and the Philippines 1898-1899; salesman at Tacoma 1900-1910, at Santa Cruz, Calif. 1910-1914; post office clerk San José, Calif. 1914-1921, from 19211928 collector for UC; associate curator UC 1928-1950, hon. curator 1950-1967.

name: Parlatore, Filippo
description: Italian botanist; Dr. med. Palermo 1837; prosector and professor of anatomy at the University of Palermo; from 1842-1877 professor of botany and director of the botanic garden in Florence; founder of the herbarium of the botanical museum at Florence.

name: Parmentier, Antoine Augustin
description: French economic botanist and military pharmacist, especially active in promoting the potato and, later, the sugar beet in France; "apothicaire aide-major" at the Invalides 1766; member of the Conseil de Santé 1782-1813; first army pharmacist 1800; inspector general of the health service 18051813.

page_title_longer_max-80: Parmentier, Joseph Julien Ghislain [std. J. Parm.]
name: Parmentier, Joseph Julien Ghislain
description: Belgian landscape gardener, botanist; maire and burgomaster of Enghien.

name: Parmentier, Paul Evariste
description: French botanist; Dr. phil. Besançon 1898; from 1901 professor of botany at the University of Besançon; director of the Station agronomique de Franche-Comté.

name: Parnell, Richard
description: British ink manufacturer, ichthyologist and botanist, born at Bramford Speke, Devon; studied medicine at Edinburgh, Paris and London; died in Edinburgh; co-founder (1836) of the Edinburgh botanical Society.

name: Parodi, Domingo
description: Italian-born pharmacist; to Montevideo 1833; pharmacist ib. 1843; in Paraguay as physician and pharmacist 1853-1867; returned to Montevideo 1869, active as pharmacist until 1879; in Buenos Aires from 1878, Dr. pharm, ib. 1881, lecturer in pharmacy at the Faculty of medical sciences from 1884.

name: Parodi, Lorenzo Raimundo
description: Argentinian botanist (esp. agrostologist); studied with L. Hauman at the Univ. of Buenos Aires, Ir. agron. ib. 1918; professor of botany at the Faculties of Agronomy in Buenos Aires (1926-1966) and La Plata (19221947) and at the Museo de La Plata (1934-1947).

name: Parrique, Géraud ("Frère Gasilien")
description: French school teacher, clergyman, lichenologist and bryologist at Sorbiers (Loire)

page_title_longer_max-80: Parrot, Johann Jacob Friedrich Wilhelm [std. Parrot]
name: Parrot, Johann Jacob Friedrich Wilhelm
description: German-born (Baden) physician and botanist; studied at Dorpat (1809-1811); to the Crimea and the Caucasus 1811-1812; military physician with the Russian army 1815; professor of medicine at Dorpat 1821; visited the Pyrenees in 1824, and climbed Ararat 1829; to the North Cape 1837.

name: Parry, Charles Christopher
description: English-born American botanist and explorer; to the United States 1832; Dr. med Columbia 1846; with the Mexican Boundary Survey 1849-1861; exploring the Rocky Mountains 1861-1867; with the Pacific Railroad Survey 1867-1869; with the U.S. Dept. of Agriculture 1869-1872; from then on free-lance explorer in Utah, Nevada, California and Mexico; "king of Colorado Botany" (J.D. Hooker).

name: Parry, William Edward
description: British explorer; made three expeditions to the Arctic (north-west passage), 1819-20, 1821-23, 1824-25; DCL Oxford 1829; knighted 1829; rear admiral 1852.

page_title_long: Parsons, Frances Theodora (formerly Mrs. William Starr Dana; née Smith)
page_title_longer_max-80: Parsons, Frances Theodora (formerly Mrs. W.S. Dana; née Smith) [std. F. Parsons]
name: Parsons, Frances Theodora (formerly Mrs. William Starr Dana; née Smith)
name_ed: Parsons, Frances Theodora (formerly Mrs. William Starr Dana; née Smith)
description: American popular writer on botany.

name: Parsons, Mary Elizabeth
description: American popular writer on wild plants, born in Chicago; to California as a young girl, first at San Rafael and later at Kentfield.

name: Parsons, Thomas Henry
description: British gardener, trained at Kew; from 1913 curator of the Peradeniya botanical Garden.

name: Parvela, August Armas
description: Finnish botanist.

name: Pascal, Diego Baldassare
description: Italian botanist of French origin; professor of botany and director of the botanical garden at Parma 1795-1802.

name: Pascher, Adolf
description: Bohemia-born German botanist; studied at Praha with Beck von Mannagetta; Dr. phil. Praha 1905; habil. Praha 1909; assistant at the Praha botanical institute 1904-1912, extra-ordinary professor of pharmaceutical botany from 1912, of systematic botany (ordinary) from 1927, director of the botanical institute and garden 1933-1945.

name: Pasquale, Fortunato
description: Italian botanist and agronomist at Napoli; son of Giuseppe Antonio Pasquale; connected with the R. Istituto Tecnico di Napoli.

name: Pasquale, Giuseppe Antonio
description: Italian botanist, Dr. med. Napoli 1842; assistant to Tenore at Napoli 1840-1848; practicing physician 1848-1860; from 1860 professor of botany at the R. Collegio medico; succeeded Cesati as professor of botany and director of the botanical garden of the University 1883; disabled from 1884.

name: Passerini, Giovanni
description: Italian botanist; Dr. med. Parma 1836; at Milano 1843-1844; from 1844-1849 and 1853-1893 professor of botany and director of the botanical garden at Parma.

name: Passy, Antoine François
description: French botanist, geologist and politician; studied in Brussels; with the Napoleonic Elba army 1813-1815; from 1815 in France; prefect of the dépt. de l'Eure 1830; later in various administrative positions with the ministry of the interior; from 1848 in retirement at Gisors.

name: Paterson, William
description: British naturalist, traveller and administrator; collected in South Africa 1777-1779; to India 1781-1785, to Australia 1791, collected for Banks; Lieut.-Governor New South Wales 1800-1810.

name: Patouillard, Narcisse Théophile
description: French mycologist; studied at the École de Pharmacie, Paris; lived in Poligny 1881-1884 and Fontenay-sous-Bois 18841885; from 1885 in Paris; from 1898-1926 living at Neuilly-sur-Seine; assistant at PC from 1901.

name: Patout, Marie Rose
description: French herbalist and midwife at Toulon

name: Patraw, Pauline Mead
description: American botanist

name: Patrick, Ruth Myrtle
description: American diatomologist at the Philadelphia Academy of Natural Sciences; married Charles Hodge 1931; Ph. D. Univ. of Virginia 1934, at the Academy of Sciences from 1937 in various positions, curator of the Limnology Dept. from 1947; chairman of this department 1947-1973, chairman board of trustees Academy 1973-1976, from 1976 honorary chairman; Tyler award 1975; chairman Section of Population Biology, Evolution and Ecology of the National Academy of Sciences.

name: Patrick, William
description: Scottish clergyman and botanist.

name: Patterson, Flora (née Wambaugh)
description: American mycologist; married Edward Patterson 12 Aug 1869; A.M. Wesleyan Coll., Cincinatti 1882; id. Univ. Iowa 1895; at Radcliffe Coll., Harvard 1892-1895; pathologist, later mycologist, in the U.S. Dept. of Agriculture 1896-1923; in retirement in Brooklyn, N.Y.

name: Patterson, Harry Norton
description: American printer, botanist and explorer, editor proprietor of the Oquawka [Ill.]. Spectator 1884-1908

name: Patterson, Paul Morrison
description: American bryologist; A.M. Univ. N. Carolina 1927; asst. prof. botany Davidson Coll. 1927-1928; assoc. prof. S. Carolina Univ. 19301933; Dr. phil. Hopkins Univ. 1933; from 1934-1966 prof. biology Hollins College, Va.

name: Pattison, Samuel Rowles
description: British palaeobotanist of Launceston, Cornwall.

name: Patze, Carl August
description: German (Berlin) botanist and pharmacist; from 1830-1836 in pharmacies in Berlin and Charlottenburg (1829-1830 in Breslau); from 1837-1874 owner of a pharmacy in Königsberg i. Pr.

name: Patzelt, Joseph Eduard
description: Austrian botanist and physician in Wien, later in Bucarest.

name: Pau [y Español], Carlos
description: Spanish botanist and pharmacist at Segorbe.

page_title_longer_max-80: Paul, Hermann Karl Gustav [std. H. Paul]
name: Paul, Hermann Karl Gustav
description: German bryologist; student of A. Engler; Dr. phil. Berlin 1902; assistant at the Kön. bayerischen Moorversuchsstation Bernau, Bayern, 1902-ca. 1943.

name: Paulet, Jean Jacques
description: French physician and mycologist. Studied medicine at Montpellier; Dr. med. ib. 1764; practicing physician in Paris 1764-1802; in retirement at Fontainebleau.

name: Paulin, Alphons
description: Austrian botanist in Slovenia; director of the botanical garden of the University of Ljubljana (Laibach) 1886-1931; Dr. phil. Graz 1880.

name: Paull, Charles Leslie Fairbanks
description: American botanist, AM Brown Univ. 1898, assistant Kansas State College 1902-1904; from 1904 with the USDA Bureau of Plant Industry.

name: Paulli [Pauli], Johan
description: Danish botanist and physician in Copenhagen.

name: Paulsen, Ove Vilhelm
description: Danish botanist; M.Sc. Copenhagen 1897; Dr. phil. ib. 1911; in the Danish West Indies 1895-1896, on the Pamir expedition 1898-1899; from 1900-1918 curator at the Botanical Museum, Copenhagen; professor of botany at the Danish pharmaceutical college 1920-1944.

name: Paulson, Robert
description: British school teacher, mycologist and lichenologist in London.

name: Pauquy, Charles Louis Constant
description: French botanist and physician; studied at Paris; practicing physician at Amiens.

name: Pauwels, Jan Lodewijk Huibrecht
description: Belgian linguist; Dr. phil. Leuven 1923; professor of Dutch linguistics ib. from 1942.

name: Pavillard, Jules
description: French diatomologist, protistologist and phytogeographer; Lic. sci. nat. Bordeaux 1890; Dr. sci. Paris 1905; high school teacher at Montpel- lier 1895-1912; maître de conférences (1908), professeur adjoint (1909), professeur de cryptogamie et de cytologie (1924) and from 1927-1937, professor of botany and direc- tor of the botanical garden at the University of Montpellier, succeeding Ch. Flahault.

name: Pavlov, Nikolai Vasilievich
description: Russian botanist at the Academy of Sciences of Kazakhstan at Alma Ata; specialist on Allium, Astragalus and Artemisia.

page_title_longer_max-80: Pavon y Jiménez, José Antonio [std. Pav.]
name: Pavon y Jiménez, José Antonio
description: Spanish botanist; with H. Ruiz in South America 1778-1788.

name: Pawlowski, Bogumil
description: Polish botanist; Dr. phil. Craców 1922; at the Botanical Institute of the Polish Academy of Sciences, Craców; specialist on the floras of Poland and the Balkan peninsula.

name: Pax, Ferdinand Albin
description: German botanist (born in Bohemia); Dr. phil. Breslau 1882; assistant with A. Engler at Kiel 1883-1884; with id. to Breslau 1884 as lecturer, from 1889-1893 again with Engler at Berlin; from 1893-1925 professor of botany and director of the botanical garden at Breslau; one of the most productive of Engler's collaborators.

name: Paxton, [Sir] Joseph
description: British horticulturist, editor, landscape gardener, railroad promotor and speculator, builder of glass structures (Crystal Palace), architect, civil engineer, and politician; knighted 1851.

name: Payer, Jean-Baptiste
description: French botanist; Dr. sci. nat. Paris 1840, Dr. med. Paris 1852; teacher at the École normale, and, from 1852, at the Faculté de Médecine, Paris; in politics and administration 1848-1851.

name: Payne, Frederick William
description: British diatomist; schoolmaster at the Brighton Grammar School 1873-1876; at the City of London School, 1876-1919; BA London 1871.

name: Payot, Venance
description: French (Savoie) commercial naturalist and mountain guide; local administrator and botanist at Chamonix; botanical explorer of the Mont Blanc region.

name: Payrau, Vincent
description: French botanist and pharmacist, Dr. pharm., Paris, 1900, resident pharmacist of the Paris hospitals.

name: Payson, Edwin Blake
description: American botanist; Dr. phil. Univ. Washington 1921; BA Univ. Wyoming 1917; professor of botany Univ. Wyoming 1921-1927.

name: Peacock, John T.
description: British country gentleman of Sudbury House, Hammersmith; collector of succulent plants.

name: Pearl, Raymond
description: American botanist, entomologist, student of human populations, teacher and editor; Ph.D. Univ. Mich. 1902; instructor in zoology Univ. Michigan 1902-1905, in London 1905-1906, at Univ. Pennsylvania 1906-1907; head dept. biol. Maine Agric. Exp. Station 1907-1918; professor of biometry and vital statistics Johns Hopkins, Baltimore 1918-1925; director Institute of Biological Research ib. 1925-1930; professor of biology ib. 1930-1940; D.Sc. Dartmouth 1919.

name: Pearsall, William Harrison
description: British schoolmaster and botanist at Dalton-in-Furness until 1925; retired to Kent; secretary of the Botanical Society of the British Isles 1931-1936.

name: Pearson, Arthur Anselm
description: British businessman and mycologist at Cleckheaton; authority on agarics; treasurer of the British mycological Society 1919-1946, president 1931, 1952.

page_title_longer_max-80: Pearson, Henry Harold Welch [std. H. Pearson]
name: Pearson, Henry Harold Welch
description: English botanist; M.A. Cambridge 1900, D. Sc. ib. 1907; assistant curator Cambridge herbarium 1898-1899; assistant for India at Kew 1899-1903; from 1903-1916 Harry Bolus professor of botany at the South African College, Cape Town; founder of the Kirstenbosch National Botanic Gardens of South Africa.

name: Pearson, William Henry
description: British businessman (yarn agent) and hepaticologist at Eccles nr. Manchester; from 1902 at Manchester; one of the founders of the British Bryological Society; M.Sc. Manchester 1911.

name: Pease, Arthur Stanley
description: American classicist and botanist; A.B. Univ. Illinois 1902; Ph. D. Harvard 1906; taught Latin and Greek at Harvard (1906-1909), Univ. Illinois (1909-1924), Amherst Coll. (1924-1926), Harvard (1932-1950); president Amherst College (1927-1932); active plant collector, made trip around the world 19261927.

name: Peattie, Donald Culross
description: American botanist; studied at Univ. Chicago (1915-1917; no degree).

name: Peck, Charles Horton
description: American botanist; A.B. Union Coll. (Schenectady, N.Y.) 1859, M.A. ib. 1862, D. Sc. hon. ib. 1908; high school teacher at Sandlake Collegiate Inst. 1852-1855 and 1859-1862; id. at Albany 1862; Botanist at the State Cabinet of natural History of New York 1867-1883; State Botanist of New York 1883- 1915.

page_title_longer_max-80: Peck, Franz Gustav Magnus [std. F. Peck]
name: Peck, Franz Gustav Magnus
description: German (Niederlausitz) botanist at Görlitz; studied law at Berlin; from 1839-1843 law court official (Kammergerichtsrefer- endar, "Auskultator") at Görlitz; 1843-1845 id. Berlin; from 1845 judge at various stat- ions, ultimately president of the district court at Schweidnitz 1867-1883; from 1884-1892 in retirement at Görlitz.

name: Peck, Morton Eaton
description: American botanist; B.A. Cornell College, Iowa, 1895; at Willamette University, Salem, Oregon 1908-1941, ultimately as chairman of the Department of Biology; botanical explorer of British Honduras and, for over fifty years, of Oregon; D. Sc. Cornell 1940, LL.D. Willamette 1955.

name: Peck, William Dandridge
description: American botanist and entomologist; B.A. Harvard 1782; first professor of natural history at Harvard 1805-1822.

name: Peckolt, Theodor
description: German (Niederlausitz) botanist; trained as a pharmacist in Triebel, 1837-1841; settled in Brazil 1847; practicing pharmacist in Rio de Janeiro 1848; exploring the province of Rio de Janeiro 1848-1850; pharmacist at Cantagallo 1851-1867; id. again in Rio de Janeiro from 1868 ("pharmacia e drugeria Peckolt").

name: Pedicino, Nicola Antonio
description: Italian diatomologist; teacher at a technical college at Napoli; from 1872-1877 at the agricultural college and director of its botanical garden at Portici nr. Napoli; from 1877-1883 professor of botany and director of the botanical garden at Roma, succeeding De Notaris.

name: Peekel, Gerhard
description: German missionary and plant collector; ord. 1902 Hiltrup; from 1904 in the Bismarck Archipelago; from 1908 at New Mecklenburg (New Ireland).

name: Pée-Laby, E.
description: French algologist; Dr. Sci; assistant at the botany department of the Faculté des Sciences, Toulouse

name: Pehersdorfer, Anna
description: Austrian botanist, teacher at a girl's college in Steyr.

name: P'ei Chien
description: Chinese botanist; AB Stanford 1927; AM ib. 1928, studied in U.S. 1925-1930, later at the Biological Laboratory of the Science Society of China, Nanking.

name: Peirce, George James
description: Manila-born (of American parents) American botanist; Dr. phil. Leipzig 1894 (with Pfeffer); instructor in botany, Bloomington, Ind. 1895; plant physiologist at Stanford from 1897-1934; all-round botanist; studied the effect of air pollution on plants.

name: Peirson, Frank Warrington
description: American botanist and plant collector, from 1902 realtor at Altadena, Calif.; AB Haverford 1889, AM ib. 1890; plant collector in the Pacific States.

name: Pellanda, Giuseppe
description: Italian botanist.

name: Pellegrin, François
description: French botanist; from 1912 at the Museum d'Histoire naturelle, Paris; Dr. Sci. Paris 1908; Croix de Guerre 1914-1918.

name: Pelletan, Jules
description: French microscopist and diatomist.

name: Pelletier, [Pierre] Joseph
description: French botanist and pharmacist at Paris; Dr. Sci. Paris 1812, active at the École de pharmacie at Paris from 1814.

page_title_long: Pelloe, Emily Harriet (Mrs. Theodore Pelloe, née Sundercombe)
page_title_longer_max-80: Pelloe, Emily Harriet (Mrs. Theodore Pelloe, née Sundercombe) [std. Pelloe]
name: Pelloe, Emily Harriet (Mrs. Theodore Pelloe, née Sundercombe)
name_ed: Pelloe, Emily Harriet (Mrs. Theodore Pelloe, née Sundercombe)
description: Australian botanist and artist, living mainly in Western Australia from 1901.

name: Pelourde, Fernand
description: French palaeobotanist; Dr. phil. Paris 1907; "préparateur" at the Muséum d'Histoire naturelle, Paris

name: Pena, Pierre
description: French botanist and physician; collaborated with L'Obel at Montpellier (1565) and in England 1566-1572); from then onward practicing physician in France, ultimately as chief physician of Henri III.

name: Peña, Rafael
description: Bolivian botanist.

name: Penard, Eugène
description: Swiss protozoologist, botanist and author of children's books; bank employee at Genève 1872-1881; studied at Edinburgh, Heidelberg and Genève; Dr. Sci. Genève 1888; in Colorado 1891; from 1892-1898 private tutor in Germany and Russia; from 1898 private scientist in Genève; one of the founders of the Société botanique de Genève.

name: Penfold, [Mrs.] Jane Wallas
description: British botanical artist and naturalist; lived in Madeira.

name: Penhallow, Davis Pearce
description: American actuo– and palaeobotanist; B.S. Amherst Agr. Coll. 1873; professor of botany and chemistry at the College of Agriculture, Sapporo (Japan) 1876-1880; at Harvard 1880-1882; at the Houghton Experi- mental Farm, N.Y., 1882-1883; from 1883-1910 professor of botany at McGill Univers- ity, Montreal; D.Sc. Montreal 1904.

name: Penland, Charles William Theodore
description: American botanist; and ecologist; professor of botany at Colorado College (Boulder) from 1922.

name: Pennant, Thomas
description: British zoologist and antiquary; sheriff of Flintshire; gentleman-naturalist; correspondent of Linnaeus.

name: Pennell, Francis Whittier
description: American botanist; travelled and collected widely in the Americas; president of the Philadelphia botanical Club 1942-1952; Ph.D. Univ. Pennsylvania 1913; associate curator at NY 1914-1921; from 1921 Curator of botany at PH; eminent authority on Scrophulariaceae, botanical historian and bibliographer.

page_title_longer_max-80: Pennier de Longchamp, Pierre Barthélemy [std. Pennier]
name: Pennier de Longchamp, Pierre Barthélemy
description: French mycologist and physician at Avignon

name: Pennington, Leigh H [Humboldt]
description: American phytopathologist and mycologist; B.A. Univ. Mich. 1907, Dr. phil. 1909; from 1910 at Syracuse University as professor of botany, from 1914-1929 as head of the dept. of forest botany.

page_title_long: Penzig, Albert Julius Otto [later Alberto Giulio Ottone]
page_title_longer_max-80: Penzig, Albert Julius Otto [later Alberto Giulio Ottone] [std. Penz.]
name: Penzig, Albert Julius Otto [later: Alberto Giulio Ottone]
name_ed: Penzig, Albert Julius Otto [later Alberto Giulio Ottone]
description: German (Silesian) botanist, from 1878 in Italy, Italian citizen 1882; Dr. phil. Breslau 1877; at Pavia with Garovaglio 1878-1879; with Saccardo at Padua 1879-1883; at the Stazione agronomica, Modena 1883-1886; professor of botany and director of the botanical garden, Genova 1887 (Jan)-1929; in Java Nov 1896-Apr 1897.

name: Peola, Paolo
description: Italian palaeobotanist; teacher at the Genova Technical Institute.

name: Pepoon, Herman Silas
description: American botanist; head instructor in botany and agriculture, Lake View High School, Chicago, Ill.

name: Peragallo, Hippolyte
description: French diatomologist.

name: Peragallo, Maurice
description: French diatomologist; brother of H. Peragallo.

name: Pérard, Alexandre Jules César
description: French botanist; bank-clerk, later high school teacher at Montluçon.

name: Pereboom, Cornells
description: Dutch physician and botanist at Amsterdam.

name: Pereboom, Nicolaas Ewoud
description: Dutch botanist, son of Cornells Pereboom.

name: Pereira, Huascar
description: Brazilian botanist.

name: Pérez Arbeláez, Enrique
description: Colombian botanist; Dr. phil. Burgos 1918; Dr. theol. ib. 1926; Dr. Sci. München 1928.

page_title_longer_max-80: Pérez Lara, José María [std. Pérez Lara]
name: Pérez Lara, José María
description: Spanish botanist, studied at Sevilla; B.A. 1862; expelled from the University 1863; henceforth living on his ample private means at Jerez.

name: Perini, Carlo
description: Italian physician and botanist; Dr. med. Padua; practicing at Triest.

name: Perkins, Mrs. E.E.
description: British botanist at Chelsea; "professor of botanical flower painting" (t.p. Elem. bot.).

name: Perkins, George Henry
description: American botanist, zoologist and geologist; Dr. phil. at Yale 1869, from 1869-1933 at the University of Vermont in various positions, incl. 56 years as curator of the University Museum; vice-president of the University 1907-1931; State geologist of Vermont 1898-1933; LL.D. Univ. Vermont 1911, Litt. D. Knox College 1912.

name: Perkins, Janet Russell
description: American botanist; studied at the Univ. of Wisconsin 1867-1871; private teacher in Hildesheim and studying music and languages at Paris 1871-1874; from 1875-1895 private teacher at Chicago and (for three years) travelling in Europe California, Açores and Hawaii; to Berlin, studying botany e.g. with Engler, Gilg, and Kny 1895-1898; at Heidelberg 1898; again at Berlin as voluntary associate of Engler from 1898; Dr. phil. Heidelberg 1900.

name: Perktold, Josef Anton
description: Austrian cryptogamist and clergyman; entered the Praemonstratenser Convent of Wilten 1825 (baptismal name Anton); ordained 1829; clergyman at Tarrenz 1829-1830, Ellbögen nr. Innsbruck 1830-1840, Tulfes 18341836, Vill 1836-1842, Igels 1842-1852, ultimately again at Wilten as canon of its Convent.

name: Perleb, Karl [Carl] Julius
description: German botanist and physician; professor of natural history at the university of Freiburg in Breisgau 1818-1845; director of the botanical garden ibid. 1828-1845.

page_title_longer_max-80: Pernhoffer, Gustav, Edler von Bärnkron [std. Pernh.]
name: Pernhoffer, Gustav, Edler von Bärnkron
description: Austrian amateur botanist; friend of A. Kerner v. Marilaun.

name: Pernitzsch, Heinrich
description: German (Saxonian) forester and botanist at Heidelbach (Sachsen); "königlicher Sächs. Oberförster".

name: Perreymond, Jean Honoré
description: French botanist, school inspector and music composer at Fréjus.

name: Perrier, Alfred
description: French botanist; Dr. med. Paris 1835; from 1836 practicing physician and amateur naturalist at Caen.

page_title_long: Perrier de la Bâthie, Eugène Pierre [baron] de
page_title_longer_max-80: Perrier de la Bâthie, Eugène Pierre [baron] de [std. E. Perrier]
name: Perrier de la Bâthie, Eugène Pierre [baron] de
name_ed: Perrier de la Bâthie, Eugène Pierre [baron] de
description: French landowner, agronomist and botanist at Conflans (Albertville), Savoie; professor of agriculture at Albertville 1875-1900.

page_title_long: Perrier de la Bâthie, [Joseph Marie] Henri [Alfred]
page_title_longer_max-80: Perrier de la Bâthie, [Joseph Marie] Henri [Alfred] [std. H. Perrier]
name: Perrier de la Bâthie, [Joseph Marie] Henri [Alfred]
name_ed: Perrier de la Bâthie, [Joseph Marie] Henri [Alfred]
description: French botanist; nephew of E. Perrier; soldier in Indochina (Tonkin), from 1896-1933 living in Madagascar (1914-1918 in the French army in Europe), later in Paris.

page_title_long: Perrin, Ida Southwell (née Robins; Mrs. Henry Perrin)
page_title_longer_max-80: Perrin, Ida Southwell (née Robins; Mrs. Henry Perrin) [std. Perrin]
name: Perrin, Ida Southwell (née Robins; Mrs. Henry Perrin),
name_ed: Perrin, Ida Southwell (née Robins; Mrs. Henry Perrin)
description: British popular writer on botany and botanical artist.

name: Perrine, Henry
description: American botanist; introduced many tropical plants into the southern U.S.; consul at Campeachy, Yucatan, 1827-1831, 1832-1837, at Key West (Indian Key) from 1937.

name: Perrot, Émile Constant
description: French pharmacist, anatomist and botanist; Dr. sci. Paris 1899; succeeded G. Planchon as professor of materia medica at the École de Pharmacie, Paris, 1899, (aggrégé; prof. tit. 1902)-1937; Dr. h.c. Univ. Utrecht 1945.

name: Perrottet, George (Georges Guerrard) Samuel
description: Swiss-born French gardener, sericiculturist, agronomical botanist, traveller and director of tropical cultures; in the "Rhône" around the world 1819-1821; Sénégal 1824-1829; in Pondichéry 1834-1839 and, ultimately, as government botanist from 1843-1870.

name: Perroud, Louis François
description: French botanist; Dr. med. Paris 1858; connected with the Faculté de Médecine and hospital physician at Lyon from 1860-1889.

name: Perry, Lily May
description: Canadian-born American botanist; Dr. phil. Wash. Univ., St. Louis 1932; at Gray Herbarium 1925-1932, University of Georgia 1932-1934, Sweet Briar College 1934-1935; later at Arnold Arboretum

name: Perry, William Groves
description: British bookseller and botanist, curator of the Warwickshire Museum at Warwick.

name: Persoon, Christiaan Hendrik
description: South African botanist (Dutch citizen), especially mycologist, who was educated (high school) at Lingen; studied theology at Halle 1783-1786, and medicine and natural sciences at Göttingen 1787-1802; Dr. phil. Leopoldina 1799; lived in Paris 1802-1836; left his herbarium and library to the Dutch government after having exchanged his earlier herbarium in 1828 for an annual pension with the same government.

name: Persson, Nathan Petter Herman
description: Swedish physician and bryologist; Dr. phil. h.c. Stockholm 1945; in various functions (1947-1969 as curator) at the Naturhistoriska Riksmuseum, Stockholm.

name: Perty, Joseph Anton Maximilian
description: German botanist and zoologist; Dr. med. Landshut 1826; Dr. phil. Erlangen 1828; habil. München 1831; at München until 1833; from 1833-1876 professor of zoology at Bern.

name: Pescott, Edward Edgar
description: Australian botanist, pomologist and historian; principal of a school of horticulture at Burley, Victoria 1909-1916; from 1917-1937 government pomologist and seed-tester in the victorian Department of Agriculture.

name: Pestalozzi, Anton
description: Swiss botanist; assistant to the botanical museum at Zürich 1896.

name: Petagna, Luigi
description: Italian botanist and entomologist at Napoli; from 1812 professor of zoology, from 1813 also director of the Museo zoologico Napoli of the University of Napoli.

name: Petagna, Vincenzo
description: Italian botanist, physician and entomologist; professor of botany and director of the Monteoliveto botanical garden at Napoli.

name: Petch, Thomas
description: British botanist (plant pathologist and mycologist) and schoolteacher at King's Lynn and Leyton; at the Royal Botanic Gardens, Peradeniya, Ceylon (Sri Lanka) 1905-1925; director Tea research institute of Ceylon 1925-1928.

name: Pételot, [Paul] Alfred
description: French botanist; assistant at the Faculté des sciences, Nancy, 1908-1918; teacher at the Hanoi high school (lycée) 1918-1922; director of the entomological station of Cho-gangh 1922-1924; professor of botany at the Indochina University from 1924.

name: Peter, [Gustav] Albert
description: German (Prussian) botanist; Dr. phil. Königsberg 1874; private tutor at München 1874-1884 and working with Nägeli on Hieracium; habil. München 1884; "Custos" at the botanical garden, München 1884-1888; professor of botany and director of the botanical garden Göttingen 1888-1923; in retirement working at a Flora von Deutsch-Ostafrika.

name: Péterfi, Márton [Martin]
description: Hungarian (Transylvanian) botanist, especially bryologist; school teacher at Deva, from 1906 at Cluj; curator of the National Transilvanian Museum from 1908.

name: Petermann, Wilhelm Ludwig
description: German (Saxonian) botanist; habil. Leipzig 1835; suceeded Kunze as professor of botany in 1851.

name: Peters, Karl [Carl]
description: German (Prussian) botanist and gardener at Berlin and Berlin-Dahlem; from 1886-1925, subsequently as Reviergehilfe, Öbergärtner (1894), Garteninspektor (1907), and Oberinspektor (1913).

page_title_longer_max-80: Peters, Wilhelm Carl Hartwig [std. W. Peters]
name: Peters, Wilhelm Carl Hartwig
description: German (Schleswig) zoologist, physician and traveller; 1842-1848 in S. and E. Africa and India; professor of medicine Berlin 1851; professor of zoology ibid. 1856.

name: Petersen, Hans
description: German (Schleswig) botanist and high school teacher at Sonderburg on Alsen (now Als) from 1862-1894; from 1895-1927 living in retirement at Schwesing (Husum).

name: Petersen, Henning Eiler [Ejler]
description: Danish botanist, mainly mycologist and algologist; M.Sc. København 1902; Dr. phil. ib. 1914; lecturer at the Polyteknisk Laereanstalt 1916-1930; lecturer ("docent") at University of Copenhagen 1929-1946.

name: Petersen, Johannes Boye
description: Danish algologist; assistant at the Polyteknisk Laereanstalt 1916-1929, lecturer ib. 1929-1951; (cryptogamic "amanuensis") at the Copenhagen botanic garden 1920-1951; professor of botany at Copenhagen University 1951-1958.

name: Petersen, Karl
description: German botanist.

name: Petersen, Niels Frederick
description: Danish-born American botanist; grew up in Plainview, Nebraska; M.S. Univ. Nebraska 1911, instructor of botany at Baton Rouge 1909-1913; in Panama 1914; at Univ. of Chicago 1915-1916; at Nevada Experiment Station 1917-1920; from 1921 at Nebraska Experiment Station; later settling again at Plainview, Nebr.

name: Petersen, Otto Georg
description: Danish botanist, Dr. phil. Kjøbenhavn 1882; with the Botanical Museum 1878-1882, from 1882-1893 in various functions at the University and the Botanical Garden; from 1893-1902 lecturer, from 1902-1919 professor of botany at the Copenhagen Agricultural College.

name: Petersen, [Lorents Christian] Severin
description: Danish mycologist, schoolmaster at Slotsbjergby near Slagelse, later at Sorø.

name: Pethybridge, George Herbert
description: British botanist (phytopathologist); Ph. D. Göttingen 1899; with Department of Agriculture and Royal College of Science at Dublin from 1900, Economic Botanist 1908-1923; mycologist and asst. director of the Plant Pathology Lab., Harpenden, 1923-1936; O.B.E. 1937.

page_title_long: Petif [de la Gautrois], Johann Friedrich Carl Ludwig Corentin
page_title_longer_max-80: Petif [de la Gautrois], Johann Friedrich Carl Ludwig Corentin [std. Petif]
name: Petif [de la Gautrois], Johann Friedrich Carl Ludwig Corentin
name_ed: Petif [de la Gautrois], Johann Friedrich Carl Ludwig Corentin
description: German (Württemberg) botanist; Dr. med. Stuttgart; private tutor in Graubünden 1787-1789; municipal physician at Tuttlingen 1789-1802; director of a madder factory at Mussbach bei Neustadt (Pfalz) 1802-ca. 1834; from 1834-1839 at Haardt (ib.); from 1839-1845 with his daughter at Zeist (Netherlands).

page_title_long: Petit, Emil Charles Nicolai [Nicolai Emil Charles]
page_title_longer_max-80: Petit, Emil Charles Nicolai [Nicolai Emil Charles] [std. Petit, E.]
name: Petit, Emil Charles Nicolai [Nicolai Emil Charles]
name_ed: Petit, Emil Charles Nicolai [Nicolai Emil Charles]
description: Danish botanist and physician; one of the founders of "Det Naturhistoriske Selskab" (later Botanisk Forening); schoolteacher from 1843-1848; military physician 1841-1852; practicing physician 1848-1852; id. in Fredensborg 1852-1873; living at Copenhagen from 1878.

page_title_longer_max-80: Petit, Paul Charles Mirbel [std. P. Petit]
name: Petit, Paul Charles Mirbel
description: French pharmacist and algologist, esp. diatomologist.

name: Petitmengin, Marcel Georges Charles
description: French botanist; curator of botany (préparateur) at the Pharmaceutical college of Nancy; travelled in Greece with R. Maire (1906).

name: Petit-Radel, Philippe
description: French botanist.

name: Petiver, James
description: British botanist, entomologist and apothecary to the Charterhouse; demonstrator at Chelsea (1709), owner of an important natural history cabinet.

name: Petkoff [Petkov], Stefan Pavlikianoff
description: Bulgarian botanist; habil. Sofia 1901; from 1906 professor of botany and director of the botanical garden of Sofia, ord. prof. 1911-1936.

name: Petrak, Franz
description: Austrian mycologist, born in Mährisch-Weisskirchen (later Hranice); studied in Vienna from 1906-1910 with R. von Wettstein; Dr. sci. ib. 1913; high school teacher in Wien until 1916; in the Austrian Army 1916-1918; from 19181938; living as a private scientist in his home town selling exsiccatae; at the Naturh. Museum, Wien 1938-1951; travelled in the United States Apr 1950-Feb 1951.

name: Petrescu, Constantin C.
description: Roumanian botanist at Iasi, published on the flora of the Dobragea (Dobruja) and Moldavia; with the Botanical laboratory, Iasi, from 1911 (preparator), 1914 (assistant), 1920 (head assistant) until 1936.

name: Petri, Friedrich
description: German (Berlin) botanist; Dr. phil. Berlin 1863; pupil of A. Braun; from 1864-1896 teacher at the high school (Realschule) of Luisenstadt (Berlin; 1865 ordentlicher Lehrer, 1875 Oberlehrer, 1884 Professor); in his later years especially active in chemical technology and hygienics.

name: Petri, Lionello
description: Italian botanist.

name: Petrie, Donald
description: Scottish botanist; M.A. Aberdeen 1867; to Australia 1868, teacher at Scotch College, Melbourne; inspector of schools Otago prov. govt., New Zealand 1874; chief inspector of schools, Auckland 1894.

name: Petrov, Vsevolod Alexeevic
description: Russian botanist.

name: Petrovic, Sava
description: Serbian botanist; educated at Belgrad and Paris (Faculté de médecine), M.D. 1868; physician to King Milan 1873; "Sanitätsoberst" (military physician) at Belgrad.

name: Petrowsky [Petrowski, Petrovsky], Andrei [Andreas] Stanislavovic
description: Russian botanist; high school teacher at Jaroslaw.

name: Petry, Arthur
description: German botanist; high school teacher at Nordhausen.

name: Petter, Franz
description: Austrian botanist; from 1823 high school teacher (German language) at Spalato (Central Dalmatia).

name: Petters, Franz
description: Bohemian botanist and clergyman; ordin. 1807; in various clergical positions at Schönwalde and Kratzau (Kragau); correspondent of Opiz.

name: Petterson, Bror Johan
description: Finnish botanist, curator at the Botanical Museum, University of Helsinki 1959-1965; travelled in the Canary Islands 1947, 1949, 1951 and Sudan & Egypt 1962.

name: Petunnikov, Alexej Nikolaievic
description: Russian amateur botanist at Moscow.

name: Petzholdt, Georg Paul Alexander
description: German (Saxonian) botanist, published on palaeobotany, agriculture and peat research; originally physician at Dresden; from 1846 professor of agronomy and technology at Dorpat (Tartu); later in retirement at Freiburg i. Br.

name: Petzi, Franz von Sales
description: German (Bavarian) botanist; studied mathematics and physics at München; high school teacher at the Regensburg Gymnasium; editor and curator of the herbarium of the Regensburgische botanische Gesellschaft.

name: Petzold, [Carl] Eduard Adolph
description: German (Prussian) botanist and gardener; trained in practice at Matzdorf (1835-1838); and Neuenhof (1838-1840); at the forestry school of Eisenach 1840-1844; Hofgärtner at Ettersburg (1844-1848), and Weimar (1848-1852); from 1852-1881 director of the garden at Muskau (W. Schlesien); in retirement at Blasewitz (Sachsen) 1882-1891.

name: Petzold, [Karl] Wilhelm
description: German (Saxonian) botanist and geologist; Dr. phil. Halle 1876; in the campaign in France 1870-1871; high school teacher at NeuBrandenburg 1874-1877, id. at Weisenburg i. E. (Wissembourg) 1877-1879, id. at Braunschweig 1880-1897.

name: Peyl, Josef
description: Bohemian garden director at Kacina near Kuttenberg (Kutná Hora); published mainly on fungi.

name: Peyre, B.L.
description: French botanist, army surgeon with the 18th "Régiment d'Infanterie de Ligne".

name: Peyritsch, Johann Joseph
description: Austrian botanist, especially plant teratologist; Dr. med. Wien 1864; naval physician at Pola 1864-1866; from 1866-1871 con- nected with the Vienna general hospital; from 1871-1878 at the Natural History museum ("2. custos"); habil. Univ. Wien 1874; professor of botany at Innsbruck (suc- cessor to A. Kerner) 1878-1889; especially interested in plant teratology and Laboul- beniales.

name: Peyronel, Beniamino
description: Italian mycologist at the Istituto botanico dell'Università, Torina

name: Pfeffer, Wilhelm Friedrich Philipp
description: German (Hesse-Nassau) plant physiologist, pharmacist, chemist and bryologist; Dr. phil. Göttingen 1865; assistant pharmacist in Chur 1865-1869; with Pringsheim in Berlin 1869-1870; with Sachs at Würzburg 1870-1871; habil. Marburg 1871, "dozent" ib. 1871-1873; professor of botany Bonn 1873-1877, at Basel 1877, at Tübingen 1878-1887; ultimately director of the botanical garden and of the plant physiology laboratory at Leipzig 1887-1920; leading plant physiologist of his era.

name: Pfeiffer, Hans Heinrich
description: German biosystematic botanist; Dr. phil. Washington, D.C.; specialist on Cyperaceae; ultimately at Bremen.

name: Pfeiffer, Johan Philip
description: Dutch chemical engineer, botanist and forester; Dr. phil. 1917; wood technologist at Semarang, Java 1912-1920; manager of an oil factory at Kediri, Java, 1920-1922; lecturer and professor at Delft technical College 1922-1929; from 1929 with the Batavian Oil Company at Amsterdam.

page_title_longer_max-80: Pfeiffer, Louis [later Ludwig] Karl Georg [std. Pfeiff.]
name: Pfeiffer, Louis [later: Ludwig] Karl Georg
description: German (Hesse-Nassau) botanist and malacologist; Dr. med. Marburg 1825; practicing physician at Kassel 18261833; military physician in Poland 1831; from 1833 active as Privatgelehrter; travelled to Cuba 1838-1839; Dr. phil. h.c. Marburg 1875.

name: Pfeiffer, Norma Etta
description: American botanist; Ph.D. Univ. Chicago 1913; taught at the University of North Dakota from 1913-1923, at the University of Wisconsin 19231932; at the Boyce Thompson Institute, Yonkers, N.Y. 1924-1954; in retirement living in Dallas, Texas.

name: Pfeil, Friedrich Wilhelm Leopold
description: German (Prussian) forestry botanist; in active service during the Napoleonic wars 1813-1815; administrator of the property of the princess of Carolath in Silezia 1815; director of the Berlin Forestry College 1821; founder and director of the forestry school of Neustadt-Eberswalde, 1830-1859.

name: Pfitzer, Ernst Hugo Heinrich
description: German (Prussian) botanist; Dr. phil. Königsberg 1867; habil. Bonn 1868; from 1868-1872 at Bonn; from 1872-1906 professor of botany and director of the botanical garden at Heidelberg; outstanding orchidologist.

name: Pflaum, Fritz
description: German (Bavarian) botanist; Dr. phil. München 1897.

name: Pfuhl, Fritz C.A.
description: German (Pommeranian/Prussian) botanist and high school teacher at the Marien Gymnasium at Posen (now Poznan, Poland).

name: Pfund, Johann Daniel Christian
description: German botanist; born in Hamburg; practicing physician in Prague, from 1842-1845 also custos at PR; later physician in Alexandria, Egypt; collected in the Nile valley; died on a trip to Nubia, Kordofan and Darfur 1874-1876.

name: Phares, David Lewis
description: American botanist, active in Mississippi.

page_title_long: Phelps, Almira (previously Lincoln, née Hart or Heart)
page_title_longer_max-80: Phelps, Almira (previously Lincoln, née Hart or Heart) [std. A. Phelps]
name: Phelps, Almira (previously Lincoln, née Hart or Heart)
name_ed: Phelps, Almira (previously Lincoln, née Hart or Heart)
description: American popular writer on botany and teacher at the Troy Female Seminary; from 1838-1841 in charge of a seminary in West Chester, Pa., from 1841 id. of the Patapsco Female Institute, Ellicott City, Md.; married Samuel Lincoln 1817, John Phelps 1831.

name: Phelps, William
description: British clergyman, topographer and botanist; B.A. Oxford 1797, rector at Oxcombe 1851.

name: Phelsum, Murk [Mark, Murck] van
description: Dutch naturalist; Dr. med. Franeker 1755; practicing physician at Sneek, Friesland, from 1764.

name: Philibert, Henri
description: French bryologist; educated at the École normale supérieure, Agr. phil. 1846; Dr. lit. 1865; high school teacher at Avignon, Pau, Grenoble, Montpellier, Chaumont, Angoulême 1843-1867; lecturer in philosophy at the Faculté des lettres, Aix-en-Provence 1867-1882; hon. professor, in retirement, from 1883.

name: Philibert, J.C.
description: French botanist.

name: Philip, Robert Harris
description: British diatomist at Hull.

name: Philippar, François Haken [Aken]
description: Austrian-born botanist (of French parents); professor at the national agricultural college of Grignon, 1830, and at the "École normale primaire" at Versailles, 1832; founder of the "Jardin des Plantes de Versailles".

page_title_longer_max-80: Philippe, Xavier (earlier Philippe Xavier Camus) [std. Philippe]
name: Philippe, Xavier (earlier: Philippe Xavier Camus)
description: French naturalist, municipal librarian and plant salesman living at Bagnères-de-Bigorre.

page_title_longer_max-80: Philippi, Federico (baptized Friedrich Heinrich Eunom) [std. F. Philippi]
name: Philippi, Federico (baptized Friedrich Heinrich Eunom)
description: Chilean botanist and entomologist of German origin (born in Napoli), son of R.A. Philippi, whom he succeeded in 1874 as professor of botany at Santiago; from 1897 also director of the Museo nacional (de Chile).

page_title_long: Philippi, Rudolph [Rudolf; later called Rodolfo Amando] Amandus
page_title_longer_max-80: Philippi, Rudolph [Rudolf; later called Rodolfo Amando] Amandus [std. Phil.]
name: Philippi, Rudolph [Rudolf; later called Rodolfo Amando] Amandus
name_ed: Philippi, Rudolph [Rudolf; later called Rodolfo Amando] Amandus
description: German (Prussian) botanist, studied in Berlin, Dr. phil. 1830, teacher at the technical school at Kassel 1835-1838, 1840-1851; in Italy 1830-1832, 1838-1840; emigrated to Chile 1851; at first as farmer and teacher at Valdivia; professor of botany and zoology at Santiago from 1853-1874, until 1897 director of the Museo nacional (de Chile).

name: Phillips, Edwin Percy
description: South African botanist; Dr. sci. Univ. Cape 1915; with the South African Museum at Capetown 1917-1918; from 1918-1944 at the National Herbarium, Pretoria (chief (1939-1944).

name: Phillips, Henry
description: British botanist and horticultural writer; banker at Worthing, later living in London and Brighton.

name: Phillips, John
description: British geologist and palaeobotanist; curator of the York Museum 1824-1840; professor of geology, Trinity Coll., Dublin 1844-1853; keeper Ashmolean museum, Oxford 1854-1870.

name: Phillips, Reginald William
description: British botanist; B.A. Cambr. 1884; Dr. sci. 1898; head Dept. Biol. Bangor 1884; professor of botany ib. until 1922.

name: Phillips, Robert Albert
description: Irish botanist in Cork.

name: Phillips, Walter Sargeant
description: American botanist; AB Oberlin 1929, Dr. phil. Chicago 1935; taught English at Taiku, Shansi, 1929-1931; at University of Chicago 1932, University of Miami 1935, University of Arizona 1940, from 1947-1972 as head of the Department of Botany and curator of the herbarium; student of the Polypodiaceae.

name: Phillips, William
description: British botanist, mycologist and antiquary at Shrewsbury.

name: Phinney, Arthur John
description: American botanist; MD Pulte Med. Coll. 1877; in the Indiana Geological Survey 1881-1886; with the U.S. Geological Survey from 1890; practicing physician at Indianapolis.

page_title_long: Phipps, Constantine John, second baron Mulgrave
page_title_longer_max-80: Phipps, Constantine John, second baron Mulgrave [std. Phipps]
name: Phipps, Constantine John, second baron Mulgrave
name_ed: Phipps, Constantine John, second baron Mulgrave
description: British captain in the Royal Navy; arctic explorer.

name: Phoebus, Philipp
description: German botanist; Dr. med. chir. Berlin 1827; from 1828 practicing physician at Berlin; 1831 prosector at the Charité; 1832 lecturer at the University of Berlin; practicing in the Harz 1835-1843, professor of medicine and pharmacology at Giessen from 1843-1865; Dr. phil. h.c. Giessen 1849; Geh. Medizinalrath 1865.

name: Pia, Julius [von]
description: Austrian palaeobotanist; Dr. phil. Wien 1911; in various functions at the Natural History Museum ib. from 1913 (Volontär), 1916 (assistant), 1928 (Kustos I. Klasse).

name: Picard, Casimir
description: French botanist and physician; studied medicine at Amiens; practicing physician at Abbeville 1828-1841; "administrateur" of the museum of Abbeville; founder of the Société Linnéenne du Nord de la France, 1838.

name: Picard, François
description: French entomologist and mycologist; professor of zoology at the École nationale d'Agriculture, Montpellier 1909-1921; at the Paris Laborat- oire d'évolution des êtres organisés 1921-1939.

name: Picbauer, Richard
description: Moravian mycologist and floristic botanist; teacher at Chvalkovice nr. Olmütz (1908), high school teacher at Olmütz until 1914; in military service 1914-1919; high school teacher at Brünn (Brno) 1919; Dr. phil. 1925 Brünn; from 1923 connected with the agricultural research station Brünn (Brno);

name: Piccioli, Antonio
description: Italian botanist; curator of the Firenze botanical garden.

name: Piccioli, Elvira
description: Italian bryologist and high school teacher at Vittoria Veneto.

name: Piccioli, Giuseppe
description: Italian botanist; curator of a botanical garden at Firenze.

name: Piccioli, Ludovico
description: Italian botanist and forester; forestry inspector in the province of Siena; habil. Univ. Siena 1905; director of the experimental arboreta of Vallombrosa 1913-1922; later professor of silviculture at the Facoltà Agraria e Forestale della R. Università, Firenze.

page_title_longer_max-80: Picco, Vittorio (latinized Picus, gen. Pici) [std. Picco]
name: Picco, Vittorio (latinized: Picus, gen. Pici)
description: Italian botanist and physician at Torino.

name: Piccone, Antonio
description: Italian botanist; high school teacher at the Liceo Cristoforo Colombo in Genova.

name: Pichi-Sermolli, Rodolfo Emilio Giuseppe
description: Italian botanist (pteridologist); Laureato Sci. nat. Firenze 1935; at the Herbarium Universitati Florentinae 1935-1950; from 1957-1959 at Sassari; later at Genova and Perugia.

name: Pichon, Thomas
description: French botanist.

name: Pickard, Joseph Fry
description: British draper, tea merchant and botanist in Yorkshire (Leeds).

name: Pickel, Bento José
description: German-born Brazilian botanist, explorer and plant collector; sometime professor at the agricultural college at Tapera (Pernambuco) and at São Paulo.

name: Pickering, Charles
description: American botanist, zoologist and anthropologist; M.D. Harvard 1826; from 1827-1838 at Philadelphia; from 1838-1842 with Wilkes and Brackenridge on the U.S. Exploring Expedition; in Egypt, India, Arabia and E. Africa 1843-1844; from 1844 residing in Boston.

name: Pickett, Fermen Layton
description: American botanist; Dr. phil. Indiana Univ. 1914; at the Department of Botany at Washington State College from 1914, head of the Department from 1918, dean of the graduate school from 1930.

name: Picquenard, Charles-Armand
description: French botanist; Dr. med. Paris 1900; pupil of Nylander at Paris; settled at Quimper 1900 as practicing physician, ardent amateur naturalist and boy scout leader.

name: Piddington, Henry
description: British meteorologist and botanist; commander in the mercantile marine; from circa 1800 curator of the Museum of economic geology and coroner at Calcutta.

name: Piepenbring, Georg Heinrich
description: German (Kurhessen) pharmacist and botanist at Meinberg (Lippe), Karlshafen (Hessen); later professor of chemistry and pharmacy at Marburg; from 1805 at Rinteln.

name: Pieper, Gustav Robert
description: German botanist.

name: Pieper, Philipp Anton
description: German (Prussian) botanist and practicing physician at Paderborn.

name: Pierce, Newton Barris
description: American phytopathologist for the U.S. government for the Pacific coast region 1889-1906; later private collector and breeder of rare plants at Santa Ana, Calif.

name: Pieri, Michele Trivoli
description: Italian botanist and physician at Corfù.

name: Pierre, Jean Baptiste Louis
description: French botanist, born on Réunion; studied in Paris 1851, in 1855 at Strasbourg; from 1861-1865 at the Calcutta botanical garden; from 1865-1877 director at the Saigon botanical garden, exploring Cambodja, Cochinchina and S. Siam; back to France 1877, living near or in Paris.

name: Pierrot, Philogène
description: French botanist, printer and newspaper publisher at Montmédy near Sedan; sometime burgomaster of the city and county-counsel.

name: Pieters, Adrian John
description: American botanist (plant physiologist and morphologist); Ph.D. Univ. Mich. 1915; assistant botanist USDA, Washington 18951900, botanist ib. 1900-1906; seed grower 1906-1910; instructor in botany Univ. Mich- igan 1912-1915, agronomist Bureau Plant Industry, USDA 1915-1926, principal agronomist 1926-1935; in charge of Lespedeza investigations 1935-1940; one of the founders of the Bureau of Plant Industry 1901; "father of Lespedeza".

name: Pietsch, Friedrich Maximilian
description: German (Saxonian) botanist; Dr. phil. Halle 1893; high school teacher at Gera.

page_title_longer_max-80: Pijl, Leendert van der [std. v.d. Pijl]
name: Pijl, Leendert van der
description: Dutch botanist and flower-biologist; studied at Amsterdam University 1923-1927; high school teacher at Arnhem 1926-1927; to the Netherlands East Indies 1927; high school teacher at Bandung 1927; Dr. phil. Amsterdam 1933; in Japanese captivity during World War II; rector at Bandung Gymnasium 1947; professor of botany at Bandung University 1948-1954; retired to the Hague, Netherlands; professor of botany at Nijmegen 1965-1975.

name: Pike, Nicolas
description: American soldier, herpetologist and algologist; U.S. consul at Porto, Portugal 1856-1866 and Mauritius (1866-1876).

name: Pilar, Georg [Gjuro]
description: Slavonian/Croatian palaeobotanist; professor at Zagreb (Agram) University.

name: Pilát, Albert
description: Czechoslovakian mycologist; Dr. sci. Praha 1926 (with J. Velenovský); from 1930 at the National Museum, Praha, from 1948 as head of the botanical department, from 1965 idem of the mycological department; rad práce (labor medal) CSSR 1969; corr. memb. Czechosl. Acad. Sci. 1959.

name: Pilger, Robert Knuds Friedrich
description: German botanist; Dr. phil. Berlin (with Engler) 1898; collected in Brazil 1898-1900; assistant at Berlin-Dahlem 1900; Custos 1908; habil. Berlin 1908; titular professor 1913, vice-director 1921, director 19451950.

name: Pillans, Neville Stuart
description: South African botanist; studied at Cambridge; at the Bolus Herbarium 1918-1953.

name: Piller, Mathias
description: Austrian botanist and clergyman (S. J.); professor of natural history at the Theresianum in Vienna; later idem in Buda.

name: Pilling, Friedrich Oscar
description: German botanist and pomologist; high school teacher at Altenburg.

name: Pilous, Zdnek
description: Czechoslavak bryologist, Privatgelehrter at Hostinné.

name: Pinatzis, Leonidas
description: Greek field-botanist, born at Kios (Gemlik, Asia minor), came to Greece as a refugee in 1922; energetic botanical explorer of Greece.

name: Pinchot, Gifford
description: American botanist, forester, conservationist and politician, M.A. Yale 1901, M.A. Princeton 1904; studied forestry in France, Germany, Switzerland, Austria; consulting forester 1892-1898; forester USDA 1898-1910, governor of Pennsylvania 1923-1927, 1931-1935.

name: Pinoy, Pierre Ernest
description: French physician and mycologist; Dr. med. Paris 1899, Dr. sci. Paris 1907; professor of microbiology and cryptogamy at the faculty of medecine of Algeria.

page_title_longer_max-80: Pinto, Joaquim de Almeida [std. J. de A. Pinto]
name: Pinto, Joaquim de Almeida
description: Brazilian botanist and pharmacist.

page_title_longer_max-80: Pinto da Silva, Antonio Rodrigo [std. Pinto da Silva]
name: Pinto da Silva, Antonio Rodrigo
description: Portugese agronomic engineer and botanist; at the Estação agronómica nacional, scientific officer from 1937 (at BélemLisboa 1937-1941, Sacavém 1942-1964, at Oeiras 1964-x), lately as investigador- coordenador; member (and chairman) of the Special Committee for Pteridophytes and Phanerogams, later Committee for Spermatophyta 1950-1969).

name: Pio, Giovanni Batista
description: Italian botanist.

name: Piper, Charles Vancouver
description: American botanist; M.Sc. Univ. Washington 1892; professor of botany at Pullman, Washington 1893; M.Sc. Harvard 1900; from 1903 in Washington, D.C., with the Bureau of Plant Industry (forage crop investigations); D.Sc. Kansas Agric. College 1921.

name: Piper, Richard Upton
description: American physician and botanist, MD Dartmouth 1840; practicing physician at Boston and Chicago.

name: Piquet, John
description: British pharmaceutical chemist and botanist at St. Hélier, Jersey.

page_title_longer_max-80: Piré, Louis Alexandre Henri Joseph [std. Piré]
name: Piré, Louis Alexandre Henri Joseph
description: Belgian botanist; high school teacher at the Bruxelles Athenaeum 1854-1883; in retirement at Spa (1884-1887).

name: Pirona, Giulio Andrea
description: Italian botanist; Dr. med. Padova 1846; from 1851-1887 lecturer at the Ginnasio liceale and Udine medical college as well as practicing physician at Udine, from 1887 with the title "professore effetivo".

name: Pirotta, Pietro Romualdo
description: Italian botanist (educated in Pavia); director of the botanic garden at Modena 1880-1883, professor of botany at the University of Roma 1883 (extraord.), 1888. (ord.) and director of the botanic garden until 1928.

name: Piscicelli, Maurizio
description: Italian explorer of northeastern tropical Africa; with the Duchess of Aosta in Somalia 1911.

name: Piso, Willem
description: Dutch physician, pharmacist and botanist; M.D. Caen 1633; practicing physician at Amsterdam; in Brazil as physician of the Dutch settlement (1633-1644) with Johan Maurits van Nassau.

name: Pitard, Charles-Joseph Marie (Pitard-Briau)
description: French botanist; Dr. sci. nat. Bordeaux 1899, pharmacien supérieur 1901; from 1897-1902 at the Faculté des Sciences, Bordeaux; from 1902 curator, from 1904 professor of natural sciences at the École de médecine, Tours; travelled in the Canary Islands (1904/05, 1905/06) and North Africa.

name: Pitcher, Zina
description: American physician and botanist, MD Middlebury College, Vermont 1822; in service on the frontier 1822-1836; later in Michigan; 18371852 regent and professor at the University of Michigan; 1840-1843 mayor of Detroit.

page_title_longer_max-80: Pittier, Henry François (Pittier de Fabrega) [std. Pitt.]
name: Pittier, Henry François (Pittier de Fabrega)
description: Swiss botanist and civil engineer, D. Sc. Lausanne 1885; Ph.D. Jena; at Lausanne 1882-1887; to Costa Rica in 1887; with USDA 1905-1919 exploring Central America, Colombia and Venezuela; from 1919-1950 in Venezuela; naturalized U.S. citizen.

page_title_long: Pittoni, Josef Claudius, Ritter von Dannenfeldt
page_title_longer_max-80: Pittoni, Josef Claudius, Ritter von Dannenfeldt [std. Pittoni]
name: Pittoni, Josef Claudius, Ritter von Dannenfeldt
name_ed: Pittoni, Josef Claudius, Ritter von Dannenfeldt
description: Austrian botanist and administrator ("Truchsess," sheriff).

name: Pizarro, João Joaquim
description: Brazilian physician and botanist; Dr. med. Rio de Janeiro 1872; later professor of natural history at the Rio de Janeiro medical faculty.

name: Planchon, [François] Gustave
description: French botanist and pharmacist; Dr. med. Montpellier 1859; prof. agr. méd. Montpellier 1860, prof. bot. Lausanne 1862; Dr. sci. Paris 1864; Pharm. I. classe 1864; prof. at École de Pharmacie, Montpellier 18641866; prof. École supérieure de Pharmacie de Paris 1866; prof. id. 1886-1900; brother of J.E. Planchon.

name: Planchon, Jules Émile
description: French botanist; Dr. sci. nat. Montpellier 1844; assistant to William Jackson Hooker at Kew 1844-1848; professor of botany at the horticultural institute, Gent, 1849-1851; at the École de Pharmacie, Nancy, 1851-1853; assistant professor at Montpellier succeeding Dunal (Faculté des Sciences) 1853-1857), professor at id. as well as at the École de Pharmacie 1857-1881; at the Faculté de Médecine and director of the botanical garden, Montpellier 1881-1888; discovered Phylloxera 1868.

name: Planchon, Louis David
description: French botanist at Montpellier; Dr. méd. Montpellier 1883; Pharm. sup. 1891, Dr. sci. 1900; from 1882-1894 at the Faculté de méde- cine; aggr. pharm. Paris 1894; associated with the École Supérieure de pharmacie, Montpellier 1883-1915; from 1901 as professor of matera medica; son of J.E. Planchon.

name: Planellas Giralt, José
description: Spanish botanist; studied at Santiago; Dr. sci. nat. Madrid 1879; until 1883 professor of natural history at Barcelona; later director of the botanical garden and professor of botany at Habana, Cuba (1883-1886).

name: Planer, Johann Jacob
description: German (Saxonian) botanist and physician; Dr. med. Erfurt 1778; prosector (1773), later professor (extraord. 1779, ord. 1783) of botany and chemistry at the University of Erfurt.

name: Platen, Paul Louis
description: German palaeobotanist; student of J.P. Felix at Leipzig.

name: Plawski, Alexander
description: Polish botanist.

name: Playfair, George Israel
description: Australian algologist; honorary curator of freshwater algae at the National Herbarium, Sydney, Australia.

name: Plaz, Anton Wilhelm
description: German (Saxonian) botanist; Dr. med. Halle 1728; extraord. professor of botany Leipzig 1733, ord. id. 1749; later professor of physiology and therapeutics; dean of the medical faculty from 1773.

name: Plée, Auguste
description: French traveller for the Paris Muséum d'Histoire naturelle; from 1820-1825 in the West Indies.

name: Plée, François
description: French botanical artist and author.

name: Pleijel, Carl Gerhard Wilhelm
description: Swedish pharmacist and botanist at Alvesta, Småland (1911-1920), pharmacist at Stockholm 1920-1936.

name: Plenck, Joseph Jacob von [Plenk]
description: Austrian botanist, military physician, teacher at the military medical academy of Vienna.

name: Plitt, Charles Christian
description: American lichenologist and bryologist; Ph.G. (pharmacy) Maryland College Pharmacy 1891; Dr. sci. 1921 Int. Acad. Sci., Baltimore; teacher at various public schools in Baltimore, later at Baltimore City College; ultimately professor of botany at the University of Maryland.

name: Plitzka, Alfred
description: Austrian-Silesian/Moravian botanist; high school teacher at Neutitschein (Nový Jicín) 1894-1903.

name: Plowright, Charles Bagge
description: British botanist and physician; MD Durham 1890; medical officer of health, Freebridge Lynn Rural District Council; from 1892-1894 Hunterian professor of comparative anatomy and physiology at the London Royal College of Surgeons.

name: Plues, Margaret
description: British botanist; entered a roman catholic convent at Weybridge in middle-age, ultimately mother superior; in her youth a popular writer on botany.

name: Plukenet, Leonard
description: British botanist and physician, probably educated at Westminster School; practicing physician in London, later Queen's botanist to Mary II (wife of Willem III) and superintendent of Hampton Court.

name: Plumier, Charles
description: French missionary, explorer and botanist; travelled in the West Indies 1689, 1693 and 1695.

name: Plummer, Sarah Allen
description: American botanist and plant collector, active in California; married John Gill Lemmon in 1880.

name: Pluskal (Pluska-Moravicanský), Franiscek Sal.
description: Moravian botanist; practicing physician at Lomnitz 1839-1857; later in Welechrad.

name: Pluszczewski, Emile
description: French pharmacist and botanist; curator at the Paris École supérieure de Pharmacie; Pharm, prem. cl. 1885.

name: Pobedimova, Evgeniia Georgievna
description: Russian botanist at the Komarov Botanical Institute; travelled in Central Asia (1932), Mongolia (1930, 1931), Caucasia (1946, 1949), Altai (1953) and Crimea (1947, 1949).

name: Pobéguin, Charles Henri Oliver
description: French botanist and colonial administrator in French Africa (Ivory Coast, Comores, Guinea, Equatorial Africa, Congo) 1892-1923.

name: Pocock, Mary Agard
description: South African phycologist; B.S. botany London University 1908 (honors degree ibid. 1921), high school teacher at Cheltenham 19091912, at Wijnberg (Cape) Girl's High School 1913-1917; worked with A.C. Seward at Cambridge 1919-1921; temporary lecturer at various South African universities and colleges from 1923 onward; turned to algology 1928 (Ph.D. 1932 Univ. Cape Town), D.Sc. h.c. Rhodes Univ. 1967.

name: Podpera, Josef
description: Czechoslovak (Bohemian) botanist; studied at the Charles University, Praha 1897-1903; Dr. phil. Praha 1903; teacher of classical languages at various colleges 1903-1914, from 1914-1920 prisoner of war in Russia and the Soviet Union, part of the time at the botanical institute of Ufa (n. Tomsk); from 1921 professor of botany at Brno; member Acad. Sci. [fix]SR 1953.

name: Poech, Josef [Alois]
description: Bohemian botanist, born at Snedovice (Wegstädl) nr Praha, studied medicine, assistant to the botanical cabinet of Praha University; associated with Opiz.

page_title_long: Poederlé, Eugène Joseph Charles Gilain Hubert dOlmen baron de
page_title_longer_max-80: Poederlé, Eugène Joseph Charles Gilain Hubert dOlmen baron de [std. Poederlé]
name: Poederlé, Eugène Joseph Charles Gilain Hubert d'Olmen baron de
name_ed: Poederlé, Eugène Joseph Charles Gilain Hubert dOlmen baron de
description: Belgian landed gentleman, botanist, sylviculturist and agronomist living in Bruxelles and on his property at Saintes.

name: Pöll, Josef
description: Austrian hieraciologist; high school teacher at Bludenz and Innsbruck; later professor at the Innsbruck teacher's college.

name: Poellnitz, Karl von
description: German agriculturist and botanist; studied at Leipzig University; specialist in succulent plants; owner of an estate at Oberlödla nr Altenburg, Thüringen.

name: Poeppig, Eduard Friedrich
description: German botanist, zoologist and explorer; studied natural sciences (Dr. phil.) at Leipzig; travelled in Cuba (1822-1824), Pennsylvania (1824-1826), Chile (1827-1829), Peru and Brazil (1829-1832); professor of philo- sophy, zoology and botany at Leipzig (extraord., 1833, ord. 1846), director of the zo- ological institute 1834; curator of the natural history collections and director of the botanical garden.

name: Poetsch, [Pötsch], Ignaz Sigismund
description: Bohemian-born Austrian botanist and physician; Dr. med. Wien 1849; until 1852 working in various hospitals in Wien; 1852-1854 practicing in Gaming; from 1854-1877 physician (Stifts– und Convictsarzt) at Kremsmünster; from 1875-1884 in retirement at Randegg.

name: Poeverlein, Hermann
description: German administrator and botanist; Dr. jur. Erlangen 1898; in the judiciary and administration at Ludwigshafen (1904, assistant judge), Kemnath (1916) and Speyer (1919, Regierungsrat; 1932 Regierungsdirektor); from 1934 in semi-retirement at Augsburg; from 1941 retired, from 1945/6 at Karxheimzell and later at Ludwigshafen; specialist on Uredinales.

name: Poggenburg, Justus Ferdinand
description: German-born (Hannover) American botanist; at his death business manager of the "New Yorker Staats Zeitung".

name: Pohl, Johann [Baptist] Emanuel
description: Bohemian-born Austrian botanist and traveller; Dr. med. Praha 1808; army physician 1809-1811; at the garden of J.M. de Canal (Freiherr von Hochberg) 1811-1817; travelled in Brazil with Spix, Martius et al. 1817-1821; afterwards curator at the Vienna Natural History Museum and the Vienna Brasilian Museum.

name: Pohl, Johann Ehrenfried
description: German (Saxonian) physician and botanist; professor of botany at Leipzig; from 1788 royal physician at Dresden.

name: Pohl, Julius
description: German botanist; professor of pharmacology at the German University of Prag (1895).

name: Pohle, Richard Richardowich
description: German-Latvian botanist, born in Riga of German parents; in military service at Berlin 1889/90; studied at Dresden Technical University 1894-1899, from 1895-1899 also assistant at the Dresden Botanical Institute; travelled in N. Europe 1898-1899; at University of Rostock 1900-1901; Dr. phil. ib. 1901; until 1914 at the Botanic Garden St. Petersburg; later professor of geography at the Technical University of Braunschweig.

name: Poirault, [Marie Henri] Georges
description: French botanist; son of J.P.F. Poirault; on oceanographic voyage of Talisman, 1883; with A.S. Famintzin, St. Petersburg 1886-1888; Dr. sci. Paris 1894; at Mus. Hist. nat. Paris, 1888-1889; director of the Villa Thuret at Antibes 1899-1936.

name: Poirault, Jules Pierre François
description: French pharmacist and botanist; professor at the École de Médecine and director of the botanic garden at Poitiers.

name: Poiret, Jean Louis Marie
description: French clergyman and botanist; travelled in North Africa 1785-1786.

name: Poisson, Henri [-Louis]
description: French botanist; in Madagascar 1916-1954 as veterinary surgeon and inspector (1921-1934) and amateur botanist; Dr. sci. nat. Paris 1912.

name: Poisson, Jules
description: French botanist; at the Paris Muséum d'Histoire naturelle from 1843 (sic "élève jardinier") until 1909, from 1864 as "préparateur" (botany), from 1873 aide-naturaliste.

name: Poiteau, Pierre Antoine
description: French botanist and botanical artist; gardener at the Jardin des Plantes, Paris 1790; from 1796-1801 at Haiti; subsequently at the botanical garden of the École de médecine and (1855) Chef des Pépinières (Versailles); from 1819-1822 in French Guiana; 1820 professor at an agricultural college in Fromont; ultimately active as editor for the Société d'Horticulture.

name: Poivre, Pierre
description: French plant collector and administrator, travelling and collecting in China (1739-1745), Indochina, the Moluccas, the Philippines and Madagascar, for the French East India Company from 1748-1757, in France as agriculturist 1757-1767; from 1767-1773 "intendant" of Réunion and Ile de France; from 1773 again in France

name: Pokorny, Alois
description: Bohemian-born Austrian botanist; studied at the University of Wien 1844-1848; worked at the natural history museum (W) 1848-1849; from 1849-1886 high school teacher in Vienna, until 1864 at the academic Gymnasium, then director of the Realgymnasium of Wien-II; Dr. phil. Göttingen 1855; id. and habil. Wien 1857; lectured phytogeography at the University 1857-1868; developed nature printing with von Ettingshausen.

name: Polakowsky, Helmuth
description: German botanist; until 1880 in Berlin.

name: Pole-Evans, Illtyd (Iltyd) Buller
description: British-born mycologist; M.A. Cantab.; South Africa 1905; mycologist to Transvaal Govt. 1905-1911; Chief Div. Mycology & Plant Pathology, Dept. Agr. S. Afr. 1911-1918; Director Botanical Survey S. Afr. 1918-1939; L.L.D. hon. Witwatersrand 1933.

name: Polgár, Sándor
description: Hungarian lichenologist; Dr. phil. Budapest 1913.

name: Polívka, Frantisek
description: Czech botanist; high school teacher at Olomouc (Olmütz).

name: Pollacci, Gino
description: Italian botanist; assistant at the Botanical Garden, Pavia (1896); habil. ib. 1903; lecturer at the botanical institute Pavia 1910-1913, at the cryptogamic laboratory ib. 1913-1915; in the Italian army 1915-1919; interim-director bot. inst. and garden 1919-1920; extraordinary professor of botany at Sassari 1920-1921; id. at Siena (also dir. bot. gard.) 1921-1927; from 1927-1942 director of the botanical in- stitute and cryptogamic laboratory Pavia

name: Pollard, Charles Louis
description: American botanist; AM Colombia Univ. 1894; curator of plants U.S. natl. Mus. 1895-1903.

name: Pollexfen, John Hutton
description: British physician and algologist; MD Edinburgh 1835, B.A. Cantab. 1843; ordained 1844, from then on clergyman at Colchester, East Wetton and from 1874-1899 vicar at the parish of Middleton Tyas.

name: Pollich, Johann Adam
description: German botanist and physician at Kaiserslautern; Dr. med. Strassbourg 1763; from 1764 devoting himself solely to natural his- tory.

name: Pollini, Ciro
description: Italian botanist and physician; curator of the Verona botanical garden; teacher at the Verona Lyceum.

name: Polscher, W.
description: German (Prussian) high school teacher at Duisburg.

name: Polunin, Nicholas Vladimir
description: British botanist, ecologist and conservationist; D.Sc. Oxon.; demonstrator and lecturer in botany Oxford 1938-1947; McDonald professor of botany, McGill Univ. 1947-1952; director Baghdad University Herbarium 1955- 1958; guest prof. bot. Geneva 1959-1961; professor of botany Univ. of Ife, Nigeria 1962- 1966.

name: Pomata y Gisbert, Eladio
description: Spanish botanist.

name: Pomel, Auguste Nicolas
description: French botanist and geologist; deported to Algeria 1852; in various administrative functions 1856-1870; in various political posts in Algeria and Paris 1870-1880; in the "Service" of the geological mapping of Algeria 1882, director 1885-1895.

page_title_long: Ponce de Leon y Aimé, Antonio
page_title_longer_max-80: Ponce de Leon y Aimé, Antonio [std. A. Ponce de Leon]
name: Ponce de Leon y Aimé, Antonio
name_ed: Ponce de Leon y Aimé, Antonio
description: Cuban botanist; Dr. Sci. Habana 1906; high school teacher until 1934, then professor of botany at Habana University; founder of the Sociedad Cubána de botánica (1945).

name: Poneropoulos, Eustathios
description: Greek botanist.

name: Pontarlier, Nicolas Charles
description: French botanist; studied at the Lycée Saint-Louis, Paris; at École norm. sup. 1831; régent Collège des Palmiers 1833, chargé de cours, Coll. r. Bourbon-Vendée 1839; régent Col. Vannes; at Lycée de NapoleonVendée, La Roche-sur-Yon 1848-1878.

name: Pontén, Johan (Jon) Peter
description: Swedish botanist, physician and clergyman; Dr. phil. Greifswald 1800, ordained 1801, parish priest at Hultsjö from 1826, at Korsberga from 1837.

name: Pool, Raymond John
description: American botanist; Dr. phil. Univ. Nebraska 1913; professor of botany and chairman, Department of Botany, University of Nebraska 19151948.

name: Pop, Emil
description: Roumanian botanist; Dr. phil. Cluj 1928; habil. ib. 1932; connected with the chair of systematic botany, Cluj from 1920 (assistant 1922, professor 1939).

page_title_longer_max-80: Pope, Clara Maria (née Leigh) [std. C. Pope]
name: Pope, Clara Maria (née Leigh)
description: British flower painter, wife of the actor Alexander Pope (Francis Wheatley).

name: Pope, Willis Thomas
description: American botanist and horticulturist; M.S. Univ. Calif., D. Sci. Univ. Hawaii; horticulturist at USDA Hawaii Experiment Station.

page_title_longer_max-80: Popenoe, Dorothy Kate (née Hughes) [std. D. Popenoe]
name: Popenoe, Dorothy Kate (née Hughes)
description: British-born botanist; assistant at Kew 1918-1923 as collaborator of O. Stapf; to USDA Washington 1923; married Frederick Wilson Popenoe (17 Nov 1923).

page_title_longer_max-80: Popenoe, Frederick Wilson (called Wilson Popenoe) [std. Popenoe]
name: Popenoe, Frederick Wilson (called Wilson Popenoe)
description: American botanist and explorer; studied at Pomona College; agricultural explorer for USDA from 19131923; with the United Fruit Company from 1923-1957; from 1944 as director of the Escuela Agricola Panamericana, Honduras.

name: Poplu, Mme M.C.
description: French botanist.

name: Popov, Mikhail Grigorievič
description: Russian botanist and explorer of the flora of the Asiatic part of the Soviet Union.

name: Popovici, Alexandru P.
description: Rumanian botanist, professor of botany at the University of Jassi; pupil of W. Pfeffer; Dr. phil. Bonn 1893.

name: Popp, Bonifaz
description: German (Bavarian) botanist, Benedictine monk and high school teacher at Scheyern, Bayern.

name: Porcher, Francis Peyre
description: American botanist; M.D. Univ. S. Carolina 1847; studied in Paris and Italy 1847-1849; practicing physician in Charleston 18491895.

name: Porcius, Florian
description: Transylvanian botanist at Ó-Radna (Rodna); high school teacher in Zagra and Naszód; from 1849 in the civil service in various functions, from 1861-1877 at Naszód; in retirement at O-Radna.

name: Forsch, Otto
description: Austrian botanist (flower biologist); Student of R. Wettstein; Dr. phil. Wien 1901; at the Botanical Institute, Graz 1900-1903 (with Haberlandt); 1903-1911 at the Botanical Institute of Vienna Univ.; habil. Wien 1906; from 1911-1919 at the University of Czernowitz (Cernæuti); from 1919 at the Hochschule für Bodenkultur, Wien (from 1938 full professor); in Java Jan-Jun 1914.

name: Porsild, Alf Erling
description: Danish botanist, naturalized Canadian from 1939; son of M.P. Porsild; assistant botanist at the Danish biological station, Greenland 19221925; botanist in charge of surveys, Canadian Dept. of the Interior 1926-1935; at Nat- ional Herbarium of Canada, Ottawa from 1936-1966; Dr. phil. Kjøbenhavn 1955 id. h.c. Acadia 1967, Waterloo 1973.

name: Porsild, Morton Pedersen
description: Danish botanist; mag. sci. Kjøbenhavn 1900; director of the Danish Arctic biological station at Disko from 1906 (1905)-1946.

name: Porta, Pietro
description: Italian botanist and clergyman; in Vallaria 1856; later priest at Bolone, Val Vestino, Trento; explored S. Tirol, Spain, the Balearic Is. with R. Huter and G. Rigo; ultimately living in Cologna di Creto.

name: Portenschlag-Ledermayer, Franz [Edler] von
description: Austrian botanist; studied law, abandoned his career as a lawyer to practice botany; botanical explorer of the Austrian empire.

name: Porter, Carlos Emilio
description: Chilean naturalist; director of the zoology dept. of the Museo de Historia natural Valparaiso 1897-1910; natural history teacher at various colleges in Valparaiso and Santiago, e.g. at the Santiago military academy 1912-1918 and at the Institute agronómico de Chile 1901-1927; director of the zoological museum of the Institute 1914-1927, head of the invertebrate section of the Museo nacional 19121923, id. entomology section 1924-927; professor of animal parasitology at the Faculty of Agronomy 1919-1939.

name: Porter, Cedric Lambert
description: American botanist; Dr. phil. Univ. Washington 1937; instructor in botany Univ. Wyoming 1929-1932, professor of botany ib. 19321968.

page_title_longer_max-80: Porter, Lilian E. (née Baker) [std. L. Porter]
name: Porter, Lilian E. (née Baker)
description: Irish lichenologist, daughter of John Gilbert Baker (1834-1920); M.Sc. Liverpool 1911; lecturer Bangor 1913-1916; demonstrator biol. Cork 1916-1919; examiner Nat. Univ. Ireland 1921-1945.

name: Porter, Thomas Conrad
description: American botanist; Dr. Div. Rutgers 1865; presbyterian clergyman, ordained 1843 or 1844, practicing 1846-1849; from 1849-1860 teaching natural sciences at Marshall and Franklin College, Mercersburg/Lancaster; from 1866-1897 professor of botany and zoology at Lafayette College, Pa. and minister at Easton, Pa. 1877-1884,; German scholar and poet.

name: Porterfield, Willard Merritt, Jr.
description: American ethnobotanist; M.A. Franklin and Marshall College, Lancaster, Pa. 1915; teaching missionary in China; professor of biology St. John's University, Shanghai around 1933-1936; later connected with the Univ. Vermont Agric. Exp. Station, the New York Botanical Garden and the Soil Conservation Service of USA; with the C.I.A. during World War I and until 1963; Research consultant George Washington University 1963-1966.

name: Poscharsky, Gustav Adolf
description: German gardener, botanist and plant collector; royal Saxonian garden inspector at the Dresden botanical garden 1866; ultimately living at Magyar Ovár (Ungarisch Altenberg).

name: Poselger, Heinrich
description: German chemist and botanist; collector and student of succulent plants, collected plants on and near the U.S. and Mexican boundary 18491851; living on private means in Berlin, growing a rich collection of cacti and succulents.

name: Pospichal, Eduard
description: Bohemian-born Austrian botanist, sometime teacher at Litomyšl and, longtime at Triest.

name: Pospíšil, Valentin
description: Czechoslovak (Moravian) botanist (bryologist, geobotanist) at the Moravian museum at Brno.

page_title_longer_max-80: Post, Ernst Jacob Lennart von [std. L. Post]
name: Post, Ernst Jacob Lennart von
description: Swedish phytogeographer and geologist, one of the founders of pollen analysis and; Fil. lic. Uppsala 1904; State geologist 1910 (1914); Dr. h.c. Stockholm 1927; professor of geology at Stockholm 1929.

name: Post, George Edward
description: American physician, missionary and botanist; educated at New York Free Academy (City College), Univ. of New York medical dept., and at Union Theological Seminary; Dr. med. New York 1860; professor of surgery in the Syrian protestant College, Beirut and surgeon to the Johanniter Hospital, Beirut 1868-1909.

page_title_longer_max-80: Post, Hampus Adolf von [std. H. v. Post]
name: Post, Hampus Adolf von
